title: fish chowder
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Place all ingredients except half and half in a large kettle.
Cook slowly until potatoes are done and fish flakes.
Add 1 pint of scalded half and half (light cream) to finished chowder.
Let sit for 15 minutes or more for flavors to absorb into the cream.

title: mussels marinara
directions: In a large flameproof casserole, heat the oil. Add the garlic and cook over moderate heat until lightly browned, 3 to 5 minutes. Add the mussels, tomatoes, parsley and oregano.
Bring to a boil. Reduce the heat to moderate.
Cover and simmer, stirring occasionally, until the mussels open, 5 to 7 minutes.
Using a slotted spoon, transfer the mussels to soup bowls.
Discard any that do not open.
Season the sauce with salt and pepper to taste. Ladle the sauce over the mussels and serve hot.
Serve with Caprice Salad, hard Italian rolls and a hearty Chianti.
Makes 4 servings.

title: boiled mustard greens
directions: Boil mustard greens in 1-quart water, covered, until tender, about 1 hour.
Stir in margarine and pepper and serve.

title: pecan pie
directions: Heat 5 minutes on low, all ingredients and pour into an uncooked pie shell.
Bake 1 hour at 325° until a knife comes out clean.
Pie should sit until cool.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix stuffing with cornbread, sauteed onion and melted butter. Use half the stuffing mixture and put in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Put diced chicken over dressing.

title: shrimp cucumber spread
directions: Mix together all ingredients until well blended.
Chill. Serve with assorted crackers.

title: hearty roast and vegetables
directions: Trim excess fat from beef. Rub Dutch oven with fat cut from beef; cook beef in Dutch oven until brown. Sprinkle with seasoned salt, marjoram, celery seed, pepper and garlic; add water. Heat to boiling; reduce heat. Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef in pan; add taco seasoning and 1/2 cup water.
Cook and drain.
In large bowl, toss hamburger, lettuce, tomato and cheese.
Crush Doritos while still in bag, add to mixture and toss.
In separate bowl, mix French and Viva dressings; pour over salad and toss again.
Serve with garlic bread.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
Mix with rice.
Separate crescent rolls.
Place side by side in pizza pan and press together to form crust.
Combine eggs, rice and seasoning; set aside.
Spoon rice and sausage mixture over crust.
Top with cheese and pour egg mixture over all.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: clam chowder
directions: Melt butter over low heat.
When completely melted, add sifted flour until you have a thick paste; set aside.
In a large soup pot, boil potatoes for 20 minutes; strain.
While potatoes are boiling, saute onion, celery and mushrooms for 5 minutes.
Add to the soup pot full of potatoes the clam juice, clams, onion, celery and mushrooms.
Add all spices; bring to a boil for 10 minutes. Lower heat and simmer for 20 minutes.

title: pork chops in sauce
directions: Spread mustard on both sides of chops. Saut in butter until brown. Remove from pan. Saut onion in drippings. Add flour and stir. Blend in consomm. Add half and half and dill weed. Salt and pepper to taste. Cover and cook over low heat for 55 minutes. Serve over rice or noodles.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain (put in buttered casserole dish). Melt cheese and 1/2 stick margarine.
Stir cheese mixture and pour over broccoli.
Crush crackers mixed with margarine (melted) over casserole mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in salted water for 5 minutes; drain well. Combine with remaining ingredients and pour into 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with 1 cup cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: orange salad
directions: Bring orange jello and canned crushed pineapple to a boil.
Let boil 1 minute.
Set aside and let cool.
Mix 2 cups buttermilk and Cool Whip.
Then mix all ingredients together and let chill for a few hours.

title: master pie shell
directions: Mix dry ingredients thoroughly, add shortening., then water by spoonsful.
Bake at 475 degrees until lightly browned, about 8 minutes.

title: rhubarb cherry jam
directions: Mix rhubarb and sugar well. Cover and let set overnight.
Boil for 6 minutes. Add cherry pie filling and jello.
Stir until jello is dissolved. Put in jars and seal.

title: easy shoyu chicken wings
directions: Combine all ingredients. Bring to a boil. Add chicken wings and simmer for 35 minutes.

title: orange fluff
directions: Mix first four (4) ingredients and bring to a rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Place pan with mixture into another pan of cold water.
Fold in Cool Whip and pour over oranges in a bowl.
Refrigerate.

title: meringue
directions: Mix 2 tablespoons sugar, cornstarch and water.
Cook over low heat until thick and clear.
Beat egg whites until soft peaks form; add 6 tablespoons sugar, one at a time.
Add first mixture to egg whites and beat until stiff.

title: quick banana pudding
directions: Melt butter with sugar, egg, vanilla and 1 cup milk on low heat.
Sift in flour and on medium heat, bring to boil until thickens.
Add bananas and cookies.

title: finger paints
directions: Mix together the flour and the salt in a medium saucepan.
Add the cold water to the dry ingredients.
Beat with an eggbeater until smooth.
Add the hot water.
Boil until glossy with the consistency of thick starch (5 to 10 minutes) or heavy cream sauce.
Keep refrigerated.

title: epicurean beef casserole
directions: Combine beef, wine, consomme, salt, pepper and onions in casserole.
Mix crumbs with flour and stir into meat.
Cover and bake in a slow oven (300°) for about 3 hours or until beef is tender.
Serves 6.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli 5 minutes after it comes to a boil.
Drain well. Mix soup, cheese, onion, egg, mayonnaise and seasonings.
Pour over broccoli and mix well.
Pour into buttered casserole dish. Top with Ritz crackers and butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mexican white cheese dip
directions: In a saucepan over med. low heat add milk, cheese and jalapeno's, stirring constantly.
Serve with favorite tortilla chips.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Mix ingredients together and stuff into cleaned and capped bell peppers.
(You can make meatballs with the remaining meat mixture.)

title: morning glorious muffins
directions: In a medium bowl, combine flour, sugar, cinnamon and baking soda.
In a separate bowl, toss together carrots, apples, coconut and pecans.
Stir in eggs, oil, vanilla and salt.
Add dry ingredients and blend.

title: kartoffel salat(german potato salad)
directions: Dice cooked potatoes into small chunks, approximately 1/2-inch square.
Dice onion.
Place both in bowl.
Mix the vinegar, oil, water, sugar, flour, salt and pepper in small bowl.
Pour this mixture over the potatoes and onions.
Mix and serve.

title: pesto cheese spread
directions: *Cream cheese may be used.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Mix well and press into bottom of lightly greased (buttered) 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool and set aside.
Dissolve jello and boiling water. Add strawberries.
Chill until thickened.
Cream sugar and cream cheese.
Prepare whip topping.
Fold topping with cream cheese mixture.
Pour partially set jello and strawberry mixture over cooled pretzel crust and chill.
After jello is set, spread cream cheese layer over top.
Sprinkle a few crushed pretzels over top. Serves 10 to 12.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken breasts in bottom of a long dish.
Mix cream of chicken, cream and celery and milk together; pour on chicken, then sprinkle dressing mix over top.
Add margarine by slicing over top of dressing mix.
Salt and pepper.
Bake at 450° until brown.

title: harvard beets
directions: Melt butter.
Add cornstarch, sugar and salt.
Then add vinegar and cook until thick.
Add beets last and serve while warm.

title: chocolate sour cream cake
directions: Beat first five ingredients well.
Add eggs and sour cream and beat.
Bake in greased Bundt or tube pan at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool 1 hour before serving.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Sprinkle on onion soup.
Stir in water; simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Put everything else, except chips and dressing, in a bowl.
Spoon on meat mixture.
Add chips and dressing; mix up before serving.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients.
Shape mixture into balls, then layer balls in a large pot.
Mix together Karo and ketchup. Simmer at medium heat for 30 minutes.
Add lemon juice and simmer for 1 hour.
Stir gently after meatballs have firmed.

title: georgia blueberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Beat egg thoroughly.
Stir in milk, blueberries and oil.
Combine dry ingredients and add to liquid mixture, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened; batter will be lumpy.
Spoon batter into greased or paper-lined muffin pans, filling cups about 3/4 full.
Bake for 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Yields 8 to 12.

title: strawberry hard sauce(serve over cake, puddings, etc.)
directions: Sift the cup of sugar.
Cream the butter until soft and then blend sugar and butter gradually.
Beat in cream.
Stir in berries until well blended.
Refrigerate several hours before using.

title: asparagus with sesame and pine nuts
directions: Clean and prepare asparagus.
Heat oils over medium-high heat. Add ginger and cook for 1 minute.
Add asparagus and salt; cook 5 to 7 minutes, tossing occasionally until asparagus is crisp-tender.

title: dilly casserole bread
directions: In mixing bowl, soften yeast in warm water.
Add cottage cheese, sugar, onion, butter, dill seed, salt, baking soda and egg.
Add flour to form a stiff dough, beating well after each addition.
Cover; let rise in warm place until doubled in size, about 1 hour.
Stir dough down.
Turn into well-greased loaf pan or round casserole dish.
Cover; let rise in a warm place until light, about 45 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Turn out onto wire rack.
Brush with butter.

title: red kidney bean salad
directions: Drain kidney beans and place in a shallow bowl.
Slice green pepper into strips.
Cut onion up into strips.
Add vinegar so that beans, peppers and onions can marinate.
Add salt and pepper for flavor.

title: make ahead fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple juice into 2-cup glass measure.
Add orange juice to make 1 cup.
Blend in cornstarch and honey.
Microwave on High, uncovered, 3 to 3 1/2 minutes or until mixture boils and thickens, stirring twice.
Stir in lemon juice. Cool. Combine pineapple chunks with mandarin oranges, apple, bananas, grapes and marshmallows in a large serving bowl.
Mix lightly. Add thickened fruit juice mixture and yogurt.
Mix just until fruit is coated evenly.
Cover and refrigerate until thoroughly chilled. If desired, transfer to lettuce lined bowl for serving.

title: broiled tuna balls
directions: Mix all ingredients, tearing up bread into small pieces.
Form into 6 to 8 balls.
Place on broiler pan and broil until golden brown.
Spray pan with Pam.

title: south of the border dip
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Drain well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 20 to 30 minutes.
Great served with nacho chips.

title: quiche
directions: Half cook bacon; half cook onion (separately).
Cover bottom of pan with crescent rolls.
Beat eggs with cream; pour over dough. Sprinkle with cheese, onion and then bacon.
Sprinkle with parsley flakes.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: danish cucumbers
directions: Peel and slice cucumbers real thin.
Layer in bowl with salt. Set another bowl on top of cucumbers and weight down.
Let stand several hours; drain and wash off salt.
Put in glass jar.
Add a little sugar and pepper and 1/2 jar vinegar, then fill with water. Stir good and refrigerate.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix meat, eggs, crackers, onion and salt together.
Add milk, then let set until all is absorbed and moist.
Make in a loaf; place in baking dish or pan.
Pour tomato juice over the loaf. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: ranch spinach dip
directions: Mix dip mix with sour cream.
Add spinach and water chestnuts.
Mix together and chill 1 hour before serving.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients in a large bowl and then add other ingredients.
Batter will make 3 to 4 dozen muffins.

title: cincinnati chili
directions: Heat a 12-quart heavy stockpot and add the oil. Saute the hamburger, onions, garlic, cumin seed, chili powder and bay leaves until the meat is barely browned and the onions are clear.
Drain the fat and discard.

title: no-bake cookies
directions: Mix margarine, milk and sugar in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil and boil 4 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in cocoa, vanilla and oats.
Drop on wax paper.
Remove when cookies are set.

title: pumpkin-hazelnut crunch pie
directions: In a large bowl, mix pumpkin, sugar, cinnamon, ginger and nutmeg.
Add eggs.
Beat lightly with fork.
Stir in sour cream and milk; mix well.
In a medium bowl, combine brown sugar and melted margarine; stir in nuts.
Pour filling into pastry shell. Sprinkle evenly with nut topping.
Bake at 375° for about 45 minutes.
Cover and chill to store.

title: meringue ice cream cake with strawberries
directions: Do not preheat oven. Butter two 10-inch spring-form pans.

title: german dish
directions: Dumplings:
Use as directed on back of Bisquick box.

title: sugar-free cookies
directions: Combine sweetener with orange juice.
Cream oleo and add orange juice mixture.
Add the rest of ingredients.
Shape into a roll and chill.
Cut in 1/8-inch slices and put on cookie sheet. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes or until edges are brown.

title: french dressing
directions: Mix well in blender.
Use for tossed salads, chicken, etc. Store unused salad dressing in refrigerator.

title: lemon or chocolate delight
directions: Mix the flour, margarine and nuts together; spread in a greased 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake for 20 minutes.

title: pecan icebox cookies
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly.
Shape into long rolls about 2-inches in diameter.
Place on platter.
Cover and leave in refrigerator overnight.
Slice thin and bake in hot oven until light brown.

title: johnson family salad
directions: Thoroughly drain pineapple as dry as possible.
Stir pineapple and marshmallows into dressing and refrigerate overnight.

title: mince-walnut pie
directions: In a large bowl, beat eggs.
Combine sugar, flour and salt; gradually stir into eggs.
Add butter, walnuts and mincemeat; mix well.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes. Reduce heat to 325°; bake 50 minutes longer, or until filling is slightly puffed and firm.
Refrigerate any leftovers.

title: firehouse chili for a large group
directions: In large soup kettle, brown ground beef and sausage with onion and bell peppers.
Drain any excess grease and then add remaining ingredients.
Heat to a full boil, then reduce heat and simmer on low for 1 to 2 hours.
Season to taste.
Serve with Fritos and grated cheese.

title: crackling cowboy cornbread
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and mix well.
Add milk, eggs and vegetable oil.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased cast-iron skillet.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: grilled onions
directions: Peel onions and cut each until almost quartered (leave enough to hold each onion together).
Place each in a large square of heavy-duty foil.
Put one bouillon cube and 1 tablespoon of margarine in the center of each onion.
Add a few drops of Worcestershire and pepper to each.
Close foil as tightly as possible.
Grill over hot coals for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve.

title: apple crisp
directions: Put apples in buttered dish and sprinkle with lemon juice. Combine dry ingredients and butter and mix until crumbly.
Spread over apples.
Bake 30 minutes at 375°.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Sift dry ingredients.
Stir in eggs, strawberries and oil and mix well.
Add pecans.
Pour into two well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake for about 1 hour or until bread tests done.
Cool in pan for 5 minutes and then cool on wire rack.
Yields 14 to 16 slices per loaf.
Freezes well.

title: all american barbecue sauce
directions: Put onion and margarine in a four cup pan and cook for 2 minutes on high.
Stir.
Cook on high for 2 to 3 minutes more until the onion is tender.

title: hot cole slaw
directions: Heat first 5 ingredients to boiling.
Pour over cabbage, bell pepper and onion tossed with olive oil.

title: spritz
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add unbeaten egg and extract.
Mix in dry ingredients and put through cookie press.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Combine the first 2 ingredients and thicken.
Add remaining ingredients. Garnish with sour cream mixed with horseradish to taste.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Mix and bake cornbread.
Cook and crumble sausage.
Crumble as it cooks; drain off grease by pouring water over it, to get all of it.
Chop pickles, tomato, onion and pepper.
Add mayonnaise and pickle juice.
Stir in sausage.
Add cornbread. Toss.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni with 1/2 cup salt until tender.
Drain and rinse with water.
Melt butter in kettle; stir in flour until smooth. Add milk and cook until thickened.
Add remaining salt (1/4 cup) paprika, pepper and cheese.
Cook until cheese melts.
Stir in macaroni.
Pour into greased baking pan.
Garnish with pimento strips.
Bake for 30 minutes or until brown in a 375° oven. Yield: 50 to 55 servings.

title: neck bones and noodles
directions: Boil neck bones for 1 to 2 hours, until meat falls off the bone, in water that contains onion, celery and pepper.
Drain and mix with the noodles and soup.
Good with slaw.

title: italian vegetables packet
directions: You will also need 1 sheet (18 x 24-inch) Reynolds wrap heavy duty aluminum foil.

title: cheese, bacon and tomato pie
directions: Mix onion and flour; sprinkle in pie crust.
Top with tomato slices.
Sprinkle with bacon and cheese.
Bake uncovered at 400° for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with lettuce.

title: chewies
directions: Mix with electric mixer the cake mix, butter and 1 egg.
This will be thick!
Pat into a well-greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Set aside.
Mix the powdered sugar, cream cheese and 2 eggs.
Pour over the cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: sweet and sour shrimp
directions: Drain pineapple chunks, reserving liquid.
Add enough water to make 1 1/3 cups liquid.
In saucepan, combine juice, pineapple, green pepper, onion and bouillon cube.
Heat to boiling.
Simmer covered for 3 to 4 minutes.
Blend brown sugar, cornstarch, cold water and vinegar.
Add to pineapple mixture.
Cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Fold in shrimp.
Heat through.
Serve over chow mein noodles.
Serves 6.

title: corned beef spread
directions: Mix jello and water. Set aside. Cut up or blend other ingredients. Add to jello. Refrigerate. Serve with crackers.

title: green pea salad
directions: Toss together and flavor with whole celery seed.
Chill and serve.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream butter; gradually add powdered sugar, beating at medium speed of an electric mixer until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and flavorings, beating until blended.
Combine flour and salt; add to creamed mixture, mixing well.
Color 2/3 cup cookie dough with green food coloring.
Color remaining dough with orange food coloring.
Spoon orange dough into a pastry bag fitted with metal tip number 2110.
Pipe mixture into pumpkin shapes on ungreased cookie sheets.
Spoon green mixture into a pastry bag with metal tip Number 10.
Pipe green stems on each pumpkin.
Bake at 400° for 6 to 8 minutes.
Immediately arrange pecans pieces and chocolate morsels to make pumpkin faces.
Remove to wire racks to cool.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: best fudge i ever ate!(chocolate)
directions: Melt chips and Eagle Brand milk over low heat.
Turn off heat; add nuts and vanilla.
Pour into 8-inch square pan that has been lined with waxed paper.
Refrigerate 3 hours.
Turn out of pan and peel off paper.
Cut and eat!
Yum!

title: black moist cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in baking pan with fork; then make 3 holes in top.
Hole 1:
Put cooking oil.
Hole 2:
Put vinegar. Hole 3:
Put vanilla.
Then pour 2 cups water over top and mix in pan with fork.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: impossible pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into graham cracker crusts. Refrigerate or freeze and serve.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Line pie tin with pastry.
Add sugar and eggs which are well beaten to sweet potato.
Mix well, add molasses, milk and spices. Pour into pie crust and bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes until filling is solid. Remove from oven and allow to cool.
Serve with whipped cream if desired.

title: oatmeal chip cookies
directions: Cream
shortening; add sugars gradually.
Add eggs, one at a time,
beating after each addition.
Add hot water, then add
dry ingredients.
Add
oatmeal,
chocolate chips and mix thoroughly. Add vanilla and blend well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: reuben sandwich in a dish
directions: In an 8 x 8-inch glass dish, layer first 4 ingredients, then mix the Thousand Island and mayonnaise together and spread over top.
Sprinkle cheese over all.
Add bread cubes to top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Serve immediately.
This recipe can be doubled very easily.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Use a 9 or 10-inch baking dish.
Layer potatoes, onion and pork chops.
Repeat with remaining.
Mix mushroom soup and water; pour over pork chop layers.
Salt and pepper.
Bake, covered, 45 minutes.
Remove cover and bake 15 minutes more.

title: banana salad
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch.
Beat egg slightly.
Add sugar and cornstarch.
Stir in vinegar and water.
Cook until thickened. Break bananas in small pieces and then roll in dressing and crushed peanuts.
Yields 6 servings.
Preparation time is 20 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Boil jello, water, sugar and cornstarch 5 minutes.
Add berries before it cools.
Pour into pie shell.
Let refrigerate. Chill.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients.
Spread 1/2 mixture in 9 x 13 pan.
Mix next 3 ingredients and spread over batter in pan.
Then add other 1/2 batter over this.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Used powdered sugar glaze if desired.

title: myrtle allen's brown bread(from balley maloe house in ireland)
directions: Warm salt and whole wheat flour in oven in a large bowl, not hot.
Mix yeast, warm water and molasses together and let proof. Combine the mixture plus 1 more cup warm water (or enough to make wet sticky dough).
Place in greased bread pan.
Cover and set in warm place and allow to increase 1/3 in bulk.
Bake at 450° approximately 50 minutes.
Remove from pan.
May be left in turned off oven 20 minutes for a crustier finish.
To make a coarser texture, substitute 3/4 cup cracked wheat or wheat germ for 3/4 cup of flour.

title: nicholas' favorite disgustingly rich brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°; then smear the inside of an 8 or 9-inch square baking pan with shortening.
Melt butter over a low heat. Watch it.
It's easy to burn.

title: molasses crinkles
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, and egg together. Add rest and beat well. Shape into little balls in your hands, roll in a little sauce dish of sugar. Add cinnamon candy to center, if desired. Bake at 350°.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Boil macaroni.
Let it cool first, then add the rest of the ingredients, making sure everything is sliced up.
Just use enough Miracle Whip to mix.

title: hot fudge topping
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and cocoa, if using.
Add salt.
Slowly stir in boiling water.
Add unsweetened chocolate at this point. Cook until thick.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla. Sinfully good.

title: zucchini fritters
directions: Place zucchini and onion into processor.
Chop fine and let drain.
Add eggs, flour, salt and pepper to zucchini and onion mixture.
Pour into small patty forms in a skillet with butter or oil.
Brown.
Serve with sour cream.

title: hot sausage casserole
directions: Cut bread up in quarters and place in a greased, large loaf dish.
Cook sausage until lose and brown; drain all grease, except 2 tablespoons.
Saturate the onion in this.
Use half of everything, making 2 layers.
Place bread, cheese and onions; repeat.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Mix together all liquid ingredients; set aside.
Mix all dry ingredients; combine with liquid mixture.
Mix in nuts.
Pour in greased 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: spaghetti pie(weight watchers)
directions: In large bowl, toss together spaghetti, egg substitute, margarine, Parmesan cheese and parsley; set aside.
In large, nonstick skillet, heat oil.
Add beef and pepper and cook, stirring to break up meat, until vegetables are tender and beef is no longer pink.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except Mozzarella cheese.
Simmer 5 to 6 minutes, until sauce thickens.
Remove from heat and stir in 1 ounce of the Mozzarella cheese.

title: cabbage with polish sausage
directions: Melt butter in Dutch oven; add onion.
Saute until tender. Add flour, stirring until smooth.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly until mixture thickens.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Reduce heat, cover and cook until cabbage is done.

title: lemon or vanilla pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, margarine and eggs together. Add 1/2 of the flour and whipping cream. Add rest of flour and other ingredients. Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: pork chop casserole in crock-pot
directions: Brown chops and cut up meat.
Place in crock-pot.
Peel potatoes and slice.
Add onion, potatoes and tomatoes; cook until potatoes are tender.
White potatoes may be substituted for sweet potatoes.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Mix together crushed crackers and melted oleo; pat into a 7 x 11-inch glass dish (save some for topping).
Partially cook broccoli.
Put topping on top of cracker crumbs.
Add chunks of Velveeta cheese (at least 1 pound).
Add topping that you saved. Bake at 350°, covered with foil, for approximately 20 minutes. Uncover and bake approximately 20 minutes longer.
Ooooooh, it's so good.

title: summer succotash
directions: Heat margarine. Add celery and onion. Cook 10 minutes or until tender. Stir in garlic. Add corn, beans, parsley, vinegar, salt, pepper. Cook until heated through. Stir in tomato.

title: grilled ranch bread
directions: Slice 2 loaves of French bread lengthwise.
Combine 1/2 cup softened butter and package of Ranch style dressing mix.
Spread butter mixture on tops of bread slices.
Place bread under broiler (or cut surface down on grill) until crispy and golden brown.

title: sandwich cookie
directions: Mix baking powder with flour.
Add butter, milk, eggs, vanilla and sugar.
Mix with hand.
If dough sticks too much on hand, add a little more flour.
Cut dough into 2 parts.
Roll thin.
Cut round circles out of 1 dough and then roll the other.
Cut circles, cut a small hole in center of second circle.
Bake each circle separately.

title: creamy double decker fudge
directions: Line an 8-inch square pan with foil.
In small microwave-safe bowl, place peanut butter chips and 2/3 cup sweetened condensed milk.
Microwave at High (100) for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes, stirring after 1 minute until chips are melted and mixture is smooth when stirred.

title: chocolate "no bake" cookies
directions: Mix together the oats, coconut and nuts in a large bowl.
In a saucepan, combine the remaining ingredients; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until it reaches a boil.
Boil 1 minute. Remove from heat and add 1/2 teaspoon of vanilla.
Pour this over the cereal mixture in the bowl.
Mix with a fork until cereal mixture is well coated.
Drop from teaspoon onto waxed paper. Work rapidly for the mixture thickens quickly.
Let stand until firm.

title: no cook candy
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Form into balls or small patties (you may roll in nuts, if desired).
Wrap in foil.
May be kept in refrigerator.

title: meat balls in tomato sauce
directions: Mix hamburger, onion, bell pepper, salt, pepper, rice, onion powder and garlic powder.
Mix in flour.
Mix sauce.
Drop balls made from meat mixture in sauce.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour or until done.

title: mexican eggrolls
directions: Cut your cheese in blocks, of approximately 1 x 3 inches.
Put 2 slices of jalapenos on the cheese side by side.
Fold eggroll wrapper around it and when you get to the last corner, seal it with a small amount of water along the edge.
Drop into a heated deep fryer and cook until golden brown.
(Do not overcook as the cheese will run out into the deep fryer.)
You may top these with salsa or a topping of your choice.

title: pink cloud
directions: In a large bowl, mix milk, pineapple, cherry pie filling and pecans. Fold in whipped topping. Mix well. Pour into large mold or 3-quart oblong pan. Freeze. Remove from freezer 1 hour before serving. It also can be served after chilled in the refrigerator.

title: tostada salad
directions: In skillet, cook beef, onion and garlic until brown.
Drain well; add chili powder, salt and chilies.
Simmer uncovered for 15 minutes.
In heavy skillet, heat 1/4 inch oil.
Fry tortillas one at a time.
Drain on paper towels.
Place tortillas on plates; divide ingredients equally.
Layer in following order:
Beef mixture, tomato, lettuce and cheese.
Garnish as desired.

title: chuck's barbecue sauce
directions: Mix together and simmer 1 hour.
Let cool and store in bottles in refrigerator.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch.
Add water; bring to a boil.
Boil for 3 minutes.
Add the gelatin; cool.
Add the fresh strawberries.
Top with Cool Whip when ready to serve.
Makes 2 pies.

title: banana split cake
directions: Crust:
Mix together 2 cups graham cracker crumbs and 6 tablespoons melted oleo.
Spread in bottom of pan.

title: candy bar pie
directions: Melt candy bars.
Mix with 6 ounces of Cool Whip.
Add nuts if desired.
Spoon into pie crust and top with remaining cool Whip. Chill for best results.

title: peanut butter crunchies
directions: In a large pan, combine corn syrup and brown sugar.
Cook over medium heat, stirring frequently.
Add peanut butter; stir until combined.
Add Rice Krispies; stir until well coated.
Cool in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: In a large bowl, place first five ingredients.
In jar, place remaining ingredients.
Cover and shake.
Pour over vegetables and stir until well coated.
Cover and refrigerate at least 12 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: pig and whistle cake
directions: Beat real hard.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: butterfinger cake
directions: Take melted margarine and add yolks.
Mix in powdered sugar, then fold in Cool Whip.
In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, either pinch off or cut in squares the cool cake.
Layer cake, then Cool Whip mixture, then crushed bars.
Do this once again.
Keep in refrigerator.
It's very good!!

title: winter carrots
directions: Roll crackers into crumbs; mix with melted butter.
Place carrots in buttered dish.
Mix mayonnaise, horseradish, onion, salt and pepper; pour over carrots.
Cover with cracker crumbs. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chili con carne
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add tomato sauce, red kidney beans, white vinegar, chili powder, onion soup mix and garlic salt.
Cover and let simmer 45 minutes.
Stir occasionally.

title: three step pot roast
directions: Trim all visible fat from roast and layer with slices of onion, celery leaves/flakes and carrots.
Place peeled potatoes along edge of roasting pan and add about 12 ounces of water.
Cover and place in oven at 400° for 1/2 hour (this browns the roast), then 325° for the rest of the cooking time (approximately 2 more hours).
When finished cooking, ladle meat juices into shallow bowl and place in freezer compartment of refrigerator about 8 to 10 minutes to allow fat to rise and harden.
Remove hardened fat with a fork.
Makes a delicious flavored gravy.
Fat-free!
Enjoy!

title: southern rice cakes
directions: Heat butter in medium skillet.
Add onion, green pepper, red pepper and thyme.
Saute lightly.
Remove from heat.
Pour into mixing bowl.
Add rice and egg.
Stir in flour and cornstarch. Add cream and cayenne.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add more cream, if necessary, to make a smooth batter.
Heat clarified butter in skillet.
Add scoops of rice cake mixture.
Press down with spatula.
Cook until browned on both sides.

title: red wine garlic marinade
directions: Combine all ingredients in small bowl.
Pour over beef, poultry or shrimp in plastic bag, shallow dish or marinating dish. Seal bag or cover dish.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours, turning occasionally.
Drain, reserving marinade.
Grill as desired, basting often with marinade.
Yields 1 1/4 cups.

title: frito pie
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain off fat juice.
Drain beans.
Put meat in a saucepan.
Add beans and salsa.
Simmer for 15 minutes. Put Fritos in bottom of bowl.
Add meat mixture on top of Fritos. Sprinkle cheese on top.

title: instant spiced tea
directions: Mix together well.
Store in airtight container.
Use 2 teaspoons in a cup of hot water.

title: monkey bread
directions: Place salt, sugar and butter in a bowl; add warm milk.
Add 2 cups flour.
Let yeast dissolve in warm water; add to flour mixture and beat well.
Add eggs and remaining flour.
Stir in well.
Cover and let rise in warm place for 1 hour until double in bulk.
Melt 1 stick of butter in small saucepan.
Roll out dough on floured board and cut out with biscuit cutter.
Dip biscuits in melted butter to coat both sides.
Place in pan, overlapping layers.
Cover and let rise for 1 hour.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: traditional old fashioned vegetable soup
directions: * Amounts can vary according to preference.

title: one bowl brownies
directions: Line a 13 X 9 inch baking pan with foil extending over edges to form handles.
Grease foil.
Heat oven to 350° (325° for glass baking dish).

title: pistachio cake
directions: Mix cake mix, pudding, oil and eggs. Beat 2 minutes. Mix in coconut. Bake in 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: marshmallows and yams
directions: Drain potatoes.
Mash well in a mixing bowl and add chopped nuts.
In small saucepan, melt butter or oleo.
Add sugar, spice and honey.
Pour into mashed potatoes; mix well.
Place in ovenproof clear bowl on center rack at 325° for 20 minutes. Remove and top with marshmallows; return to oven.
Watch closely as marshmallows will brown quickly.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Beat eggs and add to butter and sugar mixture.
Sift all dry ingredients together.
Add wet ingredients to dry ingredients, slowly mixing all the while.
Add nuts.
Mash bananas together and add last.
Bake in an 8 x 13-inch loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour.
Let cool and slice.
Serve as is or with fresh bananas or berries as topping.

title: pepper relish
directions: Halve the peppers and discard stems and seeds.
Put peppers through food chopper, using coarse blade.
Also coarsely grind onions.
Combine undrained vegetables with remaining ingredients. Simmer uncovered 30 minutes.
Seal at once in hot sterilized jars.

title: brie en croute
directions: Saute the mushrooms in butter and maderia until tender and they give up their juices.
Drain.
Slice brie in half horizontally.
Place half the mushrooms between the slices of brie.
Put the brie back together and place the remaining mushrooms on top.

title: 4-bean casserole
directions: Saute ground beef and onion; add bacon and other ingredients and place in a large casserole.
Bake 1 hour at 325°, or microwave on High for 10 to 13 minutes, stirring once.

title: german pancakes
directions: Melt the oleo in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add all ingredients and mix a little.
Pour into pan.
Bake at 450° for 15 to 20 minutes. Serve with any fruit or syrup.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Peel and slice potatoes.
Place in greased baking dish.
Blend remaining ingredients in blender.
Pour over potatoes and bake at 400° for about 2 hours.
If potatoes get too dry, add a little more milk.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush cookies and mix well with melted butter.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: eleanor hess' chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken breasts until tender.
Save broth.
Put chunks of chicken in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle mushrooms and water chestnuts over the chicken.
Combine the soups and sour cream and pour over.
Sprinkle the stuffing over the top of the other layers.
Combine the broth and margarine and drizzle over.
Bake covered in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake a few minutes until brown.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put grated cheese on top.
Bake at 350° until it begins to bubble around the edges 20 to 25 minutes.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook, drain, rinse and cool spaghetti.
Toss all ingredients together.
Refrigerate.
Serve cold.

title: one hour scranton chili sauce
directions: Put all ingredients, except the tomato paste, in a pot; boil for
1/2 hour.
Add the tomato paste.
Boil for 1/2 hour, then put in jars.

title: savory trail mix
directions: Preheat oven to 275°.
In a medium bowl combine crackers, pretzels, cereals and pumpkin seeds; set aside.
In a 1-quart nonstick saucepan, melt margarine over medium heat; add Worcestershire sauce and seasonings.
Stir to combine.
Pour margarine mixture over cereal mixture and toss to combine. Transfer to a cookie sheet and bake for 30 minutes, stirring every 10 minutes to rearrange mixture.
Place cookie sheet on a wire rack and let cool.
Store in resealable plastic bags.

title: eileen's lemon bread
directions: Cream butter and 1 cup sugar.
Add eggs and beat.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Add alternately with milk to the egg mixture.
Stir in nuts and rind.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: quick meat and cheese bread
directions: *Approximately 1/2 pound of each, cut all in thin strips.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream and taco mix.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Top with onion, tomato and then Cheddar cheese.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Wash broccoli.
Cut off and use flowerets only.
Fry bacon and crumble.
Place broccoli, bacon, cheese and onion in large bowl. Mix well.
In separate bowl, mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar. Pour mayonnaise mix over salad and mix well.
It will seem dry, but it gets runny.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well and knead into a formed ball.
Roll out crust.

title: hint o' peanut pie
directions: Cut 6 tablespoons peanut butter into 2/3 cup flour to make crumbs.
Reserve a small amount.
Line bottom of pastry shell with remaining crumbs.
Mix 1 small box of instant vanilla pudding according to package directions.
Pour on top of crumbs.
Top with Cool Whip and garnish with reserved crumbs.

title: salmon ball
directions: Mix well and refrigerate.
Make into ball and roll in sliced pecans.

title: lollipops
directions: You will need 18 lollipop sticks.

title: beef stroganoff(low-fat)
directions: Trim fat from beef steak; cut beef with grain into 2-inch strips.
Cut strips diagonally across grain into 1/4-inch slices. (For ease in cutting, partially freeze beef, about 1 hour and 30 minutes.)
Heat margarine in a 10-inch nonstick skillet until melted.
Add onion and garlic; cook and stir over medium-high heat until onion is tender.
Stir in beef and mushrooms; cook and stir until beef is no longer pink.
Stir in wine; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.

title: homemade thousand island dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well. Chill and serve.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Mix the 2 cans of soup with water in a bowl to remove lumps. Sprinkle rice in bottom of 7 x 11-inch pan.
Pour soup mixture on top of rice and stir together.
Lay pieces of chicken on top. Place in 350° oven for 2 hours, during which time you lift up each piece of chicken with a fork and stir rice.
Do this 2 times.

title: cucumber and onion potato salad
directions: Cook unpeeled potatoes in boiling water to cover in large saucepan until tender.
Cool, peel and slice.
Combine with onion and cucumber in bowl.
Add oil, vinegar, salt and pepper; toss lightly to mix.
Chill until serving time.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Sprinkle top with paprika.
Chill. Serve with crackers.

title: jean's gooey bars
directions: Mix cake
mix, 1 stick margarine and beaten egg.
Press into greased
and
floured
x
13-inch
pan.	Sprinkle with chopped pecans.
Blend
powdered
sugar, cream cheese, 1 stick margarine and 2 whole eggs.
Pour over nuts.	Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: snickers cake
directions: Prepare cake mix using package directions.
Pour 1/2 the batter into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Melt caramels, milk and butter.
Pour over cake.
Sprinkle with 1 cup nuts and chocolate chips.
Pour remaining batter over filling. Sprinkle 1 cup peanuts over top.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: scalloped cabbage
directions: Cook cabbage in boiling water (salted) for 10 minutes; drain well.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Add flour; blend until smooth. Add milk; cook until smooth white sauce develops.
Place alternate layers of cabbage, white sauce and cheese in baking dish.
Top with cracker mixture.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add applesauce alternately with dry ingredients and bake in a 10 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: In a bowl, combine egg, bread crumbs, milk, parsley, mustard, salt and pepper.
Add beef; mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls. Place in baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes or until done.
Drain.

title: sausage quiche
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into pie shell. Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: rhubarb upside-down cake
directions: Grease 8 x 12-inch cake pan.
Put rhubarb and marshmallows in the bottom.
Sprinkle 3/4 cup sugar over this.
Set aside.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Line a baked pie shell with half of the berries; leave whole. Mix the other half of berries with cornstarch and crush.
Add lemon juice, salt, sugar and water.
Cook mixture about 5 minutes or until thick; stir and cool.
Pour over berries in pie shell. (Cream cheese may be added to baked shell before adding whole berries.)
Refrigerate pie before serving.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown the ground beef; drain.
Stir in ketchup, milk, cream of mushroom soup and cream cheese.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat; simmer, stirring occasionally, for approximately 15 to 20 minutes.

title: black cherry congealed salad
directions: Mash cream cheese; dissolve jello in hot juice from can of crushed
pineapple
and
juice from the can of cherries and heat. Let
cool and add all other ingredients consisting of 1 large Coca-Cola,
pecans,
cherries and cream cheese.
Put in refrigerator to congeal.
Cut into squares to serve.

title: potato soup
directions: Saute onion in butter in a saucepan.
Add potatoes and water. Cook covered until potatoes are tender.
Add soup, milk, salt, parsley and cream cheese.
Heat thoroughly.
Top with sharp Cheddar cheese, if desired.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Combine corn meal, salt and soda; blend.
Stir in shortening; add sour cream, corn and eggs and mix well.
Add green chilies and cheese and stir.
Pour in greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Combine onion with Veg-All, cheese and mayonnaise.
Place in a greased casserole dish and top with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: rolled beef tacos
directions: Combine all ingredients into crock-pot.
Cook all day or night on low.
Shred beef apart with forks.
Heat corn or flour tortillas in microwave or in dry skillet.
Spoon meat mixture into shell and roll.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Boil sugar, milk, water and cinnamon to soft ball stage, about 3 minutes.
Put in pecans and vanilla.
Pour on waxed paper and separate the nuts.

title: holy cow cake
directions: Mix cake as directed on box.
While hot, poke holes in it. Pour over cake the Eagle Brand milk.
Cool.
Pour caramel topping over cake.
Add Cool Whip.
Sprinkle on candy bar.

title: danish open-faced cucumber sandwiches
directions: Mix softened cream cheese, mayo, garlic powder and dry Italian dressing.
Slice cucumbers with peeling on.
Drain on paper towels.
When ready to serve, spread filling on rye bread.
Top with cucumber slice and sprinkle with dill weed.

title: charcoaled marinated chicken breasts
directions: Put chicken breasts in skillet bowl. Mix garlic, salt, sugar, mustard, vinegar, lime and lemon juices. Blend well. Whisk in the oil (apple juice) and add pepper. Pour over chicken and refrigerate overnight.

title: midnight chocolate cake
directions: Sift together in mixing bowl the flour, salt, cocoa, soda and baking powder.
Add the Crisco, sugar, vanilla and hot water.
Mix together on low speed.
Then continue beating for 2 minutes.
Add the eggs and beat 1 minute more.
Pour into well-greased 8 1/2 x 11-inch cake pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Watch carefully and don't overbake.

title: russian curry soup
directions: Combine the soups and milk; heat to just below boiling point. Add the curry and mix well.
Just before serving, add cream and sherry.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream margarine and sugar well; add eggs and beat again.
Add alternately sifted dry ingredients with pumpkin and water.
When blended, beat again until smooth.
Add about 1 cup chopped pecans, if desired.
Bake in three loaf pans, greased.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Combine yeast and warm water.
Let stand 5 minutes. Add buttermilk to yeast mixture and set aside. Combine all remaining ingredients except shortening in a large bowl.
Cut in shortening with a pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Add buttermilk mixture, stirring with a spoon until dry ingredients are moistened.
Turn biscuit dough out onto a lightly floured surface and knead lightly 4 or 5 times.
Roll dough to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with a 2 1/2-inch biscuit cutter.
Place on lightly greased baking sheets.
Cover and let rise in a warm place (85°), free from drafts, for 1 hour.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes or
until browned.
Yields 2 dozen.

title: chicken 'n dumplings
directions: Prepare Creamettes dumplings according to package directions. Drain and chill in cold water for 5 minutes.
Boil chicken in water until tender, about 1 1/2 hours.
Reserve 2 cups chicken broth. Remove chicken from bones in large pieces.
Saute onion and green pepper in butter until tender.
Combine chicken, reserved broth, onion, green pepper, soup, salt and pepper.
Drain dumplings and add to chicken mixture.
Pour into two 2-quart casseroles.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Garnish with paprika.
Serves 12.

title: crawfish casserole
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in butter. In separate container, mix tomatoes, soups, rice and water. Add crawfish tails and sauteed vegetables. Place in casserole dish. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, stirring about every 45 minutes. Uncover last 15 minutes.

title: potato puffs
directions: Blend well.
Drop by small spoonfuls on greased cookie sheet. Add if desired, bacon bits, chopped onions or grated cheese.
Bake at 385° for 3 to 5 minutes.

title: quick and easy rolls
directions: About 1 1/2 hours before dinner:
Into scalded milk in large bowl, stir sugar, salt and shortening.
Cool until lukewarm.

title: wonder salad
directions: Melt jello and cream cheese in milk.
Add crushed pineapple. Fold in whipped cream or Cool Whip.
Add nuts, if desired.
Chill until firm in square pan or dish.

title: chewy chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Stir together cocoa and butter until mixture is smooth.
Stir in condensed milk, eggs, vanilla, oats, biscuit mix, salt and both chips until well blended.
Let batter rest 10 minutes.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 9 minutes or until tops begin to dry (do not overbake).
Cool 5 minutes; remove to wire rack.
Cool completely. Store in airtight container.
Makes 48 cookies.

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter and then add eggs, vanilla and melted chips.
Sift in flour, salt, baking powder and soda.
Add milk. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: basic whole wheat bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in 2 cups water.
Mix in salt, 1 tablespoon honey and 4 cups whole wheat flour until smooth.
Keep warm until light and bubbly, about 45 minutes.
Add 1/2 cup hot water, oil, 1 tablespoon honey and remaining flour.
Knead for 10 minutes.
Keep covered in a warm place until double in size, about 1 hour.
Punch down and form 2 loaves.
Let raise in nonstick loaf pans until double in size.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool and slice. Makes 2 loaves.

title: seven layer salad
directions: This is all layered in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan and placed in the refrigerator for 8 hours before serving.

title: sherbet
directions: Put in blender or mixer and beat until foamy. Chill or freeze.

title: tar tots casserole
directions: Put all ingredients in pan.
Mix. Put Tar Tots layer on top. Add salt and pepper.
Cook until Tar Tots are brown.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: thanksgiving dinner meatballs
directions: Mix ingredients together and let set awhile, even overnight is okay.
Shape into approximately 16 balls.
Place meatballs in serving dish and cover with sauce.
Bake, covered, for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix 2 eggs, cake mix and margarine; put in 13 x 9-inch pan. Beat 2 eggs, powdered sugar and cream cheese; mix.
Pour on top of cake mixture.
Bake at 350° until light brown, 30 to 40 minutes. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Mix soups and chicken stock. Tear tortillas into small pieces and line a large baking dish with half of them.
Layer soup mixture, chicken pieces, cheese, remaining tortilla pieces and onion.
Top last layer with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Make ahead for better flavor.
Makes 8 to 10 servings and freezes well.

title: pumpkin log
directions: Grease a 10 x 15-inch cookie sheet.
Line with wax paper and grease again.
Mix batter in order given.
Beat eggs and sugar. Add pumpkin. Sift together flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt. Beat into first mixture. Spread batter in pan. Sprinkle with nuts. Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Turn out on towel that has been sprinkled with powdered sugar.
Roll up in towel (jelly roll) and wax paper.
Cool.

title: punch
directions: Mix together sugar and water.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Pour over Jell-O and stir until Jell-O is dissolved.
Add pineapple juice and water.
Mix. Place in deep freeze and freeze.
Set out to partly thaw before ready to serve.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: no fat italian dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill for 1 to 2 hours to allow herbs to blend.
Remove garlic before serving.
Makes 12 tablespoons (0 fat grams per 2 tablespoons).

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Place potatoes, sugar, salt and pepper in alternate layers in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Cover potatoes with milk. Add extra milk, if needed.
Sprinkle pork chops with salt and pepper.
Arrange on top of potatoes.
Cover and bake at 400° for 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake until pork chops are brown.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to box directions.
Bake in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool in pan for 15 minutes.
Pinch holes in cake while warm with wooden pick.
Pour cream of coconut over cake.
Let cake cool completely in pan or on wire rack.
Spread whipped topping over cake.
Sprinkle with coconut, if desired.
Cover and chill for at least 4 hours.
Keep refrigerated.
Yield:
15 servings.

title: glorified chicken sandwich
directions: Combine; spoon into hot dog buns and wrap each bun in foil. Put in 250° oven for 20 minutes or at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: whoopee pies
directions: Mix 1/3 cup of shortening, 1 cup of sugar, egg, milk and 1 1/2 teaspoons of vanilla.
Add flour, salt, soda and cocoa.
Mix until very smooth.
Drop by teaspoons on ungreased baking sheet 4 inches apart.
Bake for 10 minutes at 375°.

title: round steak with mushrooms
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Place round steak on aluminum foil in a 9 x 11-inch pan.
Top with dehydrated onion soup mix.
Add mushrooms, drained, over meat.
Cover tightly with foil paper. Cook for 1 hour.

title: party potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes.
Blend all ingredients together.
Keeps in refrigerator up to 3 weeks.
Keeps in freezer for up to 3 months. Add butter while heating up.

title: canned fruit for pie filling or crisp
directions: Bring ingredients to a boil until clear.
Fill jars 3/4 full with fruit.
Pour filling on top.
Process in hot water bath for 35 minutes.
For apples, cherries, peaches and rhubarb.

title: eggplant stir-fry
directions: Peel and cut up eggplant.
Fry in olive oil.
Add cut up tomatoes and bell pepper.
Add tomato sauce and water with garlic salt to taste.
Works best in wok.
Cover and simmer 20 to 25 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and water.
Cook until hard ball stage. Remove from heat.
Add vanilla, soda and butter that has been mixed together.
Quickly add nuts.
Pour out on warm buttered cookie sheet.

title: pepper jack potatoes
directions: In a large bowl, combine the potatoes and onions.
Combine the butter and seasoning; drizzle over the potatoes and onions. Toss to coat.
Place half in a greased 13 x 9 x 2 inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with half the cheeses; top with remaining potatoes and onions.

title: shrimp or chicken with asparagus casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter until transparent.
Add asparagus; saute about 5 minutes.
Add shrimp, chicken or scallops and cook until not transparent.
Do not overcook.
In bowl, mix Hollandaise sauce mix, egg yolks, milk, whipping cream and spices.
Pour mixture over shrimp and bring to a boil.
Put rice in a 9 x 13 pan (glass). Pour shrimp mixture on top.
Sprinkle heavily with Parmesan, then plain bread crumbs.
Put remaining 2 ounces butter on top.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: half sour cucumber pickles
directions: Wash quart jars carefully.
Bring to a boil 2 quarts water. Add salt, 2 bay leaves and vinegar at boiling point of water.
Let solution set.
Wash cucumbers.
Put sprig of dill in bottom of jar. Place cukes into jars.
Pour cooled solution over cukes.
Add more dill, 10 peppercorns, 2 bay leaves, 2 garlic cloves and pinch of alum on top.
Screw tops on jars.
Place in a cool spot for 2 or 3 days.
Then place in refrigerator about 5 days.
Enjoy.

title: beef and rice casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion in butter or margarine.
Mix together the meat, soups, water and seasonings.
Pour into a 9 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Crumble potato chips on top; bake another 15 minutes.
(Buttered bread crumbs can be substituted for potato chips.)

title: baked hash brown potatoes
directions: Mix soup and milk.
Combine potatoes, cheese and onions; stir in soup mixture.
Pour into baking pan.
Top with corn flakes and drizzle butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: low calorie pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into pie crust. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Reduce oven to 315° and bake for 1 hour. Top with pecan halves.

title: apple crisp(from 1975 edition)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Sift first 3 ingredients into a bowl; add egg.
Mix lightly with a fork until mixture is crumbly. Wash, peel and slice apples.
Arrange in a greased 8-inch square pan.
Top with crumbs.
Pour margarine over all.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake for 40 minutes.

title: cocktail weenies
directions: Combine jelly and mustard in saucepan and cook over medium heat until jelly melts.
Stir to mix well.
Heat hot dogs and place in chafing dish.
Pour sauce over hot dogs and serve.

title: impossible taco pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease pie plate (10 x 1 1/2-inch).
Cook and stir beef and onions until brown, drain.
Stir in seasoning mix.
Spread in plate; top with chilies.
Beat milk, baking mix and eggs until smooth, 15 seconds in blender on high.
Pour into plate.
Bake 25 minutes.
Top with tomatoes and cheese.
Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean, 8 to 10 minutes longer.
Cool 5 minutes.
Serve with sour cream, chopped tomatoes, shredded lettuce and shredded cheese.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash, onion, carrot and salt until tender.
Drain well and mix sour cream and chicken soup.
Pour into casserole dish. Top with dressing mix which has been stirred up with 1 stick melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for about 1/2 hour.

title: spicy macaroni
directions: Cook macaroni as directed.
Place in crock-pot.
Add Ro-Tel and wieners.
Cook at medium for about 30 to 45 minutes.
Add milk, if it starts to dry out.

title: caramel apples
directions: Put caramels and water in top of double broiler.
Place over low heat until melted about 15 minutes, stirring occasionally. Insert sticks into clean apples.
Dip into melted caramels, twirl until apples are coated.
Set on butter coated wax paper and place in refrigerator until cool.

title: garlic-roasted potatoes and greens(serves 4 to 6)
directions: Coat a shallow baking pan with cooking spray.
Place potatoes and garlic in pan.
Stir to mix, then coat with cooking spray. Bake in a 450° oven until well browned, about 1 hour, turning with a wide spatula every 15 minutes.
Drizzle vinegar and oil over potatoes.
Turn potato mixture gently with spatula to loosen any browned bits.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Transfer to a wide bowl.
Coarsely chop about half the watercress.
Mix lightly with potatoes.
Tuck remaining watercress around potatoes. Serve hot or at room temperature.

title: chocolate-chocolate cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Add chocolate and blend.
Add sifted flour, soda and salt alternately with buttermilk.
Stir in vanilla and water.
Bake in three (9-inch) pans at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken and fruit salad for two
directions: Lightly toss together chicken, 1 cup cut-up fruit, celery, green onions and almonds.
Arrange spinach leaves on salad plates and top with chicken mixture.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix all ingredients together well. Pour into a 1 3/4-quart casserole dish that has been sprayed with Pam and buttered. Dot with butter and sprinkle on remaining cracker crumbs. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: cheese balls
directions: Roll mixture in small balls the size of a walnut.
Flatten on greased cookie sheet with fork.
Bake for 15 minutes in 350° oven.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter in bowl.
Add sugar and egg yolks.
Add dry ingredients alternately with mashed bananas.
Add nuts and beaten egg whites.
Pour into greased, waxed paper-lined loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until bread tests done.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Fry bacon until crisp. Cool and crumble.
Mix with vegetables. Toss with dressing.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook chopped broccoli and drain.
Mix soup, mayonnaise and onion.
Beat in eggs.
Fold in broccoli and margarine in small pieces.
Put mixture in baking dish.
Top with cheese.
Crumble crackers on top and press down with hands.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let stand for 20 minutes before serving.

title: crock-pot dip
directions: Layer in crock-pot as listed.
Heat until warmed through, about 1/2 to 1 hour.

title: hamburger stew
directions: Slice carrots, potatoes and onion thin.
Shave corn from the cob.
Should have 2 cups.
Brown meat; drain off fat.
Add onion, pepper and mushrooms.
Boil potatoes, corn and carrots.
Add tomatoes, corn and mushrooms.
Add meat mixture and stew mix to vegetable mixture.
Add V-8 juice.
Simmer for 1 hour.

title: ham glaze
directions: Add apple cider to make thin paste; cover ham and brown.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Rinse chicken and pat dry.
Arrange in baking dish.
Combine mustard, molasses, vinegar, soy sauce, pineapple and brown sugar in dish.
Mix well.
Spoon over chicken.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until chicken is tender, basting frequently.

title: cheese and spinach puffs
directions: Cook spinach and drain.
Beat eggs, cheeses, dressing, butter, garlic and corn muffin mix.
Add spinach and stir.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until lightly browned. Appetizer can be made and frozen before baking for later use.

title: taco pie
directions: Brown ground beef with onion.
Drain, then add taco seasoning mix according to directions.
Combine refried beans with taco sauce.
Layer 1/2 bean mixture, then 1/2 meat mixture, grated cheese, 1 cup crushed corn chips, 1/2 beans, 1/2 meat and top with more Cheddar cheese (in pie shell).
Bake 20 to 30 minutes; let sit 10 minutes.
May serve with sour cream, lettuce and tomato. Oven temperature: 350°.

title: wiener wraps
directions: Cut each wiener into 4 pieces.
Cut each piece of bacon into 3 pieces.
Wrap bacon around each wiener.
Place on a cookie sheet. Sprinkle with brown sugar and dry mustard.
Cover with foil; leave in refrigerator overnight.
Then cook for 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Then remove foil and broil for 2 minutes.
Stick toothpicks in each wiener and serve.

title: strawberry dessert(given to clo fletcher by clara hollingsworth)
directions: Mix strawberry gel with fresh strawberries.
Mix pudding mix with milk and Eagle Brand milk.
Layer in trifle dish starting with cake, then strawberries, then pudding.
Top with Cool Whip and garnish with fresh strawberries.

title: almond apricot coffee cake
directions: Beat butter at medium speed with an electric mixer about 2 minutes or until creamy.
Gradually add sugar, beating for 5 to 7 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating until yellow disappears. Stir in the almond extract.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt. Add to butter mixture alternately with sour cream, beginning and ending with flour mix.
Mix at low speed just until blended after each addition.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown onions and sausage. Add all other ingredients, except cheese.
Put into casserole dish and sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: wheat cupcakes
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Line cupcake tins with paper cupcake liners. In large bowl, mix margarine, sugar and eggs; beat well. Add the milk and vanilla; blend. Stir in flour, oats, soda and salt; mix well. Add optional items if desired. Spoon batter into cupcake liners. Bake for 20 minutes, then test center to see if done. Remove and let cool slightly. Remove from tins; let cool completely or enjoy while still warm.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Break cake into bite size pieces.
Mix pudding according to directions.
Prepare gelatin with boiling water and add the frozen strawberries, stirring until berries are thawed.
Layer cake in punch bowl, then layer pudding, strawberry mixture and whipped topping, repeating layers until all is used.
End with whipped topping.
Top with chopped nuts.

title: perigourdine sauce
directions: Saute shallots in melted butter.
Add a bay leaf and 2 cups of the Madeira.
Simmer and add consomme.
Add truffles to 1/2 cup Madeira and pour into hot sauce.

title: tortilla pinwheels
directions: Mix all the filling ingredients together thoroughly.
Divide the filling and spread evenly over tortillas; roll up tortillas. Cover tightly with plastic wrap, twisting ends.
Refrigerate for several hours.
Unwrap; cut in slices 1/2 to 3/4 inch thick. Place a small bowl of salsa in the middle of a serving plate. Arrange pinwheels around salsa.
Garnish with parsley, if desired.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix the mayonnaise, wine vinegar and sugar together and set aside.
Rinse the bunch of broccoli spears and then cut into bite size, using the tops only.
Add the chopped red onion and raisins. Mix and toss with dressing mixture and serve cold.
Add the nuts right before serving.

title: texas pecan pie
directions: Arrange pecan halves in the bottom of unbaked pastry shell. Because pecan pie is a heavy pie, make a thicker pie shell than usual.
If frozen pie crust is used, use both layers.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix ingredients; place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
During last 4 minutes, top with crushed potato chips and 1 cup shredded cheese.

title: peanut butter logs
directions: Beat together peanut butter and margarine, stir in sugar (mix well).
Stir in Rice Krispies.
Measure batter in tablespoon amounts.
Shape into log.
Roll in nuts and set aside.
Melt chocolate chips and shortening in saucepan, drizzle over logs. Chill!!!!
Makes 25 to 30 logs.

title: taylor's favorite peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream peanut butter, sugars and shortening.
Add egg; mix well.
Add flour and soda.
Dough will be very stiff.
Make into balls and press down with fork.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: bill's goulash
directions: Scramble fry hamburger.
Add chopped onion.
Drain grease. Add rest of the ingredients and cook slowly to heat through.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Continue boiling 5 minutes over medium heat until candy thermometer reaches 234°, stirring constantly to prevent scorching.
Remove from heat, stir in chocolate chips until melted.
Add marshmallow creme, nuts and vanilla.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: potatoes au gratin
directions: Peel, cube (bite size) and parboil the potatoes. Grease baking dish or bowl. In microwave, heat milk, margarine, flour and cheese until melted and hot.
Stir occasionally.
Put hot sauce in blender and blend until smooth.
Pour hot sauce over hot potatoes. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or
until bubbly and with good color.

title: lemon butter sauce
directions: In small saucepan, melt butter or margarine.
Stir in lemon juice and salt if desired.
Serve with fish, seafood or vegetables.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: elegant lobster or shrimp casserole
directions: In lightly salted water, cook lobster or shrimp.
Cook 5 minutes.
Dice lobster meat and set aside.
Melt butter in top of double boiler.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Blend in enough hot milk to make 3 cups of gravy.
Slowly stir butter and flour mixture until smooth and well-thickened.
Add mushrooms.
Blend well and pour into shallow casserole.
Cook 5-inches below broiler until sauce is bubbly.
Serve over rice.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: tex-mex fiesta bake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Prepare stuffing according to package directions, using water and margarine.
Spoon into bottom of greased 11 x 7-inch baking dish.

title: kenya chicken stew
directions: Brown chicken pieces in oil.
Remove chicken; set aside.
To drippings in pan, add onions; saute until brown.
Add broth, carrots, tomatoes, paste, lime juice, hot sauce, nutmeg, cloves and cinnamon.
Return chicken to pan.
Simmer covered 15 minutes. Add green peppers; cook 10 minutes.
In small bowl, mix together peanut butter, cornstarch and 1/4 cup of liquid from pan.
Stir into chicken mixture; simmer 5 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: ben's fried rice
directions: Mix cooked rice, vegetables and margarine together in frypan. Add salt and pepper to taste.
Fry on medium heat until rice is brown and dry.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine all dry ingredients and zucchini in bowl and mix.
In separate bowl, mix eggs, oil and vanilla.
Pour over flour mixture and stir.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour and 30 minutes or until pick inserted comes out clean.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Pour dressing over mixture.

title: sock it 2 me cake
directions: Grease and flour a tube pan.
Pour half of mixture in pan, then mix 2 teaspoons brown sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon. Sprinkle over batter in pan.
Pour remainder in pan and bake at 325° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: individual corned beef-onion rolls
directions: Stir together all ingredients except rolls.
Spread mixture on rolls.
Makes 4 or 5 sandwiches.

title: cheese ball
directions: Use half the dried beef in the ball and half on top of ball. Have cheese at room temperature.
Mix all ingredients.
Form into ball and top with half of beef pieces.

title: onion and pepper casserole
directions: Cut onions in 1/2-inch slices.
Saute in pan with garlic and olive oil.
Slice peppers.
Put in baking dish; add a dash of Tabasco and next 2 ingredients.
Toss.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: scalloped chicken
directions: Saute celery and onion in butter.
Mix chicken broth, milk and flour.
Toast bread and break into pieces into chicken broth.
Add celery, onion and chicken mix.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add beaten eggs and mix well.
Put into greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Let the hash browns thaw and spread in a 13 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Salt and pepper lightly.
In a bowl, mix the butter, cheese, soup, sour cream and onion.
Pour over potatoes. Mix the corn flakes and the butter; spread on top of casserole. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: gretl's lemon chiffon
directions: Combine the boiling water and box of Jell-O and stir until dissolved.
Cool until just beginning to set.
Beat the evaporated milk until peaks form.
Add Jell-O mixture and all other ingredients and beat until all mixed.
Refrigerate for at least 3 hours.

title: veggie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Cover bottom of large cookie sheet with crescent rolls, patting to fit. Prick with fork. Bake 10 to 12 minutes. Cool.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine the pudding mix with milk in a saucepan. Add the peanut butter. Cook and stir over medium heat until the mix comes to a full boil. Cool the cooked pudding 5 minutes, stirring twice. Pour into a pie shell.
Chill 3 hours.

title: cookie bars(north pole sleigh-ride type)
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass dish).
In large bowl, combine flour, sugar and cocoa; cut in margarine until crumbly. Press firmly on bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 15 minutes. Meanwhile, in medium bowl, beat sweetened condensed milk, egg and vanilla extract until well blended.
Stir in pecans.

title: easy chocolate ice cream
directions: Squirt Dream Whip into bottom of ice cream freezer. Pour Eagle Brand milk over this. Pour Dutch chocolate milk over this. Do not stir. Freeze.

title: batter-fried chicken
directions: In a covered saucepan, simmer chicken in salted water to cover for 20 minutes; drain.
In a bowl, combine pancake mix and salt; stir in water.
Beat 2 minutes.
Dip chicken in batter; let excess batter drain off into bowl.
In a heavy skillet that's at least 3 inches deep, heat 1 1/4 inches of oil to 350°.
Regulate heat so chicken fries, about 325°.
Fry a few pieces at a time for about 5 minutes or until golden and chicken is tender.
Drain well.
Makes 4 servings.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: In bottom of soup pot, saute beef, onion and garlic in olive oil until beef is brown (approximately 5 minutes).
Add water and all remaining ingredients except macaroni.
Add more water to completely cover vegetables.
Bring to a boil.
Add macaroni. Cook until macaroni is tender.
Turn heat down to low and cover. Cook for at least 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: homemade chocolate cake
directions: Beat butter, sugar and eggs together.
Add vanilla.
Mix flour and cocoa together.
Add milk to flour mixture.
Add to butter mixture until smooth.
Pour batter into 2 floured 9-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: sherried onion casserole(serves 8)
directions: Cook onions in butter until soft but not browned (10 to 15 minutes over moderate heat).
Blend in flour, salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Stir in broth, then sherry.
Place mixture in a baking dish.
Toss bread cubes, Swiss cheese and Parmesan cheese and put on top of onion mixture, pressing some of the bread cubes into the mixture.

title: georgia special
directions: Mix together in order as listed.
Bake in 2 prepared round 9-inch cake pans at 325° for 25 minutes or until done.

title: barbecued chicken and stuffing
directions: Cook chicken and onion on both sides in hot oil in large skillet.
Add water, barbecue sauce and margarine; bring to a boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer 5 minutes or until chicken is thoroughly cooked.
Stir in stuffing mix and corn; let stand 5 minutes.

title: chocolate oil cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients together first.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Do
not beat.
Stir well.
Bake at 350° approximately 30 minutes.

title: taco casserole
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients; set aside.
Spray deep casserole dish with release agent.
Cover bottom with 1/2 the tortillas.
Continue to layer 1/2 the chicken, 1/2 the mixture and 1/2 the cheese; repeat layers beginning with tortillas.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 325°.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.

title: squash-sausage casserole
directions: Slice unpeeled squash and cook in small amount of salted water for 15 minutes or until done.
Drain and mash.
Add sausage and remaining ingredients.
Bake in greased casserole dish at 400° to 450° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: the best ever fruit cake
directions: Preheat oven to 200°.
This fruit cake is baked in a very slow oven.
Sift flour with the baking powder and baking soda.
Add cinnamon, allspice and nutmeg.
Set flour mixture aside.
Cream butter and eggs together until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla to egg mixture.
Gradually add the flour mixture to the egg mixture. Add, one at a time, the orange juice, lemon juice and the Welch's grape juice.
Stir mixture until all ingredients are well blended. Add grape jelly.
Blend well.
Place candied cherries, candied pineapple, lemon peel, orange peel, pecans and raisins in a large bowl and mix well.
Fold this mixture into the batter.
Mix thoroughly.

title: pot of beans
directions: Brown sausage and ground beef; drain.
Mix with all other ingredients.
Simmer several hours or bake in oven for 1 hour at 350°.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix crackers and water together; put in meat.
Beat eggs with fork.
Put in the rest of the ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: baked ham
directions: Place ham in browning bag.
Combine pineapple juice, brown sugar and honey.
Use needle to inject juice in ham.
Marinate at least 12 hours.
Place pineapple slice with cherry in center with toothpick.

title: banana split pie
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, sugar and 1 stick of butter.
Press in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Combine 2 eggs, powdered sugar and 2 sticks of butter.
Mix on high for about 4 minutes.
Pour over graham cracker crust.
Slice bananas; lay on pudding mix.
Pour drained pineapple over bananas.
Cover with whipped topping, cherries and nuts if desired.

title: alfredo sauce
directions: Heat margarine and half and half in 1-quart saucepan over low heat until margarine is melted.
Stir in remaining ingredients; keep warm over low heat.
Pour sauce over noodles, stirring to coat noodles.

title: coke cake
directions: Mix sugar and flour together.
Heat margarine, Coke, cocoa and marshmallows to boiling point.
Pour slowly over sugar and flour. Mix together.

title: chocolate fudge pie
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Add beaten eggs and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients, mixing well.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake in a 325° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut into squares when cooled.

title: illinois delicious apple cake
directions: Use large mixing bowl.
Beat eggs; add sugar gradually, then oil.
Add 3 cups of Delicious apples and cup of chopped pecans. Sift together 3 cups of flour, 1 teaspoon of salt, 1 teaspoon of soda and 2 teaspoons of vanilla.
Mix well but be careful not to overbeat or apples will turn into sauce.
Grease and lightly a 9 x 13-inch pan or two 9-inch pans.
Start with cold oven. Bake at 325° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: paw foots
directions: Cook ground beef seasoned with salt and pepper.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Add water to make dough.
Roll out on floured board; cut into circular shapes with knife.
Put cooked meat on half the dough.
Fold over and pinch the edges firmly. Fry in deep fat until brown.
Put in lined pan and cover until ready to serve.
Serve hot.

title: bishop's bread(red and green cherries make this a good dessert for christmas)
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir in nuts, fruit and chocolate.
Beat eggs and sugar together in separate bowl.
Add to first mixture and stir until blended.
Mixture will be very thick. Line a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan with brown paper.
Grease paper with margarine very thoroughly.
Pour in mixture.
Bake in preheated oven at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until top is browned.
Put on rack to cool, carefully removing paper.
Stores well.

title: lentil, garbanzo bean and tomato salad(low-fat)
directions: Cook lentils, carrots and bay leaf in water for 30 minutes. Drain and transfer to large bowl to cool.
Mix all remaining ingredients into lentils.
Season to taste.
Can be prepared up to four hours ahead.
Tastes better with some time to meld the flavors.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Bring sugar, syrup and water to boil.
Stir in peanuts slowly, so as not to boil.
Then keep at rolling boil until nuts begin to pop and brown.
Remove from heat; add soda.
Stir well.
Add salt. Pour onto large well greased platter or sheet, allowing room for candy to spread.
When cooled, break in pieces.

title: crispy fried chicken
directions: Mix flour
and
seasonings
in pie plate.
Mix eggs and 1/4 cup
water
in
another
plate
or
bowl.
Place crumbs in another plate or bowl.
Roll chicken pieces in flour, then egg mixture, then
crumbs.
Place on paper towels to set up, about 15 minutes. Put shortening in pan on medium heat until melted and hot.
Place chicken
in
grease,
cover and cook about 10 minutes until brown and fry until done.

title: homemade tortilla chips
directions: Preheat oven to 400.
Cut each tortilla into 8 wedges with a pizza cutter.
Arrange the wedges in batches in a single layer on an 11x17 inch baking sheet.
Bake for 6 to 8 minutes or until light brown.
Remove the chips to a wire rack to cool.
Makes 64 chips.

title: humus
directions: Saut onion and garlic in oil in a skillet until browned. Combine onion/garlic mixture with remaining ingredients in a food processor. Blend until smooth. Let stand 30 minutes before serving. Serve with toasted pita bread slices and vegetables.

title: sausage and rice casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Add vegetables and simmer until tender.
Add rice.
Add soups and seasonings.
Pour in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Stir occasionally.

title: cholesterol free pie crust
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
