Roll between sheets of wax paper that have been sprinkled with flour.
This will make enough for 1 double crust pie in 9-inch pie pan.

title: fancy dipped oreos
directions: Melt almond bark following package instructions.
Drop in Oreos and turn to coat.
Lift out and let excess drip off.
Place on wax paper.
Cool for 30 minutes, then add decoration as desired.
I use the star tip with red icing to make a mock poinsettia and then add green icing leaf tip with a silver candy bead for shine.
The possibilities are only limited to your imagination.
Stores great in sealed tub and also mails easily.

title: spicy blueberry pie
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients, toss gently. Spoon blueberry mixture into pie shell. Cut remaining pie shell into strips. Make a lattice design over filling. Brush pie with milk and sprinkle with 1 tsp. sugar. Bake at 400° for 40 to 45 minutes. Shield edges with aluminum foil during last 20 minutes of baking.

title: new year's eve braunschweiger spread
directions: In large mixing bowl, using electric mixer, cream braunschweiger (chopped in chunks first), cream cheese and mayonnaise.
When well mixed, add onion, garlic powder, dash of salt and parsley.
If desired, may add 2 tablespoons lemon juice. Serve on assorted crackers.

title: amish bread
directions: Pour boiling water over sugar (2 tablespoons), salt and butter mixture in bowl and mix.
Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water mixed with 1 tablespoon sugar.
Add yeast mixture to sugar, butter, salt and water mixture.
Add 2 1/2 cups of flour and mix until smooth. Add rest of flour to make a stiff dough.
Knead for 8 to 10 minutes or until elastic.
Place in greased bowl and grease top. Cover, set in warm place and let rise 25 minutes.
Punch down and divide into 3 sections.
Roll jelly roll fashion and place in greased loaf pans.
Slash top of dough every 1/2-inch with knife. Brush top with mixture of egg yolk and milk.
Let rise in a warm place until doubled.
Preheat oven to 400° and bake bread for 10 minutes.
Then reduce heat to 350° and bake for 20 to 30 minutes, until golden brown.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix everything together, except corn flakes and butter. Place in a casserole dish. Crush corn flakes on top, enough to completely cover top. Melt butter and pour all on top of corn flakes. Cook for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread out crescent
rolls on an ungreased cookie sheet (with sides) and pinch rolls together to make them meet.	Bake 10 minutes at	400° until golden brown.
Cool completely.
Mix cream cheese, mayo and spices until creamy. Spread over crust.

title: chicken in-a-bag
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Move top oven rack to keep from burning bag.
Sprinkle chicken on both sides with the other ingredients. Place large paper bag on a broiler pan.
Place chicken in bag. Close end of bag by rolling it under.
Bake for one hour.

title: grape-cantaloupe salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except salad dressing.
Add salad dressing.
Toss until coated.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Mix the sugar, soy sauce, vinegar, water and cornstarch. Cook over low heat until thickened, stirring constantly. Place in a kettle the pork. Add the cold water and boil 20 minutes or until tender. Pour off water if there is any left; cool. While meat is cooling, saute the onion and carrots in oil (substitute green pepper, pineapple, bamboo shoots and apples). Remove from pan. Combine ingredients with hot sweet and sour sauce and sauteed vegetables. Serve with steamed rice.

title: goulash
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package.
While noodles cook, cook and stir beef and onion in large skillet until meat is brown and onion is tender.
Drain off fat.
Stir in drained noodles, celery, catsup, mushrooms (with liquid), tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer 30 to 45 minutes.
Very good for really cold snowy nights.

title: frosty pineapple pie
directions: Bring
to a boil crushed pineapple. Dissolve gelatin in it and add
sugar.
Cool until almost stiff.
Whip evaporated milk and lemon
juice
until it stands in peaks (very stiff). Pour on
top of
gelatin mixture.
Beat in slowly with rotary beater.
Pour into
baked
or 10-inch pie shell.
Chill at least
hour. When
serving,
garnish
with drained crushed pineapple, if desired.

title: raisin spice cake
directions: Cook raisins, cinnamon, salt, cocoa, cloves and water over medium hot stove for 15 minutes.
It will be rather thick and raisins will get soft.
Let cool.

title: "kentucky corn bread"
directions: Mix all together. Pour into large black greased skillet. Bake at 450° for 20 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine beans, soup, milk and pepper.
Add half can of dried onions and mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes. Ten minutes before done, sprinkle other half can of dried onions over the top.

title: beer nuts
directions: Electric skillet at 350°.
Combine all ingredients, and stir until dry.
Put on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool and store in airtight container.

title: 3-step cheese cake
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla. Blend well at medium speed in mixer. Add eggs and mix well.
Pour batter into ready to use graham cracker crust. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until center is almost set. Cool.
For best results, refrigerate 3 hours. Top with fresh fruit.

title: super sloppy joes
directions: Cook beef and onion together; drain.
Add remaining ingredients and cook until heated completely.
Serve on hamburger buns.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: miniature cheesecakes
directions: Line cupcake tins with cupcake liners.
Place 1 vanilla wafer in each liner.
Mix cream cheese, vanilla and sugar until well blended.
Add eggs.
Mix until smooth.
Pour over wafers to 3/4 full.
Bake 25 minutes at 325°.
Top with fruit or sour cream and fruit when cool.

title: hard soap
directions: Dissolve can of lye and Borax in warm water.
Let stand for 1 hour.
Add melted grease and ammonia and stir 10 minutes.
If you want to use as hand soap in your bathroom, add a 10 cent bottle of your favorite perfume.
Mold in square box.
Let stand overnight. Cut in cakes.

title: tuna stuffed tomatoes(low calorie)
directions: Drain tuna. Combine tuna, celery, mayonnaise, chopped parsley, green onion and pepper. Cut tops off tomatoes and scoop out seeds. Turn upside down to drain. Fill with tuna salad.
Serve chilled on parsley lined plate.
Makes 36 appetizers.
Contains 21 calories per appetizer.

title: southwestern lasagne
directions: Brown beef in oil with onions and garlic.
Add tomato paste, water, salt, sugar and oregano; simmer for 15 minutes.
Cook noodles as directed.
Grate cheese.
Remove seeds from chilies. Layer noodles, sauce, cheeses and green chilies into a 10 x 15-inch pan.
This makes 3 layers.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Let set 10 minutes before serving.
Serves 8.

title: one egg cake
directions: Cream oil and sugar.
Add egg, vanilla and milk.
Mix in flour. Pour into greased pans and bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Bake
cake from directions on cake mix box.
Use only 3 egg whites.
Use
juice
from
drained	pineapple
as part of liquid in	cake.
After
cake
is	baked and still warm, poke holes
in cake
and pour over the cake, the can of Coco Lopez and
smooth over.
Put cake in the refrigerator to cool.
Take out the Cool Whip and fold in drained pineapple and coconut if desired; put on cake.
Put cake in refrigerator until ready to eat.

title: dirt
directions: Mix altogether and serve in a large pail.

title: cocoa mounds
directions: Blend together first 4 ingredients; stir over medium heat until boiling.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in the last 3 ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.

title: beef burgundy
directions: Mix together.
Cook at 325° for 3 hours.

title: orange and zucchini cake
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg. Set aside.
In large mixing bowl beat sugar, oil and eggs until well combined.
Stir in cereal, peel and vanilla.
Add flour mixture, zucchini and nuts.
Mix well.
Spread evenly in greased 10 x 6 x 2-inch (1 1/2-quart) glass baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes or until wooden pick inserted near center comes out clean. Cool completely.
Spread with Orange Cream Frosting.

title: shish kabobs
directions: Combine crushed chips with ground chuck, eggs, cheese, parsley, salt and pepper.
Mix lightly but thoroughly.
Shape mixture into 30 balls, about 1-inch in diameter.
Arrange meat balls, bacon slices, mushrooms, green peppers and tomatoes alternately on skewers.
Baste with butter and cook over low heat 10 to 15 minutes, turning and basting every 3 to 4 minutes.

title: spinach salad
directions: Wash and drain spinach.
Tear into bite size pieces.
Brown sesame seed, Ramen and almonds in margarine.

title: leona's carrot cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in medium bowl.
Pour into well-greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 300° for 60 minutes.
Top with sour cream icing.

title: corn pudding
directions: In 2-quart greased baking dish, heat milk until it comes to a boil.
Put eggs and 2 cups corn in blender. Blend until smooth. Add remainder of corn, bell pepper, onion, salt and hot sauce to hot mixture. Remove from heat and stir in eggs.
Bake, uncovered, 45 minutes at 325°.

title: snail cookies
directions: Have children roll out pie crust dough on floured surface, then let them spread it with butter and sprinkle it with cinnamon-sugar mixture.
Roll up dough and slice it, putting each piece on a cookie sheet.
Bake about 5 minutes at 350° or until done, depending on how thick the kids sliced the dough.

title: cracker bread(food processor method)
directions: Preheat oven to 475 degrees. Flour a large baking sheet (needs to be at least 10 x 15 inches). In the bowl of a food processor fitted with the steel blade, combine the flour, salt, sugar, egg, butter, and milk. Process until the dough forms a ball.
Let stand for at least 1 hour. On a lightly floured surface, roll the dough very thin (about 1/8 inch thick). Combine the seeds in a small bowl.
Sprinkle the seeds over the dough. Roll the dough again just enough to push the seeds into the dough. Place on the large floured baking sheet.

title: barley pilaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter and brown barley in butter. Transfer to casserole dish.
Saute onions and mushrooms.
Add to casserole.
Add broth.
Mix well.
Cover.
Bake 1 hour.
Serves 10.

title: pineapple banana shake
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 1/4 c. juice and setting aside. Combine pineapple, reserved juice, milk, banana and vanilla in container of an electric blender.
Process until smooth.
Add ice cubes, process until frothy.

title: southern chocolate cake
directions: Mix flour and sugar together in a large mixing bowl.
In a small saucepan, mix margarine, oil, water and cocoa.
Heat until margarine is melted.
Add to flour and sugar.
Mix eggs, buttermilk and soda in a small bowl.
Add to batter mix.
Stir well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken casserole 2
directions: Cook chicken and debone.
Cook macaroni in 1 cup of chicken broth and water.
Cook until tender.
Mix macaroni, chicken and soup together.
Add salt and pepper.
Add 1/2 cup of milk, if needed.
Pour in a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Bake about 30 minutes at 350°.
Cracker crumbs may be added the last 10 minutes of baking.

title: rotel chops
directions: Brown pork chops on one side in frypan.
Place pork chops brown side down in baking dish on top of rice.
Add water and Ro-Tel.
Add chopped green pepper and onion.
Add garlic salt and pepper.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: ad hoc split-pea soup
directions: Chop onions, carrots and celery. Place split peas, vegetables and seasonings to taste in large pot and add 2 1/2 quarts of water. Cook over low heat for 1 hour or more. Remove bay leaves before serving.

title: grace hart's party cheese ball
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and Cheddar cheese.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Chill.
Shape into a ball and roll in nuts.

title: corn-macaroni casserole
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in margarine.
Melt cheese in milk. Add all ingredients together.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Pour into 9X13-inch baking dish.
Baked covered for 1 hour at 350°.
Stir occasionally.

title: vegetable cheese soup
directions: Turn vegetables into saucepan.
Add onion, flour, salad herbs, salt and black pepper; mix until vegetables are well coated with flour.
Add chicken broth and milk; heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Cook until thickened, about 5 minutes.
Just before serving, blend in the Cheddar cheese and cream cheese.
Taste the soup and add mustard, if desired.
Serve immediately.

title: southwestern style chicken
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Place chicken breasts in greased 12 x 8-inch baking pan.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Cover with foil; bake 20 minutes.
In medium bowl combine cheese and chilies.
Pat on top of each chicken breast; sprinkle with green onion and bacon.
Return to oven uncovered.
Continue baking 12 to 15 minutes or until chicken is fork tender.
Place on serving plate; top with sour cream and avocado.
Serves 4.

title: diabetic cake
directions: Cook raisins in water until water is gone.
Add applesauce or chopped apples, eggs, sweetener, and oil.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Blend in dry ingredients and nuts.
Bake in greased and floured pan at 325° for 1 hour or until done.

title: kidney bean relish
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except kidney beans.
Mix into kidney beans and serve.

title: turkey tail adobo
directions: Cut turkey tails in half.
In a large saucepan, combine all ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Cover,
lower
heat
and simmer for 1 hour.
Drain off liquid.
Simmer,
uncovered, for 15	more minutes, or until turkey is browned.
Makes
servings.

title: rice topping
directions: Melt 1 stick of butter in skillet or Wok.
Add onion, bell pepper, mushrooms, and seasonings.
Cook until tender.
Pour into bowl to be used later.
Melt 1 stick of butter in Wok and add shrimp and seasoning and cook until done.
Add to bowl mixture. Melt 1 stick of butter in Wok and add oysters and seasoning.
Cook until done.
Add ingredients from bowl back into Wok and cook until done.
Pour over cooked rice.

title: pig in a blanket
directions: Roll out
dough
to 3/8-inch thickness. Cut into strips and wrap around
hot
dogs.
Place
on a stick and cook over a hot fire for about 10 minutes.

title: apricot bars
directions: Finely chop apricots in food processor.
Transfer to a 1-quart saucepan and add canned pineapple with juice. Cover and simmer 20 minutes, checking several times to be sure liquid has not evaporated.
Add 1/2 cup sugar and simmer 2 to 3 minutes more. Remove from heat and cool.
With an electric mixer, cream butter and 1 cup sugar until blended.
Add flour, salt and soda; mix well.
Add nuts and coconut.
Press 2/3 of dry mixture into a lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes. Remove from oven and cool for 10 minutes.
Spread pineapple and apricot filling over crust. Sprinkle remaining crumbs over entire filling pressing down gently.
Return to oven and bake 17 to 20 minutes longer.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: italian casserole
directions: Cook noodles and rinse.
Brown sausage and onion.
Drain. Combine all the other ingredients except 2 tablespoons cheese.
In large casserole, bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Add remaining cheese and bake additional 10 minutes.

title: spinach squares
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cheese, spinach and butter in blender.
Set aside.
Melt cheese and butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix everything together in pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: beef ball
directions: Mince beef in food processor.
Set aside.
Mince onions, including stems, in food processor.
Soften cream cheese.
Mix beef, onions and cream cheese in a large bowl.
Roll into a large ball.
Refrigerate.
Serve with crackers.

title: cheesy potato soup
directions: Combine potatoes, carrots, celery and onion in a large pot. Add salt and enough water to cover the vegetables. Boil for about 20 minutes or until vegetables are soft. Slightly mash some (but not all) of the potatoes. Take mixture off stove. Stir in the rest of the ingredients. Return to stove and heat on medium-low until cheese is melted and soup is bubbly.

title: clam chowder
directions: Combine potatoes, onion, milk and butter in saucepan.
Bring to a boil over low heat.
Add clams (including juice).
Remove small amount of liquid and add a tablespoon of cornstarch.
Mix well.
Pour back into saucepan and stir.
Simmer for a few minutes.
Repeat until desired thickness is reached.

title: apricot salad
directions: Mix sugar, water and pineapple (not drained).
Cook over low heat and simmer a few minutes until it boils.
Add Jell-O.
Remove from heat.
Soften cream cheese; cut into small pieces.
Whip cream cheese into Jell-O mixture.
Add another cup of cold water to mixture while beating in cream cheese.
Place in refrigerator until it begins to congeal.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into shallow 9 x 13-inch dish.
Best if left in refrigerator overnight.
This recipe may be halved.

title: homemade rolls
directions: In bowl, dissolve yeast in water. Add milk, sugar, salt, egg and flour to yeast. Turn onto floured board. Knead until smooth. Put in greased bowl; cover. Let rise until double, about 1 1/2 hours. Punch down; let rise again, about 30 minutes. Shape and let rise. Bake in 400° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: viv's chicken fajitas
directions: In bowl or shallow baking dish, mix all ingredients except chicken.
Add chicken and marinate 2 to 6 hours, stirring meat at least once.
Grill chicken over hot coals 5 minutes; turn and grill 5 minutes more.
Baste with the marinade if desired.
Cut chicken into small pieces.
Make fajitas.

title: easy fruit crunch
directions: *Fruit Equivalents: One pint blueberries or 6 to 8 medium apples or peaches.

title: hawaiian salad
directions: Mix all together and chill several hours before serving.

title: buttermilk-chive biscuits
directions: In a medium mixing bowl, combine the flour, chives, baking powder, baking soda, salt and pepper.
Stir together the buttermilk and oil; pour into flour mixture.
Stir with a fork until combined.
Drop onto a greased baking sheet in 6 mounds. Bake in 450° oven for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden.
Serve warm.
Makes 6 biscuits, 95 calories and 0 mg cholesterol per biscuit.

title: cherry cobbler
directions: Melt butter in baking dish in microwave.
Combine all other ingredients except pie filling and pour over butter.
Spoon pie filling over batter.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes, or until bubbly.
Cut into squares.
Serve individual servings with sauce.

title: dirt cake
directions: Cream sugar, cream cheese and oleo.
In large bowl, mix milk and pudding and add to cheese mixture.
Mix in Cool Whip.
Crumble cookies in food processor.
Layer "dirt" and pudding.
Begin and end with dirt.
Can be made in clean flower pot.
Add a spray of artificial flowers and use as centerpiece until dessert time.

title: janet's whole wheat bread
directions: Dissolve the yeast in 1/2 cup warm water; large mixing bowl is good.
Heat to warm the milk, 1 cup water, salt, honey and butter. Pour into the large bowl.
Stir this mixture to make sure the yeast is all dissolved.
Add 3 cups whole wheat flour; stir.
Add 2 more cups flour.
Stir well.
Add 1/2 cup flour.
Stir.
Put 1/2 cup flour on table.
Knead dough.
Let it rise until double in bulk, then knead and cut dough in half.
Butter two bread pans.
Put the dough in them and bake in preheated oven of 375° for about 25 minutes.

title: aunt helen's no bake cheese cake
directions: Mix cream cheese and Cool Whip together with electric mixer. When creamy slowly begin adding confectioners sugar (use entire box).
Beat until smooth.
Pour equal amounts into crust.
Chill in refrigerator for 2 hours before serving.
Store in refrigerator.
Top with fruit or chocolate sauce, if desired.

title: "lemon squares"
directions: Combine and
mix the first 4 ingredients. Pat evenly into pan and bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: hearty stuffed peppers
directions: Cut off tops of green peppers and remove seeds.
Wash peppers and set aside.
Brown sausage in skillet.
Add onions and mushrooms.
Cook until tender.
Drain sausage.

title: custard crunch pie
directions: Blend dry ingredients and slowly add to the eggs remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into pie shell and bake in hot oven at 400° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake another 30 minutes.

title: chicken p d q
directions: Arrange breast halves around edge of shallow 10-inch casserole with lid.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Microwave on High about 6 minutes.
Use in chicken salad.

title: never fail meringue
directions: Mix first four ingredients and cook until clear, set aside to cool.
Take egg whites and add a pinch of salt.
Beat until peaked.
Add mixture that was set aside and beat until creamy. Add 6 tablespoons of sugar gradually.
Beat until creamy.
Bake until brown at 300°.
For 2 pies, double all ingredients.

title: the macaroni routine
directions: Saute onion lightly in small amount of butter.
Combine all ingredients, adding the macaroni last.
If too dry or too wet, add more milk or bread accordingly.
Pour into an oiled casserole dish and bake in a 400° oven until it bubbles, then turn oven down to 325° until the middle is done.
It is better baked longer time at the lower temperature.

title: lemon berry pie
directions: Beat cream cheese, 1 tablespoon of milk and sugar in bowl using wire whisk until smooth. Stir in lemon peel and juice.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups of whipped topping. Spread evenly in bottom of crust.
Press strawberry halves into cream cheese layer.
Pour 2 cups of milk into large bowl.
Add pudding mixes. Beat with wire whisk 1 minute. Let stand 1 minute or until thickened.
Gently stir in 1 cup whipped topping.
Spoon over strawberries in crust. Refrigerate 4 hours or until set.
Garnish with remaining whipped topping and strawberry halves.

title: michael's green bean delight
directions: Cook green beans slowly on stove or in slow cooker with water and beef bouillon cube.
Add the ham and onions.
Add bacon, if desired.
When beans are just about done, approximately 2 hours, add 2 to 3 cups of potatoes, cut up.
Add pepper to taste.
Keep water level up.
Cook until potatoes are done, approximately 1 more hour.
Serve with Italian bread.
Yummy.

title: pineapple glaze
directions: In a pan, mix cornstarch and 1/4 cup pineapple juice until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients; cook until thick and transparent.

title: face paint
directions: Combine the ingredients and place in each cup of a muffin tin. Use a different color for each cup.
Your face paint is now ready!

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Combine all ingredients; beat for 2 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Cool 10 minutes in pan.
Spoon glaze over tops and sides.
Makes 2 large, 3 medium or 5 mini loaves. Freezes well; wrap in foil.

title: easy cheesy souffle
directions: Melt butter and dip bread into it.
Put into baking dish. Layer cheese and bread squares alternately.
Beat eggs.
Add milk and beat again.
Pour over bread and cheese.
Let stand for several hours or overnight.
Bake in slow oven, 325°, for 45 minutes to an hour.
Serve at once.
Serves 6.

title: tang pie
directions: Mix well condensed milk and Tang.
Add sour cream and 1/2 carton Cool Whip.
Pour into cracker crust.
Add rest of Cool Whip to top of pies.
Refrigerate.
Freezes well.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix spices with Worcestershire; set aside.
Soften all cheeses; put in closed container and leave at room temperature after mixing all cheeses and spice mix.
Then refrigerate for 2 hours.
Roll into a ball, then roll ball in nuts.
Chill overnight.

title: pimento cheese casserole
directions: Peel and slice potatoes.
Layer in greased casserole dish.
Mix milk and flour.
Melt butter and add milk/flour mixture.
Heat until thickens.
Add 2 cups grated cheese and stir well.
Pour over potatoes.
Sprinkle pimento over potato mixture and top with 1 cup grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: italian meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Generously grease large loaf pan.
Mix all the ingredients except catsup and bacon; reserve and set aside. Mix remaining ingredients generously and form mixture into greased loaf pans and then spread catsup on top of meat loaf.
Last lay bacon strips on top.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or longer.
Makes 8 servings.

title: crescent chicken
directions: Mix together Cheddar cheese and deboned chicken. Place in crescent rolls. Roll up and press on ends to seal. Mix cream of chicken soup with milk until well blended. Heat. Pour into casserole dish and place rolls in. Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes. Top with extra grated cheese, if desired.

title: pat-in-pan pie crust(one 8 or 9-inch pie crust)
directions: Place flour, sugar and salt in pie pan and mix with fingers until blended.
In a measuring cup, combine oil and milk and beat with a fork until creamy.
Pour all at once over the flour mixture.
Mix with a fork until flour mixture is completely moistened.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Store in airtight container. Mix 2 or 3 teaspoons to 1 cup hot water.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions on box.
Bake in 2 round cake pans.
Cool.
Mix pudding according to directions on box.
Put one cake layer in bottom of punch bowl.
Cover with 1/2 of the pudding.
Cover with 1/2 cherry pie filling, then 1/2 of the pineapple, 1/2 of the coconut, 1 carton Cool Whip and 1 cup of pecan halves.
Repeat with second cake layer and remaining ingredients.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Saute mushrooms in butter and pour into a large mixing bowl. Add seasonings, cooked chicken, soup and sour cream.
Mix well. Cook spaghetti noodles; drain and place in a buttered baking dish. Top with chicken mixture and sprinkle generously with Parmesan cheese.
Bake, covered, for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Bake, uncovered, for additional 10 to 15 minutes to brown top.

title: best ever pound cake
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar, beating at medium speed until well mixed.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each egg.
Add flour to creamed mixture alternately with milk, starting and ending with flour; mix until blended.
Stir in flavorings. Pour in greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 40 minutes.

title: homemade chicken noodle soup
directions: Beat eggs with salt thoroughly.
Add flour until ball forms. Roll out dough.
Cut into slices and then into pieces.
Sprinkle crushed bouillon cube over dough before cutting.
Roll it in with rolling pin.
Add 3 chicken cubes to pot of boiling water, then add noodles.
Use 4 to 5 pieces chicken, cut into pieces.
Add cubes, water and noodles.
Let cook for 1 hour or until tender. For thicker broth, mix milk and flour and add it.

title: caramel corn
directions: Boil first 4 ingredients together for 5 minutes, then add vanilla and baking soda, stirring often. After corn is popped, put in roasting pan.
Pour boiled liquid over corn.
Bake at 200° for 1 hour. Stir corn every 20 minutes to coat evenly. When finished, spread caramel corn out on Reynolds Wrap until cool and store in a can.

title: orange bars
directions: Mix until well blended.
Press down in an 8-inch square pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, until light brown.
Don't overcook.

title: crab cakes
directions: Break in small pieces and moisten bread with milk; mix ingredients; shape into cakes.
Fry quickly until brown.

title: reuben roll
directions: Combine beef, onion, Worcestershire, Russian dressing, salt, egg, pepper and Russian dressing.
Mix well.
Roll out jelly roll fashion.
In 1/2 of beef mixture add a layer of cheese and layer of sauerkraut.
Place the other 1/2 of beef mixture over cheese and kraut.
Best to roll on foil, then lift the foil to place beef over the filling.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, 1/2 time reduce to 300°. Do not overbake.

title: mexican hobo dinner casserole
directions: Form meat into bite-size patties.
Place into casserole dish. Alternate in layer the cubed carrots, potatoes and onion.
Spread drained kidney beans on top.
Now add hot peppers.
Spread soup on top.
Cover dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: homemade noodles
directions: Mix eggs and milk.
Sift in dry ingredients.
Roll on floured board.
Dough must be very stiff.
Roll like jelly roll and slice into thin strips.
Let dry or can be cooked at once.
These freeze real well.

title: crab dip
directions: Dissolve Knox gelatine in 3 tablespoons of cold water.
Warm soup and mix with gelatine; let cool, then mix with remaining ingredients.
Set overnight (at least).
Serve on Waverly brand crackers.
Serves lots.

title: 24 hour heavenly hash salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 4 cups boiling water.
While hot, add marshmallows.
Let cool.
Add drained pineapple and stir well. Refrigerate 24 hours, then beat until fluffy.
Fold in Cool Whip and 1/4 cup chopped nuts.
Refrigerate until set.

title: repta denton's ambrosia
directions: With sharp knife, clip oranges into bits.
Grate coconut, layer of oranges, pineapple, coconut, alternately.
Pour over all the juice from the pineapple and the juice of 1 lemon which has been weakened a little with water and sweetened.
This may be served with or without sour cream.

title: chocolate bread pudding
directions: Break bread into small pieces.
Soak in fruit cocktail juice and water.
Mix eggs, sugar and butter and beat until fluffy. Melt chocolate with milk in double boiler.
Add all ingredients to bread.
Stir in fruit cocktail, baking powder and vanilla.
Cook for 45 minutes in 375° oven.
Cook in a 7 x 11-inch pan.
Cool and serve.

title: potatoes au gratin
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water to cover, 8 minutes or until tender (do not overcook).
Drain and set aside.
Combine cottage cheese and buttermilk in container of an electric blender or food processor; process until smooth.
Transfer to a large bowl; stir in potatoes, chives and next 3 ingredients.
Spoon into a 1-quart casserole coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes; sprinkle with cheese and paprika and bake an additional 5 minutes. Yield:
6 servings.

title: chinese salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: betty crocker's swiss steak
directions: Mix flour, mustard and salt.
Sprinkle one side of beef steak with half of the flour mixture; pound in.
Turn beef and pound in remaining flour mixture.
Cut beef into 6 serving pieces.

title: squash ring
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Add squash, eggs, sugar, salt and pepper.
Cook on top of stove until thick.
If squash doesn't mound when dropped from a spoon, add 2 tablespoons flour.
Bake in well-greased and floured ring mold for 1 hour.
Remove and fill the center of ring with green beans.

title: blueberry peach pie
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a medium saucepan.
Bring to a boil over medium heat; cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add gelatin, stirring until gelatin dissolves. Cool.
Combine peaches and blueberries in a large bowl.
Add gelatin mixture and toss gently.
Spoon into prepared pastry shell.
Cover and chill 1 hour or until set.
Serve with sweetened whipped cream.
Yields 1 (9-inch) pie.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: For Sauce:
Cook onion in margarine until tender.
Stir in flour, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/8 teaspoon of pepper.
Add milk all at once.
Cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Remove from heat.

title: maid's night out casserole
directions: Butter a large baking dish and cover with one layer of thinly sliced potatoes and onion.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper, crushed particles of sage leaves and small pieces of butter.
Repeat until potatoes are used up.
Place pork chops on top and sprinkle with salt, pepper, sage, paprika and butter.
Bake at 350° for one hour.
Turn chops and bake until brown.

title: stuffed chicken breast
directions: Debone chicken breasts, then split in half; pound with mallet. Top with 1/2 slice Swiss cheese.
Add slice of ham.
Place cream cheese in center; roll up.
Wrap slice of bacon around rolls, secure with toothpicks.
Place in flat baking dish.
Cover with one can of mushrooms and one stick of melted butter.
Bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: savory crescent chicken squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Blend cream cheese and 2 tablespoons of margarine until smooth.
Add next 5 ingredients; mix well. Separate dough into 4 rectangles; firmly press perforations around edges together to seal.
Spoon 1/2 cup of meat mixture onto center of each rectangle.
Pull 4 corners of dough to top center of chicken mixture; twist slightly and seal edges.
Place on cookie sheet.
Brush top with reserved 1 tablespoon of margarine. Sprinkle with crouton crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Serves 4.

title: flaming strawberry omelet
directions: Beat the egg yolks with salt in a mixing bowl until light. Add the sugar and 1 tablespoon of rum and mix well.
Beat the egg whites until stiff and fold into the yolk mixture.
Melt the butter in a chafing dish.
Pour egg mixture into pan and cook over medium heat, pulling egg mixture from sides to middle until set. Fold in half and sprinkle with additional sugar.
Ignite remaining rum in a ladle and pour over omelet slowly.
Serve flaming with strawberries.
Yields 4 servings.

title: salmon puff
directions: Cut or tear bread into small pieces.
Mix bread, milk and margarine; stir in salmon, egg yolks, lemon juice, onion, salt and pepper.
Beat egg whites until stiff; fold into salmon mixture. Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with paprika. Cook uncovered in 350° oven 1 hour.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Mix ingredients together in medium size pot.
Cook on medium heat until chocolate reaches desired thickness.
Makes enough for 3 to 4 layer cake (may be more depending on thickness).

title: chili bean dip
directions: Mash beans with tomato sauce.
Add spices and cheese.
Serve with corn chips.
Yields 18 servings, 40 calories per serving.

title: plantation pralines
directions: Combine sugar, cream of tartar, salt and milk.
Stir over low heat until sugar dissolves.
Cook to soft ball stage.
Cool to 220°.
Add butter extract and pecans.
Spoon onto waxed paper.

title: 2 x 4 soup
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Place in crock-pot with remaining ingredients and simmer for 3 to 4 hours.

title: black bean soup
directions: Soak beans overnight in enough water to cover, then drain. Add 5 quarts cold water and cook beans over low heat for 1 1/2 hours.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with onions and peppers.
Cook macaroni and drain.
Mix macaroni, beef and tomato sauce.
Put in baking dish and spread jar of pizza sauce on top.
Put pepperoni and cheese on top.
Bake at 375° until cheese is melted and browned.
Serves 6.

title: pumpkin torte
directions: Dissolve gelatin in cold water.
Fold into pumpkin mixture. Beat egg whites until stiff and add sugar and beat until mixed. Fold into pumpkin mixture.
Pour over crust.
Top with Cool Whip when ready to serve.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Pour vinegar, water, sugar and salt mixture over the cucumbers, onion and hot pepper pod; let stand 2 hours. Refrigerate and use as needed.

title: apple cake
directions: Combine sugar and apples.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Melt butter, add egg and dry ingredients.
Stir in apples and sugar.
Pour into greased 8-inch square pan and bake in 350° oven for 55 minutes.

title: dates and walnut cake
directions: Mix well.
Using a 9 x 9-inch cake pan, cook at 350° for 45 minutes, or until well cooked.

title: zippy beef roast
directions: Brown meat well in oil in large skillet or Dutch oven.
Mix remaining ingredients together and pour over browned meat.
Cover tightly and simmer for 2 1/2 to 3 hours, or until meat is tender. Add water during cooking, if necessary.
Skim excess fat from pan and serve roast with remaining sauce.
Serves 4.

title: jumbo gingersnaps
directions: Into large bowl, measure 1/2 cup sugar and remaining ingredients.
With mixer at low speed, beat until well blended. Preheat oven to 350°.
Place 2 tablespoons sugar on waxed paper. Shape 1/4 cup dough into a ball; roll in sugar to coat.
Place balls 3 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
(Dough is very soft; balls will flatten slightly.)
Bake 15 minutes; remove cookies to wire rack to cool.
Store cookies in containers.

title: chocolate chip coffee cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, sour cream and vanilla. Beat.
Add dry ingredients and beat until smooth.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Grease and flour angel food cake pan.
Pour half of the batter in the pan and sprinkle with 1/2 the topping.
Pour in the remaining batter and sprinkle with the remaining topping. Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: hawaiian chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: me maw's chocolate sauce
directions: Melt and coat pan with butter.
Turn off heat.
Blend in cocoa, sugar and milk.
Turn heat on and boil 3 or 4 minutes.
Turn heat off and cool without stirring (this is very important).
When sauce is warm not hot, add vanilla and stir.
Serve warm over vanilla ice cream.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix well and spread in casserole dish.

title: pina colada coconut cake
directions: Bake yellow cake mix with pudding in oblong pan according to directions.
While warm, pierce with a fork.
Mix Eagle Brand milk and pina colada mix.
Pour over warm cake.
Frost with Cool Whip and top with coconut. Refrigerate.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese, potato chips and almonds in a large mixing bowl.
Spread into lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with almonds, potato chips and cheese, in that order. Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Bake in 400° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: homemade butter
directions: Oleo should be room temperature.
Mix and add buttery flavor oil.
Blend well and
freeze.

title: spinach cheese bake
directions: Thaw and drain spinach thoroughly.
Cut Cheddar cheese into small cubes.
Mix together all ingredients thoroughly.
Spoon into a greased (Crisco) 8-inch square baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, in a 375° oven for 45 minutes or until set.
Let cool 10 minutes before serving.
Serves 4.

title: indonesian pork sticks with crunchy hot peanut sauce
directions: You will need 10 to 12 bamboo skewers.

title: dad's easy beef stroganoff
directions: Partially thaw steak and cut into little pieces.
Mix all ingredients together.
Slow cook 3 to 4 hours in slow cooker or stove top on low.
Serve over noodles.

title: country style chicken kiev
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Melt butter, then mix crumbs, cheese and spices.
Spread mixture on wax paper.
Dip chicken in melted butter.
Roll in crumbs.
Lay chicken in baking dish and bake 45 minutes, uncovered.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix together the flour, baking powder and salt in a medium-sized bowl.	Cut in shortening.
Add vinegar and egg, then add water.	Mix to form a dough ball, separate into two balls, roll out on a floured surface.
Makes two 9 inch crusts.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Add vanilla, sugar and oil; beat until foamy. Stir in zucchini.
Sift together the flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Add nuts; mix.
Add dry mixture to zucchini mixture; stir until blended.
Do not overmix.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 60 minutes.

title: strawberry jam
directions: Measure 2 cups mashed strawberries into large bowl.
Then stir in sugar and let stand for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally. Then mix water and pectin in small saucepan.
Bring to boil on high heat, stirring constantly.
Continue boiling and stirring for 1 minute.
Stir into fruit mixture and keep stirring for 3 minutes or until sugar is completely dissolved.
Then fill plastic freezer containers and let stand at room temperature for 24 hours.
Then place in freezer.
Makes about 6 cups of jam.

title: lipton-onion burgers
directions: In a large bowl, combine soup, ground beef and water.
Shape into 8 patties.
Grill until done.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix together Jell-O, flour, sugar and water.
Cook over low heat and bring to boil (full).
Remove from heat immediately. Pour over strawberries in pie shell.
Let cool in refrigerator until cool.
Cover with Cool Whip and serve.
Eat well.

title: chili con carne(zesty "south of the border" specialty)
directions: Cook beef and onion in hot butter or drippings until browned. Add kidney beans and tomato soup; cook 10 minutes.
Make into a paste the chili powder, flour, water and salt; blend in.
Cook over low heat, stirring frequently, 45 minutes.
Serve hot with crackers or hot Fried Corn Meal Mush.
Makes 8 servings.

title: green bean wraps
directions: You also need toothpicks.

title: kentucky corn
directions: Mix and pour in casserole dish and bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: cream of cauliflower & cheese soup
directions: Clean and cut cauliflower into 1/2 inch pieces.
Steam in 1/2 cup of water until tender.
Do not drain.
Set aside.
Melt butter in sauce pan over medium heat.
Add flour to make a roux.
Cook for 2-4 minutes.
Add chicken stock, stirring with wire whip and bring to a boil.
Turn heat to low.
Add cauliflower, cheese, half & half, salt, and pepper.
Heat, but do not boil.

title: hush puppies
directions: Stir all ingredients together except oil.
Drop by teaspoons into hot vegetable oil (about 370°) until golden brown on all sides.
Drain on absorbent paper.

title: lena culp's cheesecake squares
directions: Mix cake mix, margarine and one egg.
Press mixture into a 13 x 9-inch pan, greased and floured.
Beat together cream cheese and brown sugar.
Blend in 2 eggs.
Beat in powdered sugar, vanilla and salt.
Pour over mixture in pan.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Peel and devein shrimp.
Saute onions, parsley and garlic in butter until onions are tender.
Reduce heat to low and add shrimp.
Cook, stirring frequently, 3 to 5 minutes.
Remove shrimp with a slotted spoon to a serving dish.
Keep warm.
Add remaining ingredients to butter mixture.
Simmer for 2 minutes.
Pour butter mixture over shrimp.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cavateni
directions: Brown beef, cook rigatoni shells and macaroni until tender, drain.
Mix beef, pepperoni, onion and pepper into Prego sauce. Grease 8x9-inch casserole dish.
Layer meat mixture, pasta, cheese and mushrooms.
Bake until bubbly in 350° oven about 30 minutes.

title: cheesed cauliflower
directions: Remove leaves and trim base from cauliflower.
Wash.
Cook in boiling salt water for 15 to 20 minutes or until tender.
Drain. Place in ungreased shallow baking pan.
Sprinkle with salt.
Mix mayonnaise and prepared mustard; spread over cauliflower.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 375° for about 10 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: brown and serve chicken
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Place chicken breasts in baking dish and spoon sugar mixture over breasts.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes, turning breasts every 15 minutes.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add frozen berries.
Add pineapple and nuts.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill.
Whip cream and beat in cream cheese.
Spread over jello layer.

title: all-in-one meal
directions: Use a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish lined with foil.
Cut meat up in small sections and put them on bottom of pan.
Season to taste. Put potatoes, carrots and onion all around meat.
Salt and pepper and add butter.
Cover with foil.
Bake in oven at 300°.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: ryzon "war meat" loaf
directions: Stir corn meal into boiling water.
When cooked to mush, add remaining items.
Pour into greased bread pan.
Bake in moderate 350° oven until brown.

title: texas beans
directions: Brown beef with onions.
Combine all ingredients.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Serve on corn bread or hot cooked rice.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Heat milk and marshmallows until melted.
Mix and freeze. Cut in squares and serve on lettuce leaf.

title: chocolate chip cookie cream cheese dessert
directions: Pat 1/2 cookie mix in bottom of 5 x 9-inch pan.
Whip softened cream cheese, vanilla and egg until well blended.
Pour over cookie mixture.
Spoon balance of cookie mix by teaspoonful over all. Bake 1/2 hour at 325° to 350°.
Double for 10 x 14-inch pan.

title: calico cabbage
directions: Put the first 5 ingredients in a baking dish.
Cut up the butter or margarine on top.
Cover; cook in oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: glazed ham in crock-pot
directions: Combine brown sugar and mustard.
Moisten with enough cola to make a smooth paste.
Rub entire ham with mixture.
Place in crock-pot.
Add remaining cola.
Cover and cook on low for 6 to 10 hours or on high, 2 to 3 hours.

title: corn fritters
directions: Stir beaten egg into corn.
Add butter, flour, milk and sugar. Stir well and season to taste.
Drop by spoonfuls one at a time in boiling oil.
Fry until golden brown.
Remove fritters from grease.
Drain.
Serve white hot.

title: butter rolls
directions: Use good biscuit recipe, adding 2 tablespoons of shortening. Divide dough into two parts, roll thin and spread generously with butter and cinnamon.
Roll each in jelly roll fashion.
Place in a greased dish.
Brush over lightly with melted butter or cooking oil and bake at 350° until brown, about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: butterscotch crunchy clusters
directions: In saucepan over low heat, melt chips with sweetened condensed milk.
In large bowl, combine chow mein noodles and peanuts.
Stir in butterscotch mixture.
Scoop up in tablespoon sized portions and drop onto waxed paper-lined baking sheets.
Chill 2 hours or until firm.

title: chicken and rice
directions: In large baking dish, spread uncooked rice.
Place chicken pieces in dish.
In saucepan, heat soup and water, then pour over chicken and rice.
Then sprinkle onion soup mix over chicken. Seal well with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken and mushroom dijon
directions: In skillet with 1 tablespoon hot margarine, cook chicken 10 minutes or until browned on both sides.
Remove.
In remaining 1 tablespoon hot margarine, cook broccoli and mushrooms until tender and liquid is evaporated, stirring often.
Stir in soup, milk and mustard.
Heat to boiling.
Return chicken to skillet.
Cover; cook over low heat 5 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink.
Serve over angel hair pasta.
tags: cream of chicken and broccoli soup

title: crunch parfaits
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spread cereal and coconut in ungreased pan (15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch).
Mix brown sugar and margarine; pour over cereal and coconut.
Bake until bubbly, 8 to 10 minutes. Cool.
Break into pieces.
Prepare instant pudding (pistachio or vanilla flavors are recommended).

title: cheese rolls
directions: Chop the green onion tops, jalapenos and pecans; set aside. Cut the cheese in 1/2 lengthwise.
Roll out between wax paper to an oblong shape.
Spread 1/2 of the cream cheese that has been softened on top of the Velveeta.
Sprinkle 1/2 of the green onion tops, jalapenos, pimentos and pecans over the cream cheese.
Put wax paper on top and gently pat into the cream cheese (just helps to make it roll better).
Start at one side and roll up like a jelly roll.
It helps to take hold of the wax paper and pull the roll over, then pull the wax paper from the cheese as you roll it. Cut ends off.
Make the second one using the other 1/2 of everything.
If you like it hotter, use more jalapenos; if you like it milder, use canned green chili pepper.

title: pork chitterlings
directions: Wash chitterlings thoroughly.
Remove some fat if there are dark spots on fat.
Some fat must be left on chitterlings.
Place chitterlings into a large pot.
Add water.
Season with vinegar, salt, red pepper and chopped onion.
Cook for 4 hours over very low heat.
Serve with collard greens and hot sauce.

title: sticky raisin buns
directions: In baking pan, melt margarine.
Add juice, sugar and cinnamon. Stir to combine.
Sprinkle raisins evenly over juice mixture. Separate biscuits and arrange in an 8 or 9-inch round baking pan over raisins.
Bake until biscuits are browned, 20 to 25 minutes in a 350° oven.
Remove pan from oven and top with 10-inch heatproof plate; invert biscuits onto plate and serve hot.

title: pickled cauliflower
directions: Break cauliflower into small pieces and put in canner.
Soak overnight with salt and alum.
Pour boiling water over that.
Next day, drain and rinse with cold water.
Put into canning jars with a hot pepper in the middle (cut off top of pepper, let seeds inside) and Mrs. Wage's kosher dill pickle mix.
Follow directions on mix to fill jars.
Run through canner 5 minutes at a boil.
if you don't have a full canner to soak, cut ingredients in half.

title: donna's coffee cake
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add eggs and sour cream.
Beat well.
Add dry ingredients.
Pour batter into a 9 x 13-inch greased cake pan.
Sprinkle brown sugar topping mixture.

title: my company recipe
directions: Cover with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350°.
Serves 18 to 20.

title: oven crusted chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In medium bowl, combine butter, flour, salt, thyme, rosemary and marjoram.
In shallow dish, place cereal.
Dip chicken in butter mixture; roll in cereal to coat. Place on rack in shallow baking pan.
Bake for 55 to 60 minutes, or until golden brown.
Makes 6 servings.

title: lite and easy fish for one
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray 12-inch square of foil with nonstick cooking spray.
Place fillet in center and all other ingredients on top.
Fold edges to seal.

title: six week muffins
directions: Mix all and pour into muffin pans.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Batter may be kept covered in fridge for up to 6 weeks.

title: easy and delicious coleslaw
directions: Stir all ingredients, except cabbage, until sugar dissolves. Add cabbage and toss.
Can serve after 2 hours, but tastes better if held overnight!

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender.
Mash the crackers into big crumbs.

Melt the margarine and stir it into the cracker crumbs. Put half of the buttered crumbs in the bottom of a baking dish. Put half of the broccoli on top of the crumbs, followed with a layer of Velveeta.
Add the rest of the broccoli and follow with another layer of Velveeta.
Put the remaining buttered cracker crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° until the Velveeta is melted.

title: bubble and squeak
directions: Heat drippings in a large heavy skillet.
Add onion and saute until tender, about 5 minutes.
Add potatoes and saute on both sides until browned.
Stir in carrots and cabbage; stir-fry until vegetables are golden and "squeak" in the skillet.
Stir in Worcestershire sauce and salt to taste.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch or 16 muffin pan.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: blueberry torte
directions: Blend cheese and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beaten. Gradually add milk.
Pour into pan and cook 20 to 25 minutes until set.
Cool.
Add 1 can blueberry pie filling; chill.
Top with whipped cream when served.

title: spinach quiche
directions: In a blender or processor combine all of the ingredients except pie shell.
Pour mixture into pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 350° and bake for 35 to 45 minutes, until done.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill and serve with crackers.

title: ranch fajitas
directions: Cut steak or chicken into 2 x 1/4-inch strips.
Brown in a nonstick skillet for 3 to 5 minutes.
Stir in peppers and cook 1 to 2 more minutes.
Stir in salad dressing mix and water; cook one minute and serve in tortillas.

title: food for the angel
directions: Crush Ritz crackers and walnuts together.
Beat egg whites stiff; gradually add sugar.
Add crackers and nuts.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool.
Spread whipping cream over cooled pan.
Decorate with cherries and coconut.

title: dirt dessert
directions: Combine both packages of pudding with milk.
Set in fridge to chill.
Divide all ingredients in 3 parts and layer in a trifle-like bowl, starting and ending with crushed cookies. Chill until serving time.

title: german apple cake
directions: Combine eggs and oil in mixing bowl.
Beat until foamy.
Beat in sugar.
Add vanilla.
Add flour, salt, soda and cinnamon.
Add flour mixture to batter; mix with a spoon.
Add apples and nuts. Spread into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
When cool, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs and oil.
Fold in the cream cheese and blueberry pie filling.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: blueberry streusel cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. In a bowl, combine blueberries, Eagle Brand and peel. In a large bowl, cut 3/4 cup butter into 1 1/2 cups biscuit mix until crumbly; add blueberry mixture. Spread in greased 9-inch square baking pan. In a small bowl, combine remaining 1/2 cup biscuit mix and sugar; cut in remaining 2 tablespoons butter until crumbly. Add nuts. Sprinkle over cobbler. Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes or until golden. Serve warm with vanilla ice cream and blueberry sauce. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: congo squares
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch sprayed dish.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: white bean minestrone
directions: In a large saucepan, heat olive oil.
When hot, saute the carrots, onion and celery for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add 6 cups water, soaked dry beans, tomatoes and oregano and simmer for 1 hour.
If using canned beans, add now with cabbage and potatoes and simmer 45 minutes.
Add zucchini and simmer for 5 minutes only.
Season to taste with pepper and add parsley or basil and Parmesan, if you wish.

title: lemon custard sponge cake(circa 1930)
directions: Mix butter and sugar.
Add lemon juice, rind and well-beaten egg yolks and mix well.
Add flour and milk alternately; beat thoroughly.
Fold in stiffly beaten, salted egg whites.
Pour into one quart casserole; set in a pan of hot water.
Bake 375 degrees for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve hot or cold.
Makes 4-6 servings.

title: purple pea hull jelly
directions: Cover pea hulls with water and cook until dark; strain juice. Use 6 cups of the juice.
Bring juice to a boil and add Sure-Jell. After it comes to a rolling boil, add sugar; stir well.
Let mixture come to a rolling boil for 15 minutes; set aside for 5 minutes.
Skim, pour into jars and seal.

title: ha' pennies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine softened butter, cheese, onion soup mix and flour.
Roll into logs 1/2-inch in diameter; wrap in waxed paper and chill.
Slice into rounds 1/4-inch thick.
Bake on greased cookie sheet for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve hot or cold. Yield: 5 to 6 dozen.

title: texas dang good pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° until slightly brown and well set.

title: kielbasa with red cabbage
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
In small bowl, combine brown sugar and next 6 ingredients.

title: pastiera pasqua(easter pudding)
directions: Combine eggs, salt and sugar.
Add milk.
Stir slowly and constantly.
Add vanilla, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Mix and add the rice to custard.
Pour into pastry lined casserole.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Heat soup. Soften gelatin in 1/4 cup of cold water.
Add gelatin to soup.
Add cream cheese and stir well until melted. Combine celery, onions, mayonnaise and shrimp.
Mix all together and place in mold.
Set overnight.

title: best doughnuts
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add eggs, milk and lard.
Mix all together.
Roll out about 1/2-inch thick.
Fry in deep, hot lard.
Drain.
Roll in granulated sugar.

title: black walnut jam cake
directions: Beat eggs, white sugar, Crisco or margarine, buttermilk and blackberry jam together.
Sift the flour, baking powder, salt, ginger, soda, cinnamon, cloves and nutmeg all together.
Mix flour mixture with the creamed mixture.
Add package of Dream Whip.
Add black walnuts and pecans.
Pour into pan and bake at 325° until done.
Bake in 3 layers for 35 to 40 minutes.
Use caramel icing.

title: glazed cornish hens
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Put hen, skin side up. Add bouillon and sprinkle hen with salt.
Cover pan with foil and bake 30 minutes. Remove foil and brush hens with glaze. Roast 20 minutes longer or until fork-tender, basting occasionally with glaze.
Serve.

title: mechado
directions: Insert fat strips, lengthwise, in beef.
In a deep pot or pan place the meat, laurel, tomato sauce, vinegar, salt to taste and water to cover.
Cover and simmer until tender.
Add potatoes, onions and pimientos and continue cooking.
When most of the broth has evaporated and potatoes are cooked, add the fat and stir well. Serve meat, sliced crosswise.

title: brownies
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Pour jar of marshmallow cream on top while hot.

title: corn relish
directions: Boil corn 5 minutes; cut from cob.
Combine remaining ingredients and simmer 20 minutes.
Thicken as you like with Pillsbury Best sauce and gravy flour.
Pack into jars.
Seal. Makes 6 quarts.
Heat jars before packing.

title: million dollar salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill overnight.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Boil chicken until tender. Place chicken pieces in a 9 x 13-inch pan. In a separate bowl, mix sour cream, soup and chicken broth. Pour over chicken pieces. Crumble Ritz crackers over the top. Sprinkle poppy seed on top. Drizzle melted butter over the top. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cranberry fruit mini-loaves
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 3 (5 x 3 x 2-inch) mini loaf pans.
Combine flour, cereal, sugar, baking powder, cinnamon and nutmeg in a bowl.
Combine cranberry sauce, orange juice, raisins, pecans, egg, oil and orange peel in a separate bowl.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring until just moistened.

title: mary harter's butterscotch pie filling
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar, salt and cornstarch.
Gradually add milk.
Stir while cooking over medium heat until bubbly, then cook 2 minutes more, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir small amount of the hot mixture into egg yolks, then return to hot mixture.
Cook 2 more minutes while stirring.
Remove from heat and add butter and vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell and spread with meringue and bake 12 to 15 minutes in a 350° oven until meringue is golden brown.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip, peanut butter and jelly.
Top crust with Magic Shell topping.
Allow to harden (putting in freezer will speed up this process).
Pour Cool Whip mixture into crust.
Drizzle top with Magic Shell.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: vegetarian mexican appetizer(recipe may be doubled or tripled)
directions: Layer in shallow serving dish each ingredient in order listed, topping with cheeses.
Top cheeses with a mixture of onions, tomatoes, olives and cilantro.
Serve with chips that will not break easily.

title: chicago style pizza
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain. Dissolve yeast in water. Add sugar and allow to set for at least 5 minutes. Place flour and salt in mixer. Add yeast and water to flour; knead with dough hook. Add oil and knead until smooth and elastic. Place in oiled bowl (lightly oiled with olive oil). Cover with damp towel and place in warm place until doubled in bulk (approximately 30 minutes).

title: banana bread
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add eggs beaten with salt and mashed bananas.
Stir in sweet milk.
Sift flour and baking soda together; stir in flour and chopped walnuts.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: bowl.
Stir in without beating the oil and eggs.
Add and stir in pineapple, pecans, bananas and vanilla.
Bake in three layers for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Shape mixture into a firm loaf; place in glass loaf or small baking dish and bake 40 to 45 minutes.

title: make ahead mashed potatoes
directions: Cook and mash the potatoes and mix the other ingredients in. Put in a buttered casserole and bake at 325° for 40 minutes.
May also be warmed in the microwave.

title: oatmeal carmelitas
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt caramels in evaporated milk in heavy saucepan.
Cool slightly.
Combine remaining ingredients except chocolate pieces and pecans in large mixing bowl.
Press half of mixture in bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes. Remove from oven.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips and pecans. Spread carefully with caramel mixture.
Sprinkle remaining crumbs on top.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes longer or until golden brown.
Cut into bars or squares.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread	rolls on ungreased cookie sheet, pressing edges and rolls together.
Make a lip around edge.
Bake at 375° for approximately 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix ground round, eggs, crumbs, Accent, water and soup mix together and pour into loaf pan.
Pour tomato sauce over all. Bake at 350°.

title: frozen jello salad
directions: May use other Jell-Os for color to fit special occasions.

title: no guilt brownies
directions: Over very low heat, melt chocolate (can use microwave).
Cool slightly.
In food processor or blender, puree all ingredients except chocolate until smooth.
Add melted chocolate.
Blend well. Pour in lightly buttered 8 inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 20-25 minutes or until just set.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar. Cut into squares.

title: renee's  strawberry cake
directions: Mix all ingredients. Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: rice pudding
directions: Mix together.
Bake in slow oven (300°) for 2 1/2 hours until rice is tender.
Stir several times during first 1/2 hour.

title: zucchini appetizers
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients and spread in pan.
Bake until golden brown, about 25 minutes.
Cut into 2 x 1-inch rectangles.
Refrigerate remaining appetizers.

title: brown rice
directions: Saute onion in margarine in skillet.
Stir into hot rice.
Add cheese and bacon; toss lightly.
Serve hot.

title: chilled blueberry pie
directions: Puree 1 cup blueberries in a food processor or blender; set aside.
Combine cornstarch and water in a pan; stir until blended. Add corn syrup, lemon juice and blueberry puree; bring to a boil. Stir constantly; boil for 1 minute.
Cool 1 hour.
Fold remaining 3 cups blueberries into mixture; set aside.
Beat whipping cream until foamy; gradually add powdered sugar.
Beat until soft peaks form.
Spread whipped cream in bottom of pie crust and up the sides.
Form a 1-inch shell.
Spoon blueberry mix into whipped cream shell.
Chill at least 4 hours.
Garnish with lemon and mint.

title: sugar-free dessert
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Add 1 cup of sugar-free applesauce.
Enjoy.

title: hot salsa
directions: Mix garlic, onion, jalapeno peppers and spices with lime juice and chop in blender.
Add cilantro and tomatoes and blend.
Will keep in a sealed jar in refrigerator for about a week.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and serve.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and heat.

title: fern's spinach noodle pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients except Parmesan cheese; mix well. Spread mixture in oiled 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, cut in squares.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: homemade chocolate cream pie
directions: Combine milk, flour, cocoa, eggs, sugar and salt.
Mix well. Cook on medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and butter.
Return to heat, stirring until butter is melted.
Pour into already baked pie shell. Garnish.

title: cheesy spinach party loaf
directions: Cut slice from top of bread; remove center (leaving 1-inch shell).
Cut removed bread into bite size pieces; reserve. Brush insides of shell with 3 tablespoons of margarine (melted). Place on cookie sheet with reserved bread.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: marinated mushrooms and vegetables
directions: In saucepan, combine the vinegar, oil, onion, garlic, 1 teaspoon salt, sugar, basil, oregano and 1/4 teaspoon pepper. Bring to boiling.
Simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.
In bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Pour hot marinade over vegetables; stir to coat.
Cover; chill several hours, stirring occasionally. Drain vegetables.
Serve in lettuce lined bowl.
Makes 7.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix all dry ingredients; dissolve yeast in the warm water. Mix with dry ingredients.
Add all other ingredients.
Roll out on floured board and cut into biscuits.
Place in pan, making sure each biscuit touches the other.
Brush with melted butter.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: zangy fruit
directions: Mix all ingredients together except orange juice, then add orange juice.

title: shipwreck hot dish
directions: Brown meat in skillet, stirring until crumbly.
Drain.
Spread potatoes and onion in 2-quart baking dish.
Layer pork and beans and browned meat over potatoes and onion.
Spoon soup over layers. Bake at 350° for 1 hour (11 x 7-inch dish).

title: chocolate pound cake(very moist)
directions: Cream the butter, shortening and sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Sift flour, cocoa, salt and baking powder together.
Add to creamed mixture, alternating with milk.
Stir in vanilla and blend well.
Pour batter into greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.

title: fish and green beans(serves 1)
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Place fish on aluminum foil; add onion powder and arrange green beans on top.
Fold foil; bake for about 25 minutes.

title: st. patrick's day cupcakes
directions: In a large bowl, stir together flour, pudding, sugar, chocolate chips, baking powder and salt.
In small bowl, combine eggs, milk, oil and vanilla.
Stir into flour mixture just until combined.
Fill greased muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.
Frost with cream cheese frosting; sprinkle with green sugar.
Makes 18.

title: old-fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add sour cream and vanilla. Beat in 1 egg.
Sift together and add to cream mixture the flour, salt, soda, baking powder and cinnamon.
Mix well.
Chill about 2 hours.

title: osilai pouletate normandine(chicken casserole)
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add milk.
Pour evenly over bread mixture. Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Take out 1 hour before baking.
Spread soup on top.
Bake, uncovered, in 325° oven for 40 minutes.
Sprinkle with grated Cheddar cheese.
Return to oven for 10 minutes.

title: parmesan squares
directions: Cut off bread crusts and cut into quarters.
Stack in 3's. Mix eggs and half and half.
Dip the stack of 3 squares into egg mixture, then in Parmesan cheese on all sides, except the bottom, which goes on the baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes in 350° oven.
They puff up and are delicious served right out of the oven.
Can be made ahead and frozen, then baked later.

title: mary's pumpkin pie
directions: Mix sugar, salt, eggs and pumpkin pie spice in bowl until smooth.
Stir evaporated milk and pumpkin.
Mix well.
Pour into unbaked 9-inch deep fluted pie shell.
Place in a preheated 425° oven. Bake for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake an additional 35 minutes or until custard is firm.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chocolate chip bars
directions: In small bowl, cream together the butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg, milk and vanilla.
Mix well; set aside.

title: kathy's chocolate cake
directions: Mix flour and
sugar.
Bring
margarine, cocoa, oil and water to a boil.
Add this mixture to flour and sugar mixture. Add buttermilk, eggs, soda and vanilla to first mixture.
Pour into three 9-inch pans and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: mexican slop
directions: Use a 9 x 14-inch baking dish.
Soften cream cheese.
Cover bottom of dish.
Layer with chili and green chilies.
Top with lots of shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: easter antipasto
directions: Line a large platter with lettuce leaves.
Arrange vegetables and eggs in separate sections on lettuce leaves.
Place tomato wedges around other vegetables and eggs.
Accent with leaves from celery sticks.

title: party cookies
directions: Blend shortening and sugar. Beat in vanilla and eggs. Sift remaining dry ingredients together. Add to the sugar and egg mixture. Stir in 1/2 cup of M&M's; decorate top of cookies with remaining M&M's. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: microwave chunky potato soup
directions: Microwave bacon
in
covered
2 quart casserole dish on High for 5
to
minutes
or
until
browned.	Drain and add potatoes, celery,
onion,
water and pepper.
Cover and microwave on High
for 10 to 12 minutes, stirring once. Combine 1/2 cup milk and
flour until smooth.
Stir this mixture, salt and remaining milk
into potatoes.
Microwave, uncovered, on High for 7 to
10 minutes or until thickened; stir twice.
Makes 1 quart.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch buttered (Pam works well) baking dish.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
May be served hot or cold.
Add chopped peppers and/or mushrooms for variety!
Recipe doubles for taller result but is still fluffy.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: purple cow fizz
directions: Add a scoop of ice cream to 1 cup of grape juice and 1 cup of ginger ale.

title: chewy cookies
directions: Mix the flour and brown sugar.
Add softened butter and eggs. Add pecans and blend well.
Pour in a greased 9 x 11-inch pan. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: lemon delite
directions: Crumble together like pie crust.
Add pecans.
Mix well. Press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes in 350° oven.
Cool.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Melt margarine.
Mix all together except corn flake crumbs. Spray a 9 x 13-inch casserole with Pam.
Add potato mixture. Sprinkle crumbs on top and bake, uncovered, 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: divinity fudge
directions: Do not use plastic utensils.
Make sure all utensils are free from grease or soap.
Mix sugar, syrup, salt and water in large heavy saucepan.
Cook over medium-high heat until a little dropped in cold water will snap apart.
Set syrup off heat.
Beat egg whites in a 4-quart bowl until stiff peaks form.
Pour syrup a little at a time in a thin stream into egg whites, beating all the time with the mixer.
When you have poured about half the syrup, you can then pour it directly out of the pan in a thin stream. When you have added all the syrup, continue beating until the candy is thick.
Add vanilla and food color and mix in.
Beat until it starts to hold its shape.
Add 1 1/2 cups walnuts.
Stir in.
Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper.

title: pudding fruit salad
directions: Mix pudding mix with milk.
Add juice, then sour cream.
Stir in fruit.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: oven stew
directions: Brown meat in shortening.
Put all ingredients in roaster. Bake at 325° for 3 hours.

title: brown-eyed susan cookies
directions: Cream butter; add rest of ingredients.
Roll into balls.
Put on cookie sheet and flatten.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 400°. Frost when cool.

title: sparkling lemonade
directions: Bruise a handful of peppermint leaves and lemon balm leaves (or lemon verbena).
Add 1 cup water to the leaves and frozen lemonade concentrate.
Let stand for 1 hour.
Strain.
Add ice and 1 quart ginger ale and 1 quart water.
Garnish with fresh mint leaves.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix in order given.
Cut or break shrimp.
Add cream or milk last, adding gradually for the desired consistency.

title: miracle (peanut butter) cookies
directions: Combine peanut butter and sugar; mix well.
Stir in egg and vanilla.
Roll dough into 3/4-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with a floured fork.
Bake cookies at 350° for approximately 10 minutes.
Allow to cool slightly before removing from pan.
Yields about 4 dozen.

title: broccoli
directions: Cook chicken and let cool in liquid.
Bone and cut in strips. Cook broccoli only until crisp-tender.
Mix together mayonnaise, half and half, cheese, lemon juice, curry and chicken soup.
Pour over chicken and broccoli.
Cover with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: saturday hamburger(serves four)
directions: Take hamburger and place into 10-inch mixing bowl.
Add Heinz, Worcestershire and A.1.
Blend briskly.
When liquid has blended into meat, add packet of onion soup mix.
Blend lightly.
Cook on grill (charcoal) or bake in oven at 400° for 30 minutes.
Serve on bun or sourdough.

title: granny's apple pie
directions: Slice apples until crust is heaping full. Pour mix of sugar, flour and cinnamon over apples. Slice butter over mixture. Place other crust over top. Mash edges together. Place in oven and bake at 350° until crust is golden brown.

title: dressing for macaroni or potato salad
directions: Thin with evaporated milk.

title: butterscotch sauce(microwave)
directions: In 8-cup microwave-safe glass bowl, combine all ingredients. Cook mixture on High (100% power) 5 minutes or until sugar dissolves and sauce boils, stirring twice.
Serve warm over ice cream or apple pie.
Makes 1 cup.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Add oatmeal to boiling water; cover and set aside.
Mix in order: butter, sugar, brown sugar, vanilla and eggs.
Add in order: flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and oatmeal.
After all ingredients are combined, mix well and bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 325° for 35 minutes or until done.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Mix pie crust according to directions and roll to 1/4-inch thickness.
Melt margarine and spread evenly across top of crust. Mix sugar, cinnamon and flour and sprinkle evenly across margarine and crust.
Roll crust into pinwheel.
Slice 1 inch thick rolls and place, cut side down, on baking sheet; bake at 450° for about 10 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: stuffed opakapaka
directions: Massage mayonnaise on fish inside and outside.
Season with garlic salt and pepper.
Stuff seafood medley in fish.
Add bacon in fish, slice lemon and lay on fish.
Wrap with ti leaves and foil.
Bake at 350° in preheated oven for 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: pepper corn salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well. Chill several hours to blend flavors.
Mix well before serving.
Makes 4 servings.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown meat and onion in oil.
Add tomatoes, paste and spices to meat.
Simmer 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: mushroom casserole
directions: Place half of the cubes into a buttered casserole.
Combine mushrooms, onions, celery and mayonnaise.
Place on top of cubes. Top with remaining cubes and spread cheese soup over all.
Cover and refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°, covered.
Then top with shredded cheese and bake 10 minutes more, uncovered.

title: bite-size fruitcake cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients and spoon out on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Let cool and remove from pan.

title: new potatoes gruyere
directions: Wash the potatoes thoroughly. Halve any large potatoes.
With a vegetable peeler, peel a strip around the center of each remaining whole potato.
In a 1 1/2 or 2-quart microwave casserole, combine the potatoes, water, onion and salt. Microwave, covered, on High for 14 to 18 minutes or until potatoes are tender, stirring mixture twice.
Let vegetables stand, covered, while preparing sauce.

title: cream cheese ball
directions: Mix in a large bowl the cream cheese, salt, pineapple and 1/4 cup pecans.
Roll into a ball.
Roll ball in remaining pecans, until well coated, and chill 1 hour.
Serve with your favorite cracker; mine is Ritz.

title: m&m candies super cookies
directions: Chop 1 1/2 cups candies;
reserve remaining for decoration. Beat
together
margarine
and
sugars
until light and fluffy. Blend
in
eggs and salt.
Mix well, stirring chopped candies and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet. Bake
at
350° for 11 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Immediately place
several candies
into top of each hot cookie.
Cool on wire rack.

title: cracker jacks
directions: Mix together butter, corn syrup, sugar, salt and baking soda; soft boil 5 minutes.
Pour over popped corn and nuts.
Place in slow oven for about 45 minutes, stirring every 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: bit cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugars, and vanilla.
Add egg and beat.
Add flour, naking soda and salt.
Stir in nuts and bits.
Drop by spoonfuls on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake 8-10 minutes at 375°.

title: mom's stew
directions: Heat oven to 275°.
To a covered baking dish, add potatoes, carrots, celery, onion and stew meat (cut in cubes).
Add tomato soup and water; pour over meat and vegetables.
Add bay leaf. Bake 4 to 5 hours.

title: green rice
directions: Saute bell pepper, green onions and parsley flakes in oleo. Add chicken broth and water.
Place rice, salt and pepper in a baking dish.
Stir in other mixture.
Bake 50 minutes in covered dish at 350°.
Mix well after baking.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine everything in a kettle but the peanut butter.
Cook over medium heat, stirring often until thermometer reaches 234° to 240° or until mixture forms a soft ball when dropped in water. Remove from heat and add peanut butter, but do not stir.
Cool to 110° (lukewarm) before beating.

title: no bake cream puffs
directions: Blend cream cheese and sugar.
Add Cool Whip.
Drain crushed pineapple thoroughly and fold into mixture.
Cut cookies in half and spread cream mixture inside.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Cook eggplant until mushy; drain.
Add remaining ingredients, reserving 1/2 cup cheese, 1/2 cup crumbs and small amount of margarine.
Mix well.

title: crunchy beef casserole
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
Brown hamburger; add all remaining ingredients (except onion rings).
Pour 1/2 of hamburger/macaroni mixture in casserole dish; layer 1/2 of onion rings and then remainder of mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes (until it is hot and bubbly).
Top with remaining onions for last 5 minutes of cooking time.
If onions are put on earlier, they burn!

title: easy cheese ball
directions: Mix cheese and dressing together and shape into a ball.
Roll in chopped pecans.
Chill overnight.

title: sharon's loose fajitas
directions: In a large, non-stick skillet, cook the beef, onions, green and red peppers and garlic, over medium heat, about 5 minutes or until the beef is browned and the vegetables are tender, stirring frequently.
Stir in the chili powder and cumin and cook for 1 minute.
Add the salsa and tomatoes.
Bring to a gentle boil, then reduce the heat.
Simmer, uncovered, for 4 to 5 minutes or until the liquid reduces slightly.

title: crocked country chicken
directions: Brown chicken pieces, skin side up, under broiler.
Blot well. Combine with remaining ingredients in slow cooker.
Cover and cook on low for 7 to 10 hours.
Remove bay leaf before serving.

title: old-fashioned chocolate cake
directions: In small bowl, stir together cocoa and boiling water until smooth; set aside.
Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 2 (9 x 1 1/2-inch) round pans.
In large mixing bowl, cream shortening, sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, beating well. Combine flour, baking soda and salt; add alternately with buttermilk to creamed mixture.
Blend in cocoa mixture.
