title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Top with 2 cups of corn flakes and 1/2 cup margarine.
Bake 1 hour at 400°.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Cook the chicken and remove from bones.
Place chicken in casserole.
Mix soups with milk.
Pour over chicken.
Prepare stuffing mix as on package.
Spoon on top of the soup.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: rice and tuna fish casserole
directions: Brown onions in butter in a large pot until tender.
Add rice and water.
Cook until rice is done.
Then add rest of ingredients and let simmer for 2 minutes.
Stir frequently.

title: unmayo
directions: Blend, then add 2 tablespoons of lemon juice.

title: banana bread
directions: Lightly grease bottom only of loaf dish (9 x 5-inch).
Combine in medium mixing bowl flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt. Mix mashed banana and lemon juice.
Set aside.
Beat sugar and margarine in a large bowl until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Alternately stir in milk and dry ingredients.
Fold in walnuts and banana mixture.
Pour batter into loaf dish.
Microwave at Medium-high 8 to 10 minutes.
Microwave until no uncooked batter can be seen through bottom of dish.
Cool for 10 minutes.

title: bread pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients in a mixing bowl.
Pour in a greased 8 x 8-inch or 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: catfish green tomato pickles
directions: Mix all together. Bring to a boil or until tomatoes turn light green. Do not continue to boil. Gently stir a couple of times. Put into sterilized jars and seal. Makes about 9 quarts.

title: toasted chicken rounds
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients; mix well.
Trim crusts from bread.
Lightly butter each slice, then spread with about 1 tablespoon chicken mixture; sprinkle with paprika.
Roll and wrap in waxed paper and refrigerate.
When ready to serve, slice each roll crosswise into 4 or 5 slices.
Toast under broiler on each side.
Serve hot.
Makes 32 to 50.

title: pumpkin pie squares
directions: Combine flour, oatmeal, nuts, oleo and pudding mix.
Press into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Blend coconut, spice, pumpkin, milk and eggs.
Pour onto first layer.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: taco seasoning mix
directions: To make taco filling, brown ground beef; drain excess fat.
Add water, tomato paste and taco seasoning mix.
Simmer for 10 minutes. Makes enough filling for 8 to 10 tacos.

title: cheesy mexican casserole
directions: Mix all and heat in skillet until cheese begin to melt. Cover bottom of baking dish with tortilla chips. Pour mixture in dish and top with grated cheese. Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 400.

title: vegetable pilaf
directions: Combine 1 1/3 cups water and bouillon granules in a medium saucepan; bring to a boil and add rice.
Cover; reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes or until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed. Add mushrooms, carrots, 1/2 cup water, parsley, green onions and pepper to rice; stir well.
Cover and cook over low heat 5 minutes.
Transfer rice to a serving dish.
Sprinkle with toasted pecans.
Yield:
8 servings (about 82 calories per 1/2 cup serving).

title: deep dish pizza
directions: *Can add another 16-ounce can of chopped tomatoes if you like a lot of tomatoes.

title: spiced apple rings
directions: Core apples, but don't peel.
Cut into 1/2-inch thick rings. In skillet over medium heat, heat butter, brown sugar, cinnamon and ginger until butter melts.
Add apples.
Cook 3 to 5 minutes, until apples are golden and fork-tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pecan pralines
directions: Melt 1 cup sugar to caramelize.
Add warm milk and other 2 cups of sugar.
Cook to a soft boil stage.
Add vanilla, butter and pecans.
Beat and drop on waxed paper in desired sizes.

title: hettie's candy
directions: In a microwave-safe bowl melt Velveeta and margarine.
Whisk together well.
In a large mixing bowl, mix powdered sugar, cocoa and vanilla.
Add cheese mixture.
Add nuts.
Stir and mix well. Makes 7 pounds candy.
Keep cool.

title: quick spinach
directions: Fry bacon until brown, remove from skillet.
In drippings cook minced garlic about 30 seconds.
Add fresh spinach.
Cover and cook until spinach is wilted and tender.
Sprinkle bacon on spinach, season with salt and pepper.
Serves 4.

title: cranberry upside-down muffins
directions: Cut cranberries into halves. Divide evenly into 12 greased or nonstick coated 3-inch muffin pans. Spoon about 1 teaspoon of the butter into each.
Sprinkle evenly with brown sugar. In a mixing bowl, stir together flour, baking powder, granulated sugar, salt and raisins. In a smaller bowl, beat egg.
Mix in milk and remaining melted butter.
Add liquid mixture to flour mixture, stirring until dry ingredients are just moistened.

Spoon batter over cranberries in prepared muffin pans, dividing it evenly. Bake at 400° until golden brown, about 30 minutes. Let muffins stand in pan on a wire rack for a few minutes until bubbling stops.
Turn muffins out carefully and serve upside down.

title: spicy pineapple-zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add oil, sugar and vanilla continue beating until thick and foamy.
Stir in zucchini and drained pineapple. Combine flour, baking soda, salt, baking powder, cinnamon, nutmeg, walnuts and raisins.
Stir gently into zucchini mixture just until blended.
Divide batter into 2 greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool thoroughly.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: ham pinwheels
directions: Combine softened cream cheese with 1 heaping tablespoonful of mayonnaise and a dash of onion salt.
Take filling and spread 1/8-inch thickness on a slice of ham.
Roll up lengthwise.
Insert toothpicks to help hold roll.
Put in freezer for about 30 minutes, then remove from freezer and slice 1/4-inch slices.

title: dalarolimpa(swedish limpa bread)
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add syrup and eggs to yeast mixture.
Add unbleached flour and rye flour and knead until smooth and elastic.
Cover and let rise until double in size. Punch down and knead slightly.
Divide into two loaves.
(Can be placed on greased baking sheet or into two greased loaf pans.) Let rise again for 30 to 40 minutes.
Bake at 375° for about 35 minutes.

title: easy sweet pickles
directions: Drain juice from dill pickles.
Pour sugar over the pickles. Place in the refrigerator for 2 to 3 days.
Shake the jar and turn it upside-down and right side up, several times during the 2 to 3-day period. At the end of the "soaking period, " open, eat and enjoy!

title: kentucky spoon bread
directions: Melt margarine.
Beat in eggs.
Add creamed corn and whole corn.
Add Jiffy cornbread mix and sour cream.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: mince pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Mix all ingredients together.
Mound into pie pan lined with pastry crust.
Cover with top crust.
Flute to seal.
Vent top.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until crust is brown.

title: sour cream and chive potatoes
directions: Mix sour cream with milk in casserole dish.
Add butter, chives, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Add potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: k. f. c.
directions: Place all dry ingredients in bag.
Moisten chicken in water; place in bag and shake.

title: clam dip
directions: Mix all together and serve chilled with potato chips.

title: potatoes au gratin
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch greased casserole dish.
Add topping and bake in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: carrot cake #1
directions: Beat eggs and sugar until light.
Add oil and vanilla and beat. Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to sugar mixture; add pineapple, nuts and carrots.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes in a greased and floured tube pan.

title: sausage-cornmeal casserole
directions: Fry sausage over low heat and break apart with fork.
Cook from 8 to 10 minutes, until sausage is cooked and crumbled, but not browned.
While sausage cooks, measure cornmeal into large bowl.
Pour the boiling water over it and stir well.
Add drained sausage.
Beat eggs and add milk and salt.
Combine with the other mixture.
Add 2 tablespoons sausage fat and mix well.
Sprinkle baking powder over mixture and stir well.

title: white fruit cake
directions: Chop nuts and fruit.
Dredge with 1/4 cup flour.
Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add well beaten eggs and blend well.
Sift remaining flour and baking powder together.
Pour into eggs and butter mixture.
Add vanilla and lemon extract.
Add fruit and nuts.
Blend well with your hands.
Grease pan well, pour in batter and bake for 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Sift the flour, soda and salt together and set aside.
Work the shortening and butter together with a spoon until fluffy and creamy.
Add the sugar slowly, continuing to work until light.
Then add the egg yolk and beat until light and fluffy.
Add the flour mixture alternately with the buttermilk, beating well after each addition.
Stir in the vanilla and then gently fold in the stiffly beaten egg white.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls 3 inches apart on a greased cookie sheet. Flatten with a spatula to 1/2 inch thickness.
Bake in the preheated oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until done.
Makes 18 (3-inch) cookies.
Servings:

title: chess squares
directions: Mix cake mix, egg, oleo and vanilla and press into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat together powdered sugar, 2 eggs and cream cheese and pour into the pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until lightly brown.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: moma's potato salad
directions: Peel and dice potatoes into small, bite-sized pieces.
Boil potatoes in water flavored with beef bouillon.
Do not overcook. Drain and cool potatoes.
Add all other ingredients.
Mix together with mayonnaise.
Garnish with tomato and green pepper.

title: holiday cranberry jello
directions: Mix lemon jello and hot water until jello is dissolved.
Add cream cheese and mix, then add pineapple and pecans.
Pour in a jello mold and chill. Mix strawberry jello and hot water until jello is dissolved, then add cranberry sauce, pour over chilled mixture and continue to chill until set.

title: brenda's punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large gallon container.
Add enough water to make up the 1 gallon.
Use flavor of Kool-Aid which matches color scheme.

title: baked lasagna
directions: Brown onion and hamburger in 2 tablespoons of olive oil in skillet.
Drain and add 2 1/2 cups of water and 2 teaspoons minced parsley, 1/2 teaspoon of garlic salt, pinch of oregano, tomato paste and Worcestershire sauce.
Simmer for 25 minutes.
Boil 9 strips of lasagna noodles for 12 to 15 minutes.
Drain and pour 1 teaspoon of olive oil over it to keep from sticking.
Layer in baking dish alternately sauce and lasagna.
Put 1 bag of mild Cheddar cheese and 1 bag Mozzarella cheese, ending with sauce and 1 cup of Parmesan cheese sprinkled on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown beef with onion and chilies.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil and simmer about 45 minutes.

title: neiman-marcus cake
directions: Mix the first three ingredients.
Wet fingers; pat mixture into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cream the cream cheese, confectioners sugar and egg.
Spread on top of batter.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: chicken in wine
directions: Spray large nonstick skillet with nonstick cooking spray; add chicken parts and cook over medium heat until brown on both sides, 6 to 8 minutes.
Transfer into 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Set aside.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Cook and drain sausage.
Cook green peppers and onion in oil until tender.
Chop sliced potatoes into smaller pieces and put all ingredients in large pot to simmer for about 15 minutes.

title: easy garden vegetable pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease pie plate.
Cook broccoli in salted water 5 minutes; drain thoroughly.
Mix broccoli, onion, pepper and cheese in pie plate.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth with hand beater.
Pour over vegetables in pie plate.
Bake until golden brown, 35 to 40 minutes.
Refrigerate any remaining pie.

title: aunt lonna's pineapple cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add remaining shortening, vanilla and/or almond flavoring and pineapple juice. Beat for 3 minutes.
Then add eggs and water.
Beat 2 minutes longer.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes for 3 to 4 layers or 35 minutes if in a large flat pan.

title: ranch beans
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook in crock-pot, 3 to 4 hours or bake in oven at 400° for 1 hour uncovered.

title: mexican dip
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients.
Beginning with bean dip, then avocado mixture, layer remaining ingredients on platter.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: seaside candy roll
directions: Chop 1 1/2 cups of nuts finely and 1/2 cup coarsely.
Mix together margarine, syrup, flavoring and salt.
Add powdered sugar and mix thoroughly.
Knead well.
Add finely chopped nuts.
Shape mixture into 2 rolls 2 inches in diameter.
Brush with additional syrup and roll in coarsely chopped nuts.
Wrap roll in wax paper and then in foil.
Refrigerate.
Slice.

title: zucchini appetizers(little bites)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients and spread in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake about 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Cut into 2 x 1-inch pieces.
Serve warm.
Can be frozen.

title: party punch
directions: Chill all liquid ingredients prior to serving.
Mix ingredients and serve in large punch bowl.

title: wacky cake
directions: In one pan make 5 holes in the dry ingredients (sugar, flour and cocoa).
Put 6 tablespoons oil in center hole; 1 tablespoon vinegar in a hole; 1 teaspoon soda in a hole; 1 teaspoon vanilla in a hole; and 1/2 teaspoon salt in a hole.
Pour 1 cup water over all and stir.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pancake syrup
directions: Simmer first three ingredients for 5 to 10 minutes.
Cool slightly and add vanilla and maple flavoring.

title: chicken breast with papaya cilantro vinaigrette
directions: Heat olive oil and pour over all ingredients (except chicken breasts).
Mix all ingredients in a bowl.
Grill chicken breasts over medium heat until fork-tender and moist.
Garnish with sauce. Serve with your favorite grilled vegetables.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream the eggs, sugar and oil together thoroughly. Add soda, salt, cinnamon and flour. Add the apples, vanilla and pecans last. Bake for 1 hour at 320°.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Brown hamburger meat and set aside.
Mix next 7 ingredients. Pour 1/2 of batter in well-greased iron skillet.
Add cheese, onion, peppers and hamburger meat.
Pour in rest of batter.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until done.

title: diabetic chicken chili with black beans
directions: In Dutch oven, saute chicken, red peppers, onion and garlic in oil for 5 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink.
Add green chilies, chili powder, cumin and coriander.
Cook for 3 minutes. Stir in beans, tomatoes and broth or beer; bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 15 minutes, stirring often. Makes 10 servings.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Brown chicken in margarine.
Place in a 9 x 14-inch baking dish.
In the same frying pan with fat, add rice, chopped onion and pepper.
Saute until vegetables are limp.
Add drained mushrooms, soups, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix well and heat to simmering.
Pour mixture over chicken in a baking dish.
Cover and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: easy pancake syrup
directions: Heat water to boiling.
Lower heat.
Stir in brown sugar; continue to stir over low heat until sugar is completely dissolved.
Serve hot.
Makes 1 pint.

title: tuna bake
directions: Add 1/2 of the can of potato sticks, tuna, mushroom soup, mushrooms and milk.
Mix all together in casserole dish.
Sprinkle the rest of potato sticks on top and bake 1/2 hour or until bubbly in 350° oven.

title: savoy pepper steak
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper; toss meat into mixture.
Shake off excess.
Heat bacon fat; stir beef in about 4 minutes or until browned.
Simmer all together, covered, 45 to 60 minutes, or until meat is tender.
Serve with steamed rice.
Serves 6.

title: almond bark treats
directions: Melt almond bark in microwave. Mix in all other ingredients. Spoon onto tin foil. When dry store in air tight container.

title: fruit cake
directions: Mix and bake 1 hour at 250° in an angel food cake pan.

title: apple bread
directions: Mix all together and bake in greased bread tin at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Makes 1 loaf.
Freezes beautifully.

title: sugarless coffee cake
directions: Mix well.
Bake in a greased and floured layer cake pan in a preheated oven at 375°.

title: kibbles and bits
directions: Melt oleo, peanut butter and chocolate chips.
Mix with cereal and peanuts; stir until coated.
Put in paper bag with powdered sugar and shake until coated.
Let cool.

title: dilled cucumbers
directions: Place cucumber slices and onion slices in large bowl. In medium saucepan, combine sugar, vinegar, dill, and salt. Cook and stir over medium heat until sugar dissolves, cook slightly. Pour over cucumbers and onions. Cover and chill 4-24 hours.

title: russian tea
directions: Add 1 to 2 teaspoons of preceding mixture to 1 cup boiling water for a delicious cup of tea.
Makes good Christmas gifts sealed in jars.

title: applesauce
directions: Heat apples and water over medium heat to boiling.
Reduce heat; simmer, stirring occasionally, 5 to 10 minutes.
Stir in brown sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Heat to boiling.

title: golden stuffed potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes in jackets until done.
Cut them in half and scoop out cooked, cooled potato (save jackets for stuffing). Combine butter and cheese in heavy saucepan over low heat; stir until cheese melts.
Remove from heat and stir in sour cream, onions, salt and pepper.
Add cooled potatoes; stir.
Place mixture in potato jackets.
Place in pan and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cranberry orange relish
directions: Put the fresh berries, oranges (seeded and quartered) and 1/4 orange peel in food chopper or food processor; chop thoroughly. Add sugar.
Mix well and chill in refrigerator several hours before serving.
Makes approximately 1 quart.

title: hot dog relish
directions: Combine cucumbers, onion, celery, green pepper, salt and water.
Let set overnight.
Drain and add vinegar, mustard seed, celery seed and sugar.
Bring to a boil and cook slowly for 10 minutes.
Put in clean jars and seal.

title: mediterranean stuffed potatoes(using a basic marinara sauce)
directions: Scrub and pierce potatoes.
Bake in preheated hot oven at 400° for 45 to 50 minutes or until done.
Cook meat, onion, garlic, peppers and mushrooms in heavy skillet over medium heat until meat is no longer pink, stirring occasionally to break up meat.
Add Marinara Sauce, olives and spices.
Simmer for 10 to 15 minutes to blend flavors.
Split potatoes lengthwise and press ends together. Fluff centers.
Top each potato with a serving of meat sauce and top with yogurt.

title: greek chicken soup
directions: Place in a large soup pot 1 nice fat chicken (Perdue chicken makes very nice broth).
Cover with water; add salt.
Cook until the chicken is done.
Remove chicken from pot; set aside.
Add the soup macaroni of your choice (1 to 1 1/2 cups will probably be more than enough).
Cook pasta until tender.
Do not boil the broth; just let the macaroni cook slowly.
when done, remove from heat and let stand while you are beating the eggs, etc.
Separate the eggs, placing the whites in a medium to large bowl and yolks in a small dish.
Place the juice of 2 lemons in another small dish.

title: big batch chex party mix
directions: Combine margarine, seasoned salt and Worcestershire sauce in microwave-safe bowl.
Microwave until margarine is melted; stir well.

title: fantastic hot ham and cheese on bun
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt butter; add poppy seed and onion. Spread mixture on both sides of bun.
Put one slice cheese between 2 slices of ham on buns.
Wrap in aluminum foil (four buns in each bundle).
Do not stack.
Heat in oven on cookie sheets for 20 minutes.
Fantastic!

title: cheese krispies
directions: Cream margarine and cheese. Add flour. Add Rice Krispies and knead by hand. Make into balls, press with fork. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: pineapple nut cake
directions: Mix all together in mixing bowl.
Pour in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place in 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
Frost with following soft frosting.

title: potato salad
directions: Cook the first seven ingredients until thick.
Add butter and Miracle Whip.
Pour over potatoes which have been boiled with jackets on, peeled and diced.
Add celery, onion and boiled eggs.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Bake Jiffy mix as directed on box.
Let cool and crumble in bottom of buttered casserole dish.
Layer sliced onion on top of mix.
Combine sour cream, creamed corn and melted butter and pour on top.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: pound cake(cold oven)
directions: Cream together the sugar, salt, margarine and Crisco.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat well after each egg.
Add lemon and vanilla flavoring.
Add 2 cups sifted flour and 1 cup milk alternately, beginning and ending with flour.
Sift baking powder and 1 cup flour; add all at once.
Put batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Pan can be lined with wax paper; put in cold oven.
Bake for 1 3/4 hours at 325°.
Good plain, or you can use your favorite icing.

title: deluxe pecan pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Prepare pastry for 9-inch one-crust pie as directed on package except stir in chopped nuts before adding water.
In a small mixer bowl, beat eggs, sugar, salt, butter, syrup and cream. Stir in vanilla and pecans.
Pour into pastry lined pie pan. Bake 40 to 50 minutes or until filling is set and pastry is golden brown.
Cool. Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: snowball surprises
directions: In mixing bowl beat butter, sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Add flour and nuts, mix well.
Chill.
Remove foil from kisses.
Form each cookie into a ball by shaping 1 tablespoon of dough around a kiss, covering completely.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until set but not brown, about 12 minutes.
While still warm, sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Store in covered container.
Tastes better next day.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: baked fish fillets
directions: Marinate fish in wine and salt for 2 hours.
Drain.
Dip in crumbs.
Arrange side by side in greased shallow pan.

title: crab casserole
directions: Leave a little bread crumbs and cheese for the top.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: french bread open sandwiches
directions: Layer mushroom soup, tomato, chicken breast and cheese in this order on French bread. Place on a cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: garlic salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: monkey bread
directions: Butter a Bundt pan.
Tear biscuits in 4 pieces.
Mix sugar and cinnamon.
Roll biscuit pieces in the sugar-cinnamon mixture. Place in Bundt pan until half full.
Bake at 350°.
Bake until golden brown.
Dump on plate and pull apart.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In large bowl, combine filling ingredients; mix well and turn into shell.
Bake 15 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° and continue baking 35 to 40 minutes.

title: whole wheat pie crust
directions: Lightly stir oil and milk into sifted flour and salt.
Roll out.
Bake at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: creamy lemon pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium mixing bowl, beat egg yolks. Stir in sweetened condensed milk, lemon juice and food coloring if desired.
Pour into crust.
Bake 8 minutes.
Cool and chill thoroughly.
Top with whipped topping.
Garnish as desired.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat until smooth.

title: surprise bread
directions: Thaw and roll loaf of bread flat and long.
Saute meat and cook until it starts to brown.
Drain; add cheese and mix well. Put meat mixture in middle of bread and fold over bread and crimp down.
Brush top of bread with margarine.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350° or until it is as brown as you like.

title: west virginia corn bread
directions: Sift together flour, baking power, sugar and salt.
Add corn meal.
Add eggs, milk and shortening; beat until smooth, pour in greased pan.
Bake in 425° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: mom's oatmeal chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream first five ingredients.
Sift together; add flour, salt and soda.
Stir in oatmeal, nuts, chocolate chips and raisins. Drop by teaspoon on baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Combine flour, salt, pepper and paprika.
Roll each piece in flour until well coated.
Heat oil in oven to 400°, about 10 minutes.
Put chicken in hot oil.
Bake 30 minutes, uncovered; turn chicken and cook 30 more minutes.

title: broccoli melange
directions: Pour vegetable oil in skillet.
Cut garlic cloves into thin slices.
Add olive oil and garlic to skillet.
Saute until golden brown, stirring constantly with wooden spoon.
Remove garlic from skillet and discard.

title: egg custard
directions: Combine sugar, milk, butter, vanilla, nutmeg and eggs.
Grease pie plate and dust with flour for crust.
Pour mixture into pie plate and bake at 325° for about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: crock-pot corn
directions: Cook on low heat for 4 hours.
Stir occasionally.

title: pudding cake
directions: Mix cake as directed.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Mix softened cream cheese with 1 cup milk.
Mix pudding with 1 cup milk. Combine with cream cheese. Spread over cooled cake. Drain pineapple. Spread over pudding mixture. Spread Cool Whip over mixture. Top with chopped walnuts.

title: microwaved chicken breast
directions: On waxed paper, combine crushed potato chips, parsley, paprika, salt and onion powder.
Brush chicken with mayonnaise, then coat with chip mixture.
In a 12 x 8-inch baking dish, cook chicken covered with a paper towel on High in microwave 8 to 10 minutes or until done.
Rearrange chicken halfway through cooking time.
This can be made with flavored chips such as barbecue, Cheddar cheese or hot jalapeno, if daring.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Put strawberries in blender and puree.
Mix gelatin with boiling water. Stir in lemonade, cranberry juice and cold water. Put juice mixture and strawberry puree in punch bowl.
Slowly add ginger ale.
Makes 25 servings.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: To prepare pastry, in a medium bowl, mix together flour and salt.
Using a pastry blender or two knives, cut butter into flour until coarse crumbs form.
In a small bowl, beat together egg and water.
Add to the flour mixture; mix lightly until a soft dough forms.
Shape into a disk, wrap in plastic wrap, and chill for one hour.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Cook according to package directions.
Add about 2 tablespoons oil to water to prevent sticking.
Prepare filling and heat sauce through while shells are cooking.
When shells are cooked (don't overcook), drain shells.
Return to pan and add cool water to cover shells.
This helps to keep the shells intact while stuffing.

title: pretzels
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in a bowl.
Add honey, salt and flour; knead.
Roll into long "snakelike" pieces.
Shape in the form of a pretzel (folded arms in prayer).
Brush with beaten egg. Sprinkle with salt (coarse salt if available).
Bake for ten minutes at 425°.

title: quick tamale pie
directions: Mix all together and place in Dutch oven or heavy baking dish with tight fitting lid.
Place in oven at 250° for 5 hours. Equally as easy for the man of the house to prepare!

title: zucchini squash casserole
directions: Cook and drain squash.
Combine with green pepper, onion, rice, salt, pepper, milk, eggs and mayo.
Put in a greased casserole dish and bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Makes 4 servings.

title: squash rolls
directions: Combine squash, sugar, shortening and salt in scalded milk. Heat to lukewarm.
Combine yeast with water.
Add to first mixture.
Add flour and mix well.
Let rise until double.
Knead and shape into rolls.
Let rise.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chicken and rice dinner
directions: Dredge chicken pieces in flour.
In a skillet, heat oil on medium and brown chicken on all sides.
Meanwhile, combine rice, poultry seasoning, salt, pepper, milk and water.
Pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Top with chicken.
Cover tightly with foil and bake at 350° for 55 minutes or until rice and chicken are tender.
Sprinkle with parsley before serving. Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: double fudge cookies
directions: Let eggs and butter come to room temperature. In large mixing bowl, beat butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla until light and fluffy. Stir together flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt; add to butter mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Chill dough in freezer for at least 30 minutes.
Pat into cookie mounds and bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 7 to 9 minutes. Cool slightly and remove to wire rack.
Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: cheese tarts
directions: Cream the cream cheese.
Add sugar and vanilla; mix.
Add eggs, one at a time; mix.
Put in graham cracker mixture.
Or put vanilla wafer in cupcake wrapper; add cream cheese mixture.
Bake at 375° about 20 minutes.
Cool.
Add topping.

title: lip smacking grilled chicken
directions: Brush chicken with oil and sprinkle with seasoned salt.
Grill until done.

title: apple spice cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed.
Add apples.
Bake in 8 x 15-inch pan in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: ham and egg casserole
directions: Spread frozen bread with oleo; cut into cubes.
Combine with ham, cheese, salt and pepper.
Beat eggs until foamy; stir in milk. Add egg mixture to other ingredients, stirring well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Serve immediately.
This recipe is great for brunch.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Beat oil, eggs, water, sugar and pumpkin.
To mixture, add spice, flour, baking soda and salt.
When all blended, add raisins and nuts.
Bake until top of bread is dry or approximately 1 hour at 350°.

title: holiday butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cream butter thoroughly.
Add sugar gradually; continue beating until mixture is light and fluffy. Beat in egg and vanilla.
Sift together dry ingredients. Gradually add to creamed mixture; mix until thoroughly blended. Chill dough for ease in handling.
On lightly floured surface, roll dough to 1/8-inch thickness.
With floured cookie cutters, cut into desired shapes.
Using wide spatula, transfer to cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with granulated sugar.
Bake at 400° for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: texas corn stuffing
directions: Saute onion in melted butter.
Combine with crumbled cornbread and seasonings.
Use as stuffing for pork chops or use as stuffing for crown of franks.
Add 1/4 cup water if needed.

title: barbecue meatballs
directions: Combine ingredients and shape into small balls.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: mock lobster dip
directions: Boil soup, add melted cream cheese and gelatin softened in 1/2 c. cold water. Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients. Serve with crackers.

title: sausage balls
directions: In a large bowl put the ingredients and mix.
Roll into balls and bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Serves 10.

title: baked corn
directions: Melt butter in 2-quart saucepan.
Sprinkle in flour.
Gradually add milk and bring to boiling point.
Add corn, salt, pepper and sugar.
Heat thoroughly.
Remove from heat and add beaten eggs.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Combine and pour on top of drained mushrooms.
(You may triple for a larger quantity.)

title: vegetable lasagne(low cholesterol)
directions: Put noodles in boiling water one at a time.
Boil until tender, about 15 minutes.
Combine Ricotta cheese, spinach that has been squeezed dry, egg whites and parsley.
Add garlic to tomato sauce.
Remove noodles from water; rinse with cold water and pat dry.

title: tasty potatoes
directions: Mix ingredients, then roll potatoes into mixture.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.
Stir after 1/2 baking time.

title: chipped beef cheese ball
directions: Cut beef into small pieces.
Dice green onions.
Add to cream cheese with the Accent and Worcestershire; mix well.
Oil hands before shaping into a ball.

title: canyon casserole
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 8 inch square glass baking dish or shallow 2 quart casserole dish.
Brown meat in large skillet over med. high heat until thoroughly cooked, stirring often.
Drain and add tomatoes, corn, water and taco seasoning mix; mix well.
Bring to a boil, stirring occasionally.
Pour into greased dish.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Mix together ingredients.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt 2 cups chocolate chips with 2 tablespoons Crisco for 2 minutes in microwave.
Spread over peanut butter mixture and chill.

title: salsa de tomatillo
directions: Boil jalapenos, tomatoes and tomatillos (green tomatoes) until tender.
Drain.
Add ingredients to blender plus the cilantro, salt, pepper and garlic.
Pulse blend 3 to 4 times.
This is a kind of chunky salsa.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Crumble cornbread and mix with bread stuffing in a large mixing bowl. Saute onions, celery, garlic and green onions in melted butter. Add to bread stuffing mixture. Gradually add stock, mixing well. Dressing should be moist enough not to be dry after baking. Stir in parsley, seasonings and giblets. Pour into 9 x 13-inch casserole and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Yield: 12 servings.

title: beer cheese party dip
directions: Cut out the center of the round rye.
Tear the center piece into medium-size pieces for dipping.
In a blender, place remaining ingredients excluding the beer.
In a saucepan, bring beer to a boil and remove from the stove.
Add beer to the blender and mix until smooth.
Pour into round rye and serve.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Chop eggs and crush crackers into bottom of buttered casserole.
Alternate layers of crumbs, cheese, eggs, asparagus and mushroom soup.
Dot with butter after all are used.
Add milk and asparagus juice.
Sprinkle with extra crackers on top.
Bake at 450° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients and simmer while you prepare noodles.
Mix noodles and sauce and place in casserole with one or a mixture of following toppings:
poppy seed, Parmesan cheese, toasted sesame seed or sunflower seeds.
Bake for 15 minutes in 350° oven.
Good with French bread and tossed salad.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Cook asparagus as directed on package until barely tender and drain. In large skillet, cook onion in butter until tender (not brown).
Stir in flour.
Add milk and cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Mix in salt, pepper, eggs and asparagus.
Turn into a two-quart casserole.
Top with cheese and bread crumbs. Bake in 350° oven until hot and bubbly, about 30 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream margarine, shortening and sugar.
Add beaten egg yolks. Mix flour, soda, coconut and nuts; stir well.
Add to first 3 ingredients the buttermilk and flour mixture in 3 parts.
Last, add well beaten egg whites.
Make 3 layers.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: cherry cream pie(no baking necessary)
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients until well blended.
Mash cherries and stir into cream cheese mixture.
Whip cream and powdered sugar until soft peaks form.
Fold into cream cheese mixture.
Turn into pie crust and refrigerate.
Garnish with sliced cherries on top. Serves 8.

title: rave reviews coconut cake
directions: Blend cake mix, pudding mix, water, eggs and oil in a large mixing bowl.
Beat at medium speed with mixer for 4 minutes. Stir in coconut and nuts.
Pour into 3 greased and floured 9-inch pans. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool in pans 15 minutes. Remove and cool on rack. Fill and top with Coconut-Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: chocolate coated mints
directions: Stir margarine, syrup and 1/2 of the sugar over low heat until bubbly.
Quickly stir in the rest of the sugar and flavoring. Stir until mix holds shape, just a few minutes.
Spoon out by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Cool for 30 minutes or longer.

title: spinach dip (for vegetables)
directions: *Squeeze as much water out as possible when using frozen spinach.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars until light; beat in eggs and vanilla.
Combine flour, soda, and oatmeal; add to creamed mixture and beat until just combined.
Place tablespoons of dough on lightly greased cookie sheets and bake at 350° until light brown, about 12 minutes.

title: chili con queso
directions: Brown meat; add onion and cook until tender.
Add remaining ingredients, cutting cheese into small pieces.
Stir until cheese is well blended and add Worcestershire.
Transfer to fondue pot and serve with corn chips.

title: ham salad
directions: Mix well and spread.

title: ladylocks (small creme rolls)
directions: You will need 2 dozen round clothespins covered in foil.

title: prune cake
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and oil, then add dry ingredients and milk. Last add prunes and nuts.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix soup, sour cream, onions and cheese. Then stir in corn and green beans. Crush crackers and put on top. Pour melted butter over crackers. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: carrot-apple-raisin bars
directions: In blender, combine raisins, honey, egg whites and water. Process until pureed.
Transfer pureed mixture to medium size bowl and add carrot.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Steam	cabbage
over
boiling	water
until
softened. Remove and
trim leaves.	Combine next 6 ingredients in bowl, mixing well.
Shape
into	2-inch	balls.	Place
on
cabbage leaves, rolling
to enclose filling. Spread sauerkraut in 9 x 9-inch baking
dish.
Place
cabbage
rolls seam side down on sauerkraut. Cover
with
tomatoes;
place
bay leaves on top. Bake, covered, at 250° for
to 3 hours or to desired degree of doneness.

title: barbecue sauce for leftover meat
directions: Combine ingredients; simmer 5 minutes.
Mix in left over meat or chicken; simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Enough sauce for 1/2 pound meat.

title: apple crisp
directions: Put apples in bowl.
Add salt, lemon juice and 1 quart water. Sprinkle 1 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Add 3/4 cup water, then mix.
Combine remaining sugar, flour and butter.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: sour cream noodles
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients in bowl; mix well.
Add noodles and mix.
Spoon into greased casserole.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: diabetic french dressing
directions: Mix together all ingredients and shake well.
A blender may be used.
Refrigerate before using.
Makes three cups.

title: pear pie
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Cook and stir on low heat until sauce thickens.
Pour into pie shells and dot with margarine. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: crumb cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a square 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan. Mix flour, salt, sugar and baking powder in large bowl.
Add oil. Mix well with fork.
Remove 1 1/2 cups of mixture and put into a medium size bowl.
To the medium bowl, add egg and milk.
Mix well with spoon.
Place into baking pan.
Mix together 2 teaspoons sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon in a small bowl.
Mix with remaining dry ingredients in large bowl.
Sprinkle evenly over top of batter in pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 9 to 12 servings.

title: mexican pinwheels
directions: Combine sour cream and cream cheese; blend well.
Stir in chilies, onions and jalapenos.
Season with salt and pepper.
Cook the tortillas according to package.
Spread cream cheese mixture on the tortillas; stack in layers.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours. (Wrap in plastic wrap.)
Cut into wedges.
Serve with picante sauce.

title: tijuana casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; drain grease.
Add onion and saute.
In a bowl, mix and set aside, soup and tomatoes.
Grease a large (or 2 small) casserole dishes; put a layer of corn tortillas.
Add a layer of meat, beans and cheese.
(Top layer should always be cheese.)
Pour soup and tomato mixture over layers.
Top with sliced cheese about 10 minutes before done, so it will melt.
Bake at 350° approximately 1 hour until top is bubbling and brown.

title: crispy peanut butterscotch fudge squares
directions: Coat 13X9 inch baking pan and rubber spatula with non-stick cooking spray. Melt margarine over low heat in medium, heavy duty saucepan. Add marshmallows and peanut butter; stir until melted. Remove from heat. Add cereal; stir until coated. Press into bottom of prepared pan using prepared spatula.

title: banana pudding
directions: Cream egg yolks and sugar.
Add salt, flour and milk.
Cook over medium heat until thickened.
Add vanilla.
Pour into baking dish alternately with bananas and wafers.
Beat egg whites with 3 tablespoons sugar until stiff.
Cover pudding and brown in oven. Serves 6 to 8.

title: white wine sauce
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Stir in flour until smooth.
Add milk.
Cook, stirring, until thick.
Remove from heat.
Add salt, white pepper, mushrooms and wine.
Makes 2 1/2 cups sauce.

title: dirt road granny's pound cake
directions: Cream the Crisco, sugar, butter, then add eggs, milk and vanilla. Add flour and baking powder. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: bunco hash
directions: Brown first 5 ingredients; add small amount of water, corn (drained) and cooked rice.
Simmer with lid for about 30 minutes on low heat.

title: sour cream enchiladas
directions: Heat first three items; do not boil.
Mix filling:
onions, beans and olives.
Dip tortillas in heated sauce one at a time. Spoon approximately 1/4 cup filling into tortilla.
Add approximately 1/4 cup of each grated cheese and 1 tablespoon of sour cream.
Fold tortilla and hold closed with toothpick.
Repeat until casserole dish is filled.
Pour any remaining sauce on top and sprinkle remaining cheese over entire casserole.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: great cauliflower salad
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well and chill.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook your pasta; let drain and cool.
Mix Good Seasons according to package directions.
Add the peppercorn Ranch and celery seed; mix well.
Pour over your pasta; add olives and stir. Cool before serving.
Can add tomatoes if preferred.

title: corn pudding
directions: Turn on oven to 375°.
First grease baking dish well with margarine.
Drain water from 2 cans of whole corn and pour into a bowl.
Add cream-style corn, 1 cup milk, butter or margarine (melted), sugar and salt.
Beat eggs with fork and pour into other ingredients stirring well.
Add cornstarch to second cup of milk and stir well until cornstarch is completely dissolved and add to mixture.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs; mix well.
Fold in sour cream.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt; add to mixture. Mix well.
Add vanilla.
Pour into 8 x 12-inch pan.
Top with nuts, 1/4 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Boil chicken tender.
Cut in bite-size pieces.
Cook spaghetti in broth (do not drain).
Saute onion, pepper and celery in 1/2 stick of butter until tender.
Mix all ingredients together. Place in 9 x 13 x 2-inch Pyrex dish.
Top with grated cheese. Bake at 350° until cheese is melted and casserole bubbly.

title: hot slaw and dressing
directions: Mix shredded cabbage, sliced olives and celery seed.
Let stand.
Mix all other ingredients in saucepan.
Heat but do not boil.
Pour over cabbage mixture.
Serve immediately.

title: salsa salisbury steak
directions: Mix beef, onion, chili powder and garlic salt. Shape mixture into 4 oblong patties. Spray 12 inch nonstick skillet with nonstick cooking spray; heat over medium high heat. Cook patties in skillet 3 to 5 minutes, turning once, until brown; drain. Stir in tomatoes; reduce heat to low. Cover and simmer about 10 minutes, stirring tomatoes occasionally and turning patties once, until patties are no longer pink in center and juice is clear. This has 7 grams carbohydrates.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Roll in ball and cover with nuts.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: Pat ham slices between paper towels to dry. Mix other ingredients together to spreadable consistency. Spread mixture on ham slices. Roll and stick with 5 toothpicks. Refrigerate overnight and slice between toothpicks. Serve attractively.

title: ham and cheese breakfast
directions: Saute in butter diced onions and green pepper.
Whip eggs with milk; put in pan.
Season with Lawry's seasoned salt, pinch of pepper (or lemon pepper) and fresh tomato (cubed).
Heat.
Add cream cheese, cubed.
Put on plate.
Crumble bacon on top.

title: sandies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add water and vanilla and mix well. Blend in flour and nuts.
Chill about 2 hours.
Shape into balls or fingers.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 325° for 20 minutes. Remove from pan, cool and roll in sugar.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: triple chocolate cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 13 x 9-inch pan; stir with a fork until blended.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cool in pan and cut into squares.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Enjoy.

title: tomato juice cocktail
directions: Wash
tomatoes
thoroughly.
Remove
blemishes and stem ends, cut into quarters.
Combine tomatoes, onion, bay leaves, cloves, cayenne
pepper
and
water
in large Dutch oven. Cook over low heat about 1 hour.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Fry onions in margarine; melt cheese in soup, milk and water. Add rest of ingredients and mix.
Bake in casserole at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: crunch chip cookies
directions: Beat butter and sugars until creamy and fluffy.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Gradually add sifted dry ingredients; mix well. Stir in oats, chocolate chips and noodles.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Drain and chop artichokes and mix with the rest of the ingredients.
Bake until bubbly or microwave for 2 minutes.
Serve warm with chips or the cracker of your choice.

title: toll house cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix 6 to 8 minutes.
Bake in a greased Bundt pan 60 minutes at 350°.

title: raspberry pinwheels
directions: In a large mixer bowl at medium speed, beat butter or margarine and cream cheese until light and fluffy.
Beat in 1/2 cup sugar, vanilla and salt.
At low speed, gradually beat in flour until mixture forms a ball.
Divide dough into two portions. Cover and chill for 30 minutes or until firm enough to handle.

title: 24 hour vegetable salad
directions: Spread romaine lettuce on bottom of large salad bowl. Sprinkle salt, pepper and sugar.
Top with 1 cup cheese.
Arrange sliced eggs on top of cheese.
Make layers of 1/2 bacon and all of the peas.
Spoon iceberg lettuce over all.
Spoon mayonnaise on top; spread to cover top of salad.
Garnish with remaining bacon, cheese and green onions.
Cover and refrigerate for 24 hours. Toss just before serving.

title: chili con queso
directions: Place cubed cheese and Ro-Tel tomatoes in microwave oven safe dish.
Cook 5 minutes. Stir.
Cook until smooth.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Excellent on vegetables.

title: club sandwiches
directions: Spread toast with salad dressing.
Place 2 slices turkey, 1 slice tomato, 2 slices bacon and 2 lettuce leaves on each of 4 slices of toast.
Cover with remaining toast.
Cut diagonally into fourths.
Yields 4 servings.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream the shortening and both types of sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix well.
In a separate bowl, combine flour, oats, soda, baking powder and salt.
Blend dry ingredients into creamed mixture.
Add nuts and chocolate chips. Mix.
Drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake until brown.

title: 10 minute chocolate pie
directions: Blend together sugar, cocoa, flour and salt.
Mix together egg yolks in milk and vanilla.
Add hot water to dry ingredients, mixing well, then add egg yolk mixture.
Cook 10 minutes or until mixture thickens, stirring constantly.
Top with egg white meringue or Cool Whip.

title: tuna burger
directions: Combine all ingredients and spoon onto 6 hamburger buns. Brush top of buns with butter.
Bake on cookie sheet at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: veggie cornbread
directions: Melt margarine in pan. Mix other ingredients in a bowl and pour batter into pan. Bake at 400° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: apple kuchen
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut margarine in cake mix until creamy. Mix in coconut.
Pat mixture lightly into ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan, building sides up.
Bake 10 minutes.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream together sugar, butter and eggs.
In a separate bowl mix cocoa and red food coloring.
Mix these into a paste and then add vanilla, salt, buttermilk or milk and vinegar mixture.
Then alternate between flour and buttermilk mixture.
Pour into other bowl.
Then add baking soda and fold in vinegar.
Do not beat after added.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes in a greased pan.

title: old faithful
directions: Brown the meat in the oil.
While browning, spray a baking dish with nonstick spray.
Put the rice in the bottom.
Over this, lay the sliced vegetables.
Next, layer the meat.
Over the meat you can place some more of the sliced vegetables.
Mix the soup with 1 can of water and pour over the meat and vegetables.
Cover and let it fend for itself in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: cheesy potato soup
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine first 5 ingredients and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Blend in potato by mashing it slightly against the side of pan with a fork.
In a separate bowl, combine 1/4 cup evaporated skim milk with cornstarch until smooth and lump-free.
Stir cornstarch mixture and remaining evaporated milk into broth mixture, cooking and stirring until thick and bubbly. Cook and stir 1 minute more, then gradually add cheeses, stirring until melted.
Pour soup into four mugs or bowls and serve piping hot.

title: skinny shake
directions: In a blender, blend at medium speed until smooth and the consistency of ice cream.
Makes 3 servings.
Only 80 calories per serving.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Line casserole dish with 6 shells.
Brown hamburger and onion. Mix all other ingredients.
Break remaining shells in mix.
Pour over shells and top with cheese.

title: lemon lush
directions: Layer One:
Mix flour, margarine and pecans or almonds.
Mix like pie dough.
Spread in 9 x 11-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream the sugar and butter.
Add eggs; mix well. Add bananas, flour and baking soda to mixture and fold in the nuts.
Grease pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: schnitz und knepp
directions: Quarter 2 washed, unpared apples and core them.
Thinly slice each quarter.
In large, hot skillet, brown ham about 2 minutes per side.
Remove to cutting board.
Add apples and apple juice to skillet; simmer, covered, 5 minutes.
Cut ham into 1 1/2-inch squares.
Prepare 1 cup Bisquick mix as label directs for dumplings, using 1/2 cup milk.
Stir ham into apple mixture.
Drop dough by heaping tablespoonfuls on top.
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup brown sugar.
Cover and cook over medium heat for 10 minutes, or until dumplings are cooked through.

title: easy cheese cake
directions: To prepare crust:
Mix first 3 ingredients and press into pan. To prepare filling, mix eggs, sugar, vanilla and cream cheese until completely smooth.
Mix sour cream and sugar with vanilla and add to the batter.
Bake all ingredients together in a preheated oven for 30 minutes at 375°.
Cool thoroughly before serving.
(Tastes better the second day.)

title: yeast dough for cinnamon rolls or hamburger buns
directions: Mix yeast in warm water with 1/4 cup plus 1 teaspoon sugar. Let foam up.
Mix shortening, rest of sugar, salt and eggs; add to first mix along with flour.
Knead until smooth on floured surface.
Turn in oiled bowl to coat with oil.
Cover and let rise.
May be baked or stored in refrigerator.
Will keep for 4 to 5 days.

title: old-fashioned oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift flour, soda, salt and cinnamon in a large mixing bowl. Add the rest of the ingredients.
Beat on medium speed about 2 minutes.
Add raisins or chopped dates and nuts.
Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for about 12 minutes.

title: apple pancakes(makes 12 pancakes)
directions: Combine egg, milk and apple.
Stir into dry ingredients.
Stir in melted butter.
Bake on a hot griddle.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Prepare and bake cake mix in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan using package directions.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water in bowl. Cool.
Add strawberries.
Mix well.
Pierce holes in cake with fork.
Pour gelatin mixture over warm cake. Cool completely. Prepare pudding mix with milk using package directions.
Spread over cake. Top with whipped topping.

title: pralines
directions: Let come to good boil, then add 4 cups of pecans. Cook slowly to soft-ball. Take off stove; add 1 tablespoon vanilla.
Beat until creamy and drop into patties.

title: avocado salad
directions: Peel the avocado and cut in cubes. Sprinkle with lemon juice. Mix jello in boiling water. Cool. Add pineapple and mayonnaise. Let stand until it starts to set. Add avocado and fold in Dream Whip made as directed. Add nuts.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix together.
Makes 2 cups dry mix or enough for 6 quarts of tea.

title: oreo cookie freeze
directions: Crush Oreo cookies in zip lock bag or food processor.
Mix with margarine and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Freeze 1 hour. Soften ice cream and spread on top of cookies.
Freeze 1 hour. Melt jar of hot fudge, pour over ice cream.
Freeze 1 hour. Spread cool whip over chocolate and top with pecans.
Freeze 1 hour or more.
Keep frozen until ready to serve.

title: pan-fried vegetables
directions: Dip slices in coating.
Heat a thin layer of oil in pan.
Add slices.
Brown on both sides.

title: pineapple cheesecake pie
directions: Combine undrained pineapple, 1/3 c. sugar and cornstarch in sauce pan; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thick and clear; cool.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Layer pan with crackers and cheese.
Add sliced boiled eggs and asparagus.
Pour soup on top.
Top with more crackers and cheese.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 10.

title: no bake chocolate peanut butter candy
directions: Melt chocolate chips.
Mix with peanut butter and corn flakes. Drop by teaspoon size balls onto wax paper.
Refrigerate until ready to eat.

title: june's spinach souffle
directions: Cook spinach; drain well.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour thoroughly.
Sprinkle 1/2 sugar/flour mix on bottom of pie shell.
Add rhubarb; sprinkle the rest of sugar/flour mix over rhubarb.
Add 1/2 pint of cream.
Bake at 400° for approximately 45 to 50 minutes or until crust is brown. Pie will thicken as it cools.

title: vanilla cream sauce
directions: Combine sugar and cornstarch in a saucepan, add milk.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thick.
Beat a small amount into egg yolk, stir into hot mixture.
Cook and stir 1 minute.
Add vanilla and cool.
Whip cream and fold into cooled pudding.

title: fudge pecan pie
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, flour, salt, corn syrup, eggs, melted butter and vanilla in large mixer bowl; beat 30 seconds on medium speed; do not overbeat.
Stir in chopped pecans.
Pour into unbaked pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes. Immediately arrange pecan halves on top.
Cool.
(For fullest flavor, cover and let stand one day before serving.)

title: cream of celery soup
directions: Cook together vegetables and broth until the vegetables are soft.
Rub through a sieve, without draining, or whirl in an electric blender.
Add 1 1/2 cups cream or top milk.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Heat slowly.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix above ingredients in sauce pan.
Boil for 3 minutes and pour over cake.

title: spicy beef and rice
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and garlic in a Dutch oven.
Add next 6 ingredients.
Cover.
Reduce heat.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Serve over hot cooked rice.
Serves 8.

title: meat loaf
directions: Saute onions and green peppers in butter.
Stir in chili sauce.
Combine 1/2 cup of this mixture with beef, bread crumbs, egg, salt and pepper.
Form into a loaf in 8 x 4 x 11-inch shallow baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: sundae dessert
directions: Spread over crushed cookie mixture and freeze. Then spread on chilled chocolate sauce.

title: quick and easy coffeecake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Melt butter in small saucepan.
Coat bottom and sides of 8 x 8-inch pan with 2 tablespoons of melted butter and sprinkle pan with 3 tablespoons of nuts.
Add remaining nuts, brown sugar and water to butter remaining in saucepan; heat to a boil, stirring frequently.

title: salad dressing cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients with salad dressing, vanilla and soda. Add powdered sugar icing.

title: tanglewood pie
directions: Mix the Cool Whip, pineapple, Eagle Brand and lemon.
Pour in crusts.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Refrigerate at all times.

title: norwegian apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Beat egg, sugar, vanilla, salt and baking powder together until smooth and fluffy.
Beat in flour until smooth and well blended.
Stir in walnuts and apples.
Turn into a lightly greased 8-inch pie plate and bake 30 minutes.
Pie will puff up as it cooks, then collapse as it cools.
Serve topped with whipped dessert topping or ice milk.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Preheat
oven
to
Grease
well	and flour three 9-inch pans.
Sift flour with baking soda and salt.
In small bowl, combine chopped apples, nuts and lemon peel.

title: blueberry sour cream muffins
directions: In a large mixing bowl, mix together flour, baking powder, soda and salt, mixing well.
In another medium bowl, beat oleo, eggs and sugar, beating well, then add sour cream and vanilla. Add blueberries to flour mixture, stirring good.
Then add the batter, mixing just until all the flour is covered.
Have muffin pan ready with baking cups; fill 2/3 full.
Cook at 350° for 25 minutes or until brown.
This is a good cupcake recipe.

title: wild plum muffins
directions: Mix
all
ingredients together.
Bake in preheated 325° oven for 15 minutes.
May freeze for later use.	Use miniature muffin tin.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients well.
Place in large casserole dish. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and butter.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cook 1 bag chopped broccoli.
Drain and mix.
Top with bread crumbs and shredded cheese.
Cook in oven at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: dijon shrimp
directions: In large skillet over medium-high heat, cook and stir shrimp and garlic in margarine until just pink.
Blend in next 3 ingredients.
Serve over rice.
Serves 4.

title: holiday cranberry souffle
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan combine berries, sugar and water.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Drain juice from cranberry mixture, saving berries and juice.
Reheat juice to boiling.
Stir in gelatin until dissolved.
Add fruit juices.
Chill gelatin until consistency of egg whites.
Blend in 1/2 of the drained cranberries.

title: creamy peach jello salad
directions: Heat pineapple in saucepan and add jello.
Stir in buttermilk. Pour into medium size bowl and refrigerate for 1 hour.
Fold in Cool Whip and pour into serving dish.
Refrigerate for another hour before serving.

title: beef and barley dinner
directions: In large skillet, brown ground beef, green pepper, onion and garlic.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil and reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 50 to 60 minutes or until barley is tender.
Stir occasionally.
When serving, put sour cream on top, if desired.

title: college cookies
directions: Combine all 3 ingredients.
Roll into balls.
Place onto cookie sheet.
Place onto cookie sheet.
Mash with fork.
Bake at 350° for about 7 minutes.

title: lemon chess pie 2
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cornmeal.
Add eggs, then other ingredients.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into two uncooked pie shells.
Bake 45 minutes in 375° oven.

title: sweet barbecue sauce
directions: Mix and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: jiffy dessert
directions: Heat fruit in a 2-quart saucepan until hot.
Mix sugar and cornstarch together and add to fruit.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Mix Jiffy cake mix according to package directions.

title: maui style ribs
directions: Combine soy sauce, sugar, sweet cooking rice wine, garlic and ginger.
Marinate 24 hours.
Best if barbecued.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in a blender.
Blend just until mixed, about 3 seconds.
Add nuts for another second if not already chopped fine enough.
Pour into pie shell and bake for 45 minutes at 350° or until filling is puffed and crust is brown.

title: no fuss chicken
directions: In a small bowl, combine flour, sage, basil and seasoned salt. Coat chicken.
Reserve remaining flour mixture.
In a large skillet, melt butter.
Brown chicken on all sides.
Transfer chicken to slow cooker.
Add 1/4 cup reserved flour mixture to the skillet (discarding the rest).
Stir until smooth.
When mixture begins to bubble.
Stir in chicken broth and bring to boil.
Boil 1 minute.
Pour over chicken.
Cover and cook on high for 2 to 2 1/2 hours or until chicken juices run clear.
Makes 4 servings.

title: potatoes and carrots au gratin
directions: In a greased 2-quart casserole, place potatoes, carrots, green pepper and onion.
Combine half the cheese and remaining ingredients.
Pour over vegetables; gently toss.
Bake at 350° covered 35 to 40 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Top with remaining cheese; bake uncovered 10 to 15 minutes more.
Yields 6 servings.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Mix beef, onion, bread, milk, egg, parsley, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Shape in 1-inch balls and brown in shortening.
Heat chili sauce and grape jelly until melted.
Add meatballs and simmer for 30 minutes.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: congri
directions: Sort through beans; discard any discolored ones.
Soak beans overnight in water to cover.
Drain beans.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Melt butter; pour in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with hash browns, packed down.
Mix remaining ingredients and cover hash browns. Cover with foil; refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Saute celery and onion in oil or butter.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 15 minutes.	Serve on hamburg rolls.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender.
Combine all other ingredients except cheese.
Add broccoli, mix well.
Pour into casserole.
Top with cheese.
Mix 1/2 cup melted butter with 1/2 package herb stuffing.
Sprinkle over cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: old fashioned beef stew
directions: Roll meat in flour seasoned with salt and pepper. Brown thoroughly in hot oil. Cover with hot water, simmer 2 hours, adding water if necessary. Add remaining ingredients cook until vegetables are tender, about 30 min. If desired thicken liquid for gravy.
This recipe gets better every time it is reheated. 8 servings.

title: herbed vinegar
directions: Add additional parsley, peppers, cloves of garlic and lemon after 2 weeks.

title: cream puff in a pan
directions: Bring water and butter to a boil.
Add the flour and beat in eggs, one at a time.
Mixture will be very gooey.
Spread into greased jelly roll pan (a cookie sheet with sides will work just as well).
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.
While it is baking, it will get all puffy and sort of distorted.
Let cool.
Beat together pudding, milk and cream cheese.
Spread over cooled crust.
Spread Cool Whip over pudding mixture.
Drizzle with chocolate syrup. Note:
If using hot fudge sauce, which is much thicker than chocolate syrup, you may have to put it in a squirt bottle or an icing bag to drizzle it over the Cool Whip.
It's a little more work, but it's worth the extra bother.

title: cornflake pecan cookies
directions: Cream butter with sugar.
Add beaten egg whites with a pinch of salt.
Add pecans, vanilla and cornflakes last.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on a cookie sheet.
Bake in a very slow oven for 1 hour.
Watch carefully.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Soak poppy seed in pineapple juice for 1 hour.
Combine poppy seed juice, cake mix, pudding, eggs, oil and almond extract.
Mix well.
Grease Bundt pan with margarine and sprinkle with sugar. Bake 1 hour at 350° or until done.

title: shrimp cocktail dip
directions: Spread cream cheese on platter.
Mix together in small bowl, shrimp, clams and cocktail sauce.
Spread over cream cheese. Serve with crackers.

title: baked potato soup
directions: Bake 6 potatoes.
Dice into bite size pieces (with the skins on).
Saute the chopped onion in butter.
Stir the potatoes and onions together.
Add enough milk to cover the potatoes.
Salt, pepper and celery salt added to taste.
Slightly mash the potatoes.
When the milk begins to boil, add the diced cheese and stir until the cheese melts.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: dump cake
directions: Put layer of pineapple in pan, then layer pie filling, then layer of cake mix.
Cover layer of cake mix with slices of oleo. Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: five cup salad
directions: Gently mix all ingredients together.
Wait at least 2 hours before serving.
Best if made one day before serving.

title: squash pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, eggs, flavoring, butter and salt.
Mix well. Stir in squash.
Pour into 2 pie shells.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: low-fat vegetable dip
directions: Mix together, then chill. Serve with carrots, celery, etc.

title: brussels sprouts with walnuts
directions: Remove loose leaves and trim ends from sprouts.
Add to lightly salted boiling water and cook covered for 8 to 10 minutes or until they are tender but still bright green; drain and rinse with cold water.

title: never fail dumplings(serves 6)
directions: Sift flour with baking powder and salt; cut in shortening. Add enough milk to make a drop batter.
Drop by spoonfuls into boiling stock.
Cover tightly and cook for 10 minutes.
Serve at once.

title: extra-chunky tomato sauce
directions: Saute onion and pepper in oil until tender.
Add sauce; simmer (turn on lowest heat for at least 15 minutes).
Turn off heat; add sliced mushrooms.
Wait 5 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Break bread into pieces in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Crumble sausage, brown and drain.
Mix eggs, milk, salt and mustard.
Add sausage.
Pour mixture over bread.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mash squash; add other ingredients and mix well.
Pour into greased 1-quart casserole.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: blue ribbon barbecue beans
directions: Brown sausage and bacon in a large skillet.
Add onion and green pepper.
Cook until tender.
Drain.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Heat for approximately 20 minutes.
(You'll win the Blue Ribbon every time!)

title: sweet pastry shells
directions: Sift the flour into a mixing bowl and rub in the butter.
Add the egg yolk and enough water to bind to a firm dough.
Roll out thinly and stamp out 2-inch circles with a fluted pastry cutter. Press into tiny patty pans and chill for 30 minutes.
Preheat the oven to 400°.
Fill each pastry case with a crumpled piece of aluminum foil and bake for 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove the foil halfway through baking to allow the pastry shells to dry out and become crisp and golden brown.

title: cocoa meringue pie
directions: Cook and stir these ingredients over low heat until the mixture
thickens
and boils.
Place it over boiling water and cook until mixture is smooth and thick.
Cool and fill the pie shell.
Cover it with a meringue.

title: salsa
directions: If using whole tomatoes,
pour	tomatoes
into	a large mixing bowl.
Crush
them	or
use the blender.
Add remaining ingredients and serve with tortilla chips.	Making this ahead, will give the best flavor.

title: "will's" hamburgers
directions: Mix ingredients.
Form into 8 thick or 12 medium thick patties. Preheat frypan; melt 1 tablespoon cooking oil in pan.
Fry patties, turning once to brown on both sides.
Never let your husband know how easy they are to prepare.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli until crisp and tender.
Melt butter; stir in flour.
When blended, add chicken broth, stirring rapidly. Continue to cook, stirring, until thick and smooth.
Add broccoli and simmer for 5 minutes.
Ladle into blender and blend until smooth.
Return to saucepan and bring to a boil.
Add milk, cheese and nutmeg; stir until cheese melts.
Serves 2.

title: mississippi mud bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat butter, sugar, egg and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Mix in flour, baking soda and salt. Stir in half of the semi-sweet, half of the white chocolate and half of the walnuts.

Spread in greased foil lined 9-inch square baking pan. Bake 25 minutes or until toothpick comes out almost clean. Sprinkle with remaining chocolates. Cover with foil and let stand 5 minutes. Swirl melted chocolates with knife to marbleize. Sprinkle with remaining nuts. Cool and cut into bars.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix the sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine (cut in small pieces) and bring to a boil.
Boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla flavoring and peanut butter and stir until melted.
Add oatmeal and stir.
Drop on waxed paper by spoonfuls.

title: crabcakes
directions: Saute celery and parsley in butter.
Mix in the crabmeat and add other ingredients.
Shape into 6 cakes.
Dust with cracker meal.
Put on a small cookie sheet and bake in a 375° oven for about 15 minutes or until browned.

title: bro.  farmer's cornbread
directions: Mix all together.
Put in a hot, greased iron skillet.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: rhubarb jam
directions: Cut rhubarb in small pieces.
Add sugar and water.
Cook until rhubarb has mashed up well.
Add Jell-O and bring to a boil.
Cool and bottle up.
Must be kept in refrigerator.

title: asparagus salad
directions: Soak gelatin in 1/2 cup cold water.
Heat to boiling the remaining 1 cup of water with the sugar, vinegar and salt.
Add gelatin mixture to hot liquid.
Stir until dissolved.
Cool, then add remaining ingredients, including the can of asparagus (including the liquid for asparagus).
Pour into a 7 x 11-inch dish.
Chill until set.
Cut into squares.
Garnish with lettuce and mayonnaise.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix
ham, pork, ground beef, eggs, graham cracker crumbs and milk
well.
Shape
into balls.
Mix tomato soup, mustard, vinegar and sugar.
Pour over meat balls.
Bake 1 hour at 350°. Double recipe for sauce, but make each batch separately.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: strawberry topping for angel food cake
directions: Beat with electric mixer on high for 25 minutes or until holds stiff peaks (do not underbeat).
Spread on cake, garnish with whole berries.

title: louise's sauerkraut balls
directions: Cook sausage and onion, drain.
Add 3 tablespoons bread crumbs and sauerkraut in a bowl.
Combine cream cheese, mustard, pepper and garlic salt.
Stir in sausage mixture.
Chill. Shape into balls; coat each ball in flour, dip in eggs and milk.
Then roll in bread crumbs.
Deep fry (takes only a minute or two).
Freeze when cool.
Heat in oven for 15 minutes when ready to serve (350°).
Makes about 35 to 40.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients, including the nuts.
Mix well in bowl, add liquids that have been mixed together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 3 one-pound loaves or 6 small loaves (if baked in tin cans, 1 pound coffee cans, fill only 2/3 full).

title: zucchini in cream
directions: Mix all ingredients lightly.
Pour in greased baking pan. Bake 1 hour in 375° oven or until squash is tender.

title: pesto shrimp and scallops
directions: Cook and peel shrimp; set aside.
Cut scallops in 1/2.
Start water boiling for pasta.
Mix pesto, sun-dried tomatoes and wine cooler in frying pan; heat thoroughly.
Add scallops and cook until almost done.
Add shrimp until hot.
Cook pasta and drain; put back in same pan.
Pour shrimp and scallop mixture into pasta; mix up, heat and serve.
Makes 2 to 3 servings.

title: lemon zucchini bread
directions: Blend together sugar, eggs, oil, lemon peel and extract.
Sift flour, baking soda, baking powder and spices; add alternately with zucchini.
Add nuts.

title: spice cookies
directions: Cream
shortening
and	sugar.	Add
eggs and molasses. Sift dry
ingredients
and
add	to sugar mixture.
Form dough into balls
the size of walnuts.
Dip one side into granulated sugar. Place sugared side up
on
cookie
sheet, allowing for spread. They will rise and then
flatten.
Bake 15 minutes in hot 375° oven.

title: little smokies
directions: Tear crescent rolls into small pieces, enough to be able to wrap around each Smokie.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
(There are approximately 50 Smokies in a package.)

title: eggplant italiano
directions: Peel and slice, 1/2-inch thick, the eggplant.
Dip in milk, then in bread crumbs.
Fry in oil until golden brown.
Meanwhile, slice 1 zucchini 1/2-inch and arrange on bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with browned 1/3 eggplant, 1/3 cheese and 1/3 sauce.
Layer zucchini, eggplant sauce and cheese until gone.
Top with Parmesan cheese crumb mixture.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes, covered and 15 minutes, uncovered.
Serve with French bread, garlic bread and/or cooked fettuccini.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix Jell-O in 2 cups hot water.
Add pineapple and blueberry and let congeal.

title: mother's best fudge cake
directions: Combine chocolate, 1/2 cup milk, well beaten egg and 2/3 cup sugar in saucepan; cook over low heat until thickened, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Thoroughly cream shortening, 1 cup sugar and vanilla.
Beat in eggs 1 at a time.
Sift dry ingredients together; add alternately with 2/3 cup milk.
Blend in chocolate mixture. Pour into 2 paper (wax) lined 9 x 1 1/2-inch round pans.
Bake in moderate oven, 350°, for 25 to 30 minutes.
Frost with Chocolate Satin Frosting.

title: cinnamon pecans
directions: Mix first 3, then add last 3 ingredients. Cook on medium heat. Stir often until sugar begins to crystallize on pecans. Take from heat. Stir until well coated. Spread on wax paper until cool.

title: beef and macaroni
directions: In a large saucepan, combine shortening, beef, green pepper and onion.
Cook until lightly brown, stirring occasionally to break up meat.
Add soup, catsup, salt, pepper and water.
Mix well.

title: garlic potatoes(or "lauren's favorite potatoes")
directions: Cut unpared potatoes into 1/4-inch slices.
Put them into a buttered 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Mix the butter and oil together and brush the slices with it.
Sprinkle with garlic, salt and thyme.
Bake in a 400° oven for about 45 minutes, or until the potatoes are browned on edges.
Serves 4.

title: sweet potato-cashew bake
directions: Prepare and cook sweet potatoes (whole).
Combine brown sugar, cashews, ginger and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Drain peaches well.
In a 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish, layer half each of sweet potatoes, peaches and brown sugar mixture.
Repeat layers.
Dot with butter. Bake, covered, in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Uncover, bake another 10 minutes.
Top with brown sugar mixture after baking. Serves 6.

title: fluffy banana pudding
directions: Pour milk in a large bowl.
Add pudding mix.
Beat with a wire whisk for 1 to 2 minutes or until well blended.
Refrigerate 1 hour.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cut Provolone, salami, pepperoni and tomatoes into 1/2-inch chunks. Mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix together and form into balls.
Put in casserole and pour tomato soup over top.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: freezer cole slaw
directions: Pour over cabbage mixture and stir.
Package in freezer containers.

title: italian style pork chops
directions: Brown 4 to 6 pork chops in Crisco and drain.
While browning chops, mix in saucepan the tomato sauce, mushroom pieces, garlic, onion and other spices.

title: pound cake
directions: Beat egg whites and add 6 teaspoons of sugar and put in refrigerator.
Beat yellow of eggs, shortening, butter and sugar for 20 minutes, then add flour and milk alternately.
Fold in egg whites and put in a tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: shoe peg corn salad
directions: Drain corn and add diced vegetables.
Combine sugar, oil, vinegar, salt and pepper and pour over vegetables.
Store in covered container and refrigerate overnight.
Drain and serve. Keeps well for several days.

title: peanut butter play dough(child-approved)
directions: Measure peanut butter into a large bowl.
Add honey.
Stir in powdered milk a little at a time.
As mixture becomes stiff, use clean hands to make it into a pliable dough.
Mold into shapes or roll with a rolling pin and cut with cookie cutters. Decorate, then eat!

title: cream waffles
directions: Cream together butter and brown sugar.
Mix in egg and buttermilk.
Mix together oats, flour, baking powder, salt and allspice; add to creamed mixture.
Stir in bananas.
Spoon into greased or paper lined muffin pan, filling almost full.
Bake at 400° to 425° for 20 to 25 minutes, until golden brown.

title: green pea salad(12 servings)
directions: Drain peas well. Add other vegetables. Stir in small amount of mayonnaise, salt and pepper. Refrigerate. Very good.

title: "dirt" cake
directions: You also need 1 (8-inch) plastic flowerpot or any large container (with high sides).

title: apple dip
directions: Blend together cream cheese and marshmallow cream.
Serve immediately with apple chunks.

title: spinach salad
directions: Mix together well.
Make dressing and pour over salad.

title: sweet and sour chicken wings
directions: Rinse chicken; pat dry.
Cut off and discard wing tips.
Cut each wing at joint to make 2 sections.
In a shallow dish, combine flour, garlic salt and lemon-pepper seasoning; coat chicken pieces with flour mixture.
Heat oil in a 12-inch skillet.
Add coated chicken pieces and cook until brown, turning occasionally.

Remove chicken from skillet and arrange pieces in a shallow baking dish. In a medium saucepan, combine the sugar, vinegar, pineapple juice, ketchup and soy sauce; heat to boiling, stirring to dissolve the sugar.
Pour over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 30 minutes, turning over after 15 minutes.

title: cream cheese coffee cake
directions: Grease and flour spring-form pan.
Combine flour and 3/4 cup sugar.
Cut in margarine with pastry blender to coarse crumbs. Reserve 1 cup.
To remaining, add baking powder, baking soda, salt, sour cream, 1 egg and almond extract; blend well.
Spread over bottom and sides of pan (1/4 inch on sides).

title: lasagne
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions. Brown ground beef, garlic and onion. Drain grease.
Add parsley, basil, salt, oregano, tomatoes and tomato paste.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
In bowl, mix together cottage cheese, Mozzarella cheese and Parmesan cheese.
