Place half of the noodles in a 13 x 9-inch casserole dish, then half of the cheese mixture, then half of the meat sauce. Repeat. Cook at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: congo squares
directions: Mix together melted butter and brown sugar; add flour and eggs alternately.
Stir in pecans and chocolate chips.
Pour into a greased and floured 9x13 baking pan.
Bake 40-45 minutes at 300°.
Cool and cut in squares to serve.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Boil sweet potatoes until tender.
Place in a baking dish. Mix last 4 ingredients and cook until thick.
Pour over potatoes.

title: pumpkin dream dessert
directions: First Layer:
Cut 1 cup oleo into 2 cups flour until crumbly. Add 1 cup chopped nuts.
Press into lightly greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: hot banana peppers
directions: Soak (cut or whole) peppers in ice cold saltwater for 3 hours. Change water often.
Boil together oil, sugar and vinegar.
Let cool completely.
Drain peppers and pack in jars.
Pour liquid over peppers.
Sprinkle garlic salt and basil over peppers, if desired. Seal.

title: green rice casserole
directions: Cook the broccoli according to package directions; drain well.
In a large bowl, combine the broccoli, rice, soup, and butter.
Add the Cheez Whiz, reserve a small amount for the top of the casserole.
Stir until butter and Cheez Whiz are blended in. Transfer to a greased casserole and top with remaining Cheez Whiz. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until the top starts to bubble.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Blend all ingredients except coconut in a large mixing bowl. Beat 4 minutes at medium speed.
Pour into 2 greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly pressed.
Do not overbake.
Cool in pan 15 minutes, then turn onto cooling rack.
When cake is cold, frost.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Keep refrigerated.

title: beans
directions: Make the day before so flavor goes through.
Heat when you make it.
Heat the next day for 1 1/2 to 2 hours, uncovered.
It works good in a slow cooker (cook longer).

title: trifle
directions: Slice pound cake.
Spread with raspberry jam (like a sandwich).
Spread over bottom of a trifle bowl.
Sprinkle with sherry or peach Schnapps.
Drain peaches.
Sprinkle some of the juice over the cake, then spread the fruit over all.
Pour the partially set jello over top and let set until firm.
Make up 1 envelope of custard; cool and pour over top. Cover with whipped cream or Cool Whip.
Decorate top with cherries, slices of kiwi or nuts, as desired.

title: fruitcake squares
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Line a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan with foil.
Lightly grease foil.
In a large bowl, beat margarine and sugar with electric mixer until pale and fluffy.
Beat in egg, vanilla and citrus peel.
Gradually stir in flour until blended, then chopped fruits.
Spread in prepared pan.
Bake 30 minutes until set and lightly golden around edges.
Cool in pan on wire rack.
Sprinkle generously with confectioners sugar.
Cut into 2-inch squares.
Decorate tops with cherry pieces.
Store cookies airtight in cool place up to 2 weeks.
Yield: 24 squares.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Bake crust first according to package directions on a pizza pan.
Combine sour cream, mayonnaise and Ranch dressing.
Spread over cooled baked crust.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and add your favorite raw veggies.
Don't cook vegetables.

title: pineapple sheet cake
directions: Mix together ingredients.
Do not overmix and do not use mixer.
Spray bottom (not sides) of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Soak bread in milk.
Mix remaining ingredients and add; mix well.
Bake in loaf pan 1 hour at 350°.

title: bacardi frozen fruit strawberry or pina colada pie
directions: Mix strawberry daiquiri, Eagle Brand milk and Cool Whip together real good, then put in crusts and freeze.
Take out when needed.
Very good.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, flour and salt.
Add milk, water and butter.
Cook over medium flame, stirring until boiling.
Cook 5 minutes longer constantly stirring.
Cool; stir in vanilla.
Keep in refrigerator and use as needed.

title: fructose candy cookies (soft)(jason poti and family)
directions: Place each
cookie
2-inches
apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Best
to
put one cookie sheet at a time in 350° oven. Use
ice cream
scoop to measure cookies.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool 1 minute on sheet and remove.

title: pizza
directions: Measure warm water into a bowl.
Add yeast; stir until dissolved.
Add flour; beat.
Turn dough onto floured surface; knead until smooth.
Roll out onto greased baking sheet.
Layer other ingredients on top; bake at 375° until done.

title: baked flounder stuffed
directions: In a 10-inch skillet, cook bread crumbs in the butter or margarine over medium heat until golden brown and crisp.
Remove crumbs to mixing bowl.
In the same skillet, melt butter or margarine.
Add green onions, celery, green pepper and garlic. Cook over medium heat until vegetables are tender.
Add vegetables to bread crumbs.
Stir chopped shrimp, crab meat, parsley, salt, red pepper and black pepper into bread mixture.
Rinse fish and pat dry.
To cut a pocket, place flounder on a board, dark side up. Make a slit in the center of fish, cutting lengthwise along backbone.
Cut a pocket on both sides of first cut.
Stuff fish loosely with bread mixture.
Place fish in a greased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Brush fish with butter.
Bake in a 400° oven about 20 minutes or until fish flakes easily with a fork. Transfer fish to a serving platter.
Garnish the cooked fish with lime slices and green onion, if desired.
Makes 4 servings.

title: garlic nibbles
directions: Mix oil, herbs, garlic and dressing mix.
Place crackers on cookie sheet.
Pour sauce over.
Toss to mix 3 or 4 times over an hour or so.
Store in tin or Baggie.

title: toll house marble squares
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch.
Mix butter, sugars and vanilla thoroughly.
Beat egg.
Blend in flour, soda and salt.
Mix in walnuts.
Spread in prepared pan.
Sprinkle chocolate morsels over top of dough.
Place in oven 1 minute. Remove from oven and run knife through dough to marbleize.
Return to oven; bake 12 to 14 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into 2-inch squares. Makes 2 dozen.

title: pinto bean casserole
directions: In large skillet, brown beef, onions and pepper.
Add all ingredients, except cornbread mix and pour into 9 x 12 x 2-inch greased pan.
Mix package of cornbread mix as stated on package and pour over top.
Bake at 425° until brown.

title: sausage corn bake
directions: Combine all ingredients except cracker crumbs, mixing well. Spoon into a lightly greased 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking pan; sprinkle with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until done.
Makes 6 servings.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Saute onions and celery in skillet with small amount of margarine.
Add to chicken, then add cream cheese and mayonnaise to salad consistency.
Bake in dish sprayed with Pam.
Sprinkle with cheese and potato chips.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until top is brown.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: all-purpose punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid as instructed on package.
Add orange juice, pineapple juice and lemon juice; mix.
Add ginger ale before serving.

title: zucchini cookies
directions: Cream together sugar, margarine and egg until fluffy.
Then add remaining ingredients.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature.
In a large mixing bowl, mix all ingredients.
Pour into a greased 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until a knife comes out clean when inserted in middle of dish.
It should be golden brown and bubbly on top.
Serves 6.

title: recipe for a great marriage
directions: Add handfuls of:
risking, forgiving, healing, commitment, romance and prayer.

title: fruit roll
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, salt and yeast.
Cut in margarine. Add egg yolks.
Roll into a ball and cut into 4 pieces. Refrigerate 8 hours or overnight.

title: halloween cookie pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Lightly grease a 12 inch pizza pan. In a large mixer bowl, beat sugar and margarine until creamy. Add egg, water and vanilla. Beat well. In a separate bowl, stir together flour, soda and salt. Add to sugar mixture, beating on low until blended. Stir in peanut butter chips. Spread batter in prepared pan to within 1/2 inch of edge. Bake 11 to 13 minutes or until set. Remove from oven. Sprinkle marshmallows, chocolate chips and nuts over top. Return to oven. Bake 5 to 7 minutes or until marshmallows are lightly browned. Cool completely.

title: blueberry french toast
directions: Slice bread diagonally 3/4-inch thick.
Place in 10 x 15-inch pan.
In bowl, beat eggs and milk plus baking powder and vanilla. Pour slowly over bread, turning to coat.
Cover with plastic wrap and put in refrigerator overnight.
In morning, place 4 cups frozen blueberries, 1/2 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon in greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Place bread, wet side up, on berries. Wedge slices together.
Brush top of bread with 2 tablespoons melted butter.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until toast is golden brown and berries are bubbling around the sides.
Remove from oven and sift powdered sugar on top.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: corn dip
directions: Boil corn, salt and garlic.
Add cream cheese and remaining ingredients while still hot.

title: never fail brownie pie
directions: Blend melted butter and chocolate with all other ingredients. Pour into a greased 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve hot with ice cream.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken loaf
directions: Combine chicken, bread crumbs, rice, onion, salt, green pepper and broth.
Stir in eggs.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch greased cake pan at 325° for 1 hour.

title: easy and good chicken
directions: Wash and season chicken.
Place in glass dish.
Leave uncovered and place in microwave for 25 minutes on High.
Place in oven at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and rice separately and set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients together in large bowl.
Add broccoli and rice to mixture.
Pour into an ungreased 10-inch square dish.
Put additional shredded Cheddar cheese on top if want.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: sweet potato cheesecake
directions: Crust:	Combine
crumbs
and
margarine.
Press mixture onto bottom and 1
inch up sides of an 8-inch spring-form pan. Set aside.

title: sweet potato balls
directions: Mash potatoes, add butter, milk, salt and rind.
With a tablespoon, scoop up about 1/4 cup mixture and shape around marshmallows.
Roll each ball in corn flakes.

title: baked rice custard
directions: Beat eggs, sugar salt and vanilla.
Don't overbeat.
Then slowly add scalded milk while mixing so eggs don't cook.
Sprinkle top with nutmeg.
Set bowl in pan of warm water.
Bake about 1 hour at 350° or until knife comes out clean when inserted in middle.

title: coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Cool 15 minutes.
Poke holes down through cake with a utility fork.

title: velveeta cheese fudge
directions: In saucepan melt butter and cheese.
Sift sugar and cocoa together, then add to cheese/butter mixture.
Add vanilla and nuts (if desired).
Mix well and spread evenly in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool.
Cut into pieces.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Melt butter in heavy skillet.
Mix in all vegetables.
Add all seasonings, then shrimp.
Stir constantly.
Cook on low heat for approximately 30 minutes to 1 hour.
Serve over fluffy rice.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix all meatball ingredients and shape into small balls.
Bake at 400° approximately 30 minutes until done.
I bake on broiler pan so grease drains.

title: chicken and sausage casserole
directions: Boil chicken.
Cook rice according to directions on box.
Fry sausage in skillet and pour off fat.
Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Bake in casserole dish at 375° for 30 minutes or until browned on top.
A 9 x 13-inch pan is nice, as the casserole cooks faster and the portions aren't too thick.

title: quick and easy
directions: Wrap each cracker with 1/2 slice of bacon.
Bake at 250° for 50 minutes.
Store in airtight tin.

title: citric acid punch
directions: Dissolve sugar, citric acid and water and let cool.
Add remaining ingredients.
May use sweetened or unsweetened juice. Makes 2 gallons, 64 (1/2-cup) servings.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine sugars, oil and eggs. Add pumpkin. Sift dry ingredients and add to pumpkin mixture. Add water. Bake in greased and floured 1 pound coffee cans or bread pans. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: corny beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onions in skillet.
Cook noodles according to package.
Drain.
Mix all other ingredients in bowl. Add meat and onions.
Toss in cooked noodles and put in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: low-fat chalupas
directions: Preheat oven to 500°.
Place tortillas directly on the rack; heat until crisp (watch them closely, or they will burn).
Heat beans in the microwave until hot.
Place the hot tortilla on a cookie sheet; spread the beans on the tortilla.
Add grated cheese.
Place in the oven until the cheese melts.
Sprinkle shredded lettuce, tomato, onion and peppers on top.
Season with salt, pepper and picante sauce.
Enjoy!

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Melt together the chocolate and butter.
Cool well.
Mix together the sugar, eggs, flour, dash of salt and vanilla.
Mix together.
Stir in the pecans and pour into well buttered 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool.
Top with Cool Whip and serve with shaved chocolate.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Pat dough into pizza pan to resemble pizza crust.
Bake at 325°
until golden brown.
Cool.
Beat cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip until creamy.
Spread on cooled crust.
Place fruit on pizza in circular pattern so each piece has each fruit.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Boil sugar, Karo and water until thread spins or 250° temperature.
Then add peanuts and stir continuously after peanuts are added.
Cook until temperature reaches 280°.
Take from fire; add butter, salt and soda.
Pour onto buttered board to cool.

title: lemon tea cookies
directions: Stir lemon juice into milk; set aside.
Stir together flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Beat butter for 30 seconds; add sugar and beat until fluffy.
Add egg and lemon peel; beat well. Add dry ingredients and milk mixture alternately to beaten mixture, beating well after each addition.
Drop from a teaspoon 2 inches apart on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes.
Remove at once on a wire rack; brush Lemon Glaze over.
Makes 48.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Mix all ingredients and heat slowly. Bring to a boil.
Boil slowly for 2 minutes. Remove from heat and beat until cool (or begins to thicken).
Spread on cake.

title: pralines
directions: Use your favorite large pot.
Be sure it's big enough to prevent boilovers as the candy does need a lot of room to bubble up.
Pour into the pot buttermilk, granulated sugar and baking soda.
That's it!

title: okra and potatoes
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients until tender.
Heat iron skillet with tablespoon oil.
Add okra mixture and potatoes.
Stir and cook until lightly browned.
Serves 6 to 8.
Ingredients may be adjusted and amounts of potato or okra may vary.
This recipe may also be used with squash rather than okra.

title: turkey burger
directions: Mix ingredients.
Patty turkey up and pan-fry.
Even great for the grill or oven bake.
(Substitute turkey for your usual ground beef.)

title: olive spread with walnuts
directions: Finely chop black olives and 3 Tbsp toasted walnuts in processor. Add olive oil, Dijon mustard, garlic, thyme, oregano, sage and cayenne pepper and process until coarsely pureed. Stir in remaining 1/4 c chopped toasted walnuts. Serve on French-bread baguette slices that have been brushed with olive oil and toasted in a 350 degree oven until golden. Makes about 1 1/3 cups.

title: pop pete's banana pudding
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and milk. Put in 2-quart microwave dish and nuke 7 to 8 minutes, until it gets warm. Continue to stop and stir to prevent lumping. Then add your egg yolks. Add vanilla and teaspoon of butter. Then add your bananas. Beat egg whites until stiff. Then add 2 teaspoons of sugar and a teaspoon vanilla. Mix thoroughly. In your pie dish, layer vanilla wafers, banana slices, then pour pie mixture over. Optional: Add more bananas. Then add icing meringue. Cook at 350° until brown.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt butter and mix with crumbs.
Spread in casserole dish.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: brown sugar nut brownies
directions: In a large bowl with an electric mixer, beat together the sugar, the brown sugar, the corn syrup and the butter until the mixture is smooth and creamy.
Add the eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition and stir in the chocolate, the flour and a pinch of salt.
Reserve 25 whole nuts.
Chop the remaining and stir them into the batter.
Pour the batter into a buttered and floured 9-inch baking pan, smoothing the top and arrange the remaining nuts on top.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes or until the batter pulls away slightly from the side.
Cool completely before cutting.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Cut tomatoes with 1/4-inch slices.
Season with salt and pepper.
Dredge with cornmeal.
Heat bacon drippings in heavy skillet.
Add tomatoes and fry slowly until browned, turning once.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix and pour into pie shell.
Makes 2 pies.

title: soft scrambled eggs
directions: Heat butter in skillet.
Beat eggs and water or Pet milk in skillet.
Stir with fork until whites cook.
Serve with toast, sausage, etc.

title: magic apple pie
directions: Mix and beat together.
Pour into greased pie pan.
In a 350° oven, bake for 30 minutes.
Cut into wedges and serve.
It has a magic crust.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: In a bowl, beat together cream cheese, margarine and vanilla until light and fluffy. Gradually add 2 cups powdered sugar and beat well. Beat in enough of the remaining powdered sugar to make frosting of spreading consistency.
Spread on cake.
Cover cake and store in refrigerator.

title: baked carrots
directions: Wash and scrape carrots.
Cut in half lengthwise and crosswise. Place in a baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Sprinkle mixture over the carrots, then pour boiling water over all.
Cover and bake in a 350° oven for about an hour and a half.

title: tomato sauce
directions: Scald, peel tomatoes; cook 15 minutes. Drain off half the juice. Chop remaining vegetables; add tomatoes; simmer about 1 1/2 hours. Tie spices in cloth bag; add with remaining ingredients to tomato mixture; continue cooking 1 1/2 hours. Remove spices; seal in hot sterilized jars. Makes 6 pints.

title: corn meal rolls
directions: Combine and cook until thick corn meal, sugar, salt, shortening and milk.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add eggs and yeast that has been dissolved in warm water.
Beat well.
Add flour.
Turn out on floured board and knead until smooth and satiny.
Let rise 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Shape into rolls.
Let rise again until double in bulk.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.

title: sunshine cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients 3 times; pour in milk, stir.
Fold in egg whites and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: banana oatmeal cookies
directions: In a large bowl, cream sugar, shortening, eggs and vanilla. Combine flour, baking soda, cloves and cinnamon.
Add to the creamed mixture.
Stir in bananas, oats and chocolate chips.
Drop by rounded tsp. onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375 degrees for 10-12 minutes.
Immediately remove cookies to wire racks to cool.
Yield about 4 dozen.

title: amish sugar cookies
directions: Combine sugar, oleo and oil; beat well.
Add eggs; beat again. Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Flatten with a fork.
Bake at 375° for about 10 to 12 minutes.

title: farmers chop suey
directions: Combine all vegetables with cottage cheese.
Season to taste. Top with sour cream; refrigerate.

title: green tomato pie
directions: To peel tomatoes easily, immerse in boiling water until skins will slip off (about 3 minutes).

title: buttermilk cinnamon bread
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt. In a small bowl combine oil and 1 1/2 cups sugar.
Add buttermilk and eggs; mix well.
Stir into dry ingredients just until moistened.
Fill two greased 8 x 4 x 2-inch or five 5 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pans about 1/3 full.
Combine cinnamon and remaining sugar; sprinkle half over the batter.
Top with remaining batter and cinnamon-sugar.
Swirl batter with a knife.
Sprinkle with nuts. Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean.
Cool in pans for 10 minutes before removing to a wire rack.
Yield:
2 loaves or 5 mini loaves.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Cook carrots in small amount of water until done.
Drain and put in casserole dish.
Combine mayonnaise, onion, horseradish, salt and pepper.
Spoon over carrots.
Mix butter with saltines and sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Add lemon juice to salmon.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake in greased baking dish for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: sherry's mozetti
directions: Prepare noodles according to package.
Brown beef and onion. Drain off excess fat.
Combine ingredients except cheese and mix. Pour into casserole and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° until hot and cheese is bubbly.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Mix cheese and cracker crumbs; add melted butter.
Mix asparagus juice with the cream of mushroom soup and heat.
Place 1/2 of cracker mix in bottom of greased casserole.
Place asparagus on top of this; cover with 1/2 cup of chopped pecans. Pour soup mix over all.
Sprinkle remaining crumbs over top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Baking dish which has been sprayed with non-stick cooking oil (or grease well).

title: easy cheese twists
directions: Separate biscuits; roll each biscuit into a 10 inch strip and twist.
Bring around in a circle and seal ends by pinching dough. Brush with beaten egg and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at temperature and time indicated on can of biscuits.
Cool slightly before serving.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together at one time.
Grease and flour, very well, a Bundt pan.
After mixing all ingredients about 3 minutes with electric mixer, pour into prepared Bundt pan.
Bake at 375° exactly 40 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Brown chicken in
a
small
amount of butter or Crisco. Remove chicken
from
pan;
to drippings add other ingredients (except rice).
Bring to a boil.

title: angel hair spaghetti salad
directions: Cook and rinse spaghetti in cold water; mix with other ingredients and chill overnight.

title: sauerkraut cake
directions: Cream butter with sugar.
Beat eggs with vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients; add alternately with water and egg mixture.
Stir in thoroughly rinsed and chopped kraut.
Turn into greased and floured 8 inch square or round pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Cool on rack.
Top with Mocha Cream Frosting.

title: brown rice
directions: Mix ingredients into a casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool for 2 minutes.
Ready to serve.

title: apricot coconut balls
directions: Grind apricots.
Combine apricots and coconut.
Mix well.
Add condensed milk and blend.
Shape into small balls and roll in confectioners sugar.
Makes approximately 32.
Great at Christmas.

title: chicken bog
directions: Bring to a boil; simmer 20 minutes.
Let set on stove and cut off.
When cooking chicken, add 2 onions and season to taste (salt and pepper).
If you want puffier rice, add a little more broth.

title: eagle brand milk pound cake
directions: Cream the sugar, butter and Eagle Brand milk together.
Add eggs one at a time; beat well.
Add salt and baking powder to flour and add 1 cup at a time to creamed mixture.
Add milk and flavorings; mix well.
Add coconut, nuts or pineapple for variations.
Pour in tube pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
You may need to add a strip of foil to top of pan if your pan is not very deep.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into pie shell. Cook at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: fudge pecan chewies
directions: Combine oleo, milk and chocolate in heavy saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until chocolate is melted. Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla, flour and chopped pecans. Spoon out onto greased sheets (teaspoon).
Put pecan in center of each.
Bake at 350° for 7 minutes; do not overbake.
Let cool for short time before putting on rack.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix in a large bowl the eggs, sugar and oil; beat at medium speed about 1 minute.
Sift flour and cinnamon together.
Add to egg mixture.
Mix thoroughly.
Add carrots and 1/2 cup pecans, mix well.
Pour into 2 greased 8 or 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: apple upside down cake
directions: Use a 9-1/2 inch skillet or 8 inch pan.
Toss apple slices in plenty of cinnamon and sugar.
Spray skillet with oil. Sprinkle sides and bottom with a generous amount of cinnamon and sugar. Place apples in skillet.
Mix together eggs, sugar, salted butter, vanilla, flour and baking powder.
Cover apples well. Bake at 375 degrees for 45 minutes. Cool slightly and turn out on plate.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Stir in eggs, milk and vanilla. Set aside.
Sift together flour, soda, cinnamon, salt, baking powder and cloves.
Add flour mixture to mixture you set aside. Add in persimmon puree.
Mix well.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 1 hour at 350°.
May add Cool Whip or whipping cream to top of pudding.

title: victoria's grape jam
directions: Thank God for dirty dishes,

title: peaches 'n cream pie
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Blend in sugar and 2 tablespoons milk.
Fold in 2 cups of whipped topping and spread in crust.
Top with diced peaches, pressing down lightly.
Chill. Prepare pudding mix with 1 cup milk as directed on package.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Fold in remaining whipped topping and spoon over cheese mixture.
Freeze 1 hour or chill in refrigerator 3 hours before serving.
Garnish with remaining whipped topping and peach slices if desired.

title: fudgy brownies
directions: In a
small bowl, combine cocoa and oil until smooth.
In another bowl, beat eggs, then add vanilla and cocoa mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in flour and salt just until moistened.
Fold in walnuts.
Pour into a greased 8 inch square baking pan and sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Bake at 325 degrees for 35 minutes.

title: stuffed eggplant
directions: Wash and peel the eggplant; cut in half lengthwise and remove the seeds.
Mince the water chestnuts and combine with the pork or beef, onion, ginger, sherry, soy sauce, salt and sugar.
Mix well. Stuff each half of the eggplant with the mixture.
Steam for 30 minutes.
Serves 2.

title: cranberry hamburg loaf
directions: Spread the sugar over the bottom of a greased loaf pan. Spread cranberry sauce over the sugar.
Combine all other ingredients in a bowl and mix well.
Put the meat mixture on top of the cranberry sauce.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool 10 minutes and turn onto the serving platter.

title: easy red beans and rice
directions: Combine all ingredients, except rice.
Bring to a boil, then simmer 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve over rice.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: glurch or "silly putty"
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
If too sticky, add small amounts of liquid starch until rubbery.
Store in airtight container in refrigerator.

title: coconut cake
directions: Cook cake according to directions on back of box.
While cake is baking, mix Cool Whip, 3 ounces of coconut and powdered sugar. Mix well.
Put in refrigerator.
When cake is completely cool, put the refrigerated mixture on the cake and sprinkle remaining coconut on top and sides.

title: grasshopper salad
directions: Drain and save juice from pineapple.
Add enough water to the juice to make 3 3/4 cups.
Heat the juice and water and dissolve the jello.
Place cream cheese and jello mixture in a mixer. Blend until smooth.
Stir in sugar, pecans, cherries and pineapple.
Chill until set.

title: apricot salad
directions: Crush apricots with a fork.
Melt jello in the boiling water and cool.
Mix together.
Add ice cream and chill.

title: pork chops with mushroom soup
directions: Brown pork chops after rolling chops in flour.
Mix soup and milk.
Pour over browned chops.
Cook 45 minutes to 1 hour on low heat.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Mix vegetables in a large mixing bowl and toss lightly.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over vegetables.
Chill about 12 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cook over medium heat until thick. Pour into a baked pie shell.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Brown beef; drain.
Combine beef, beans and spices.
Place 4 noodles in bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread half of beef mixture over noodles, cover with light layer of salsa.
Repeat noodles and beef mixture.
Cover with remaining noodles.
Combine water and salsa.
Pour over all.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Combine sour cream, onions and olives.
Spread on top.
Top with cheese.
Bake, uncovered, until cheese is melted.

title: alice's barbecue beans
directions: Empty beans into a pot.
Add ketchup, mustard, maple syrup, oregano, cloves and bay leaves.
Fry bacon slightly and add to beans.

In pan used for bacon, fry mushrooms till brown, fry onions until transparent and green peppers until crisp stage. Stir well and pour into casserole dish(es) and bake 2 hours at 275°. If more than one casseroles made, freeze the unused portion and cook for two hours later.
Or, can freeze mixture after it is cooked - then simply warm up.

title: quick and easy chicken casserole
directions: Note:
Can substitute with can of mushroom soup and sprinkle with cheese.

title: cream soup
directions: Scald milk and add butter and seasoning; thickens with flour which has been mixed with a little cold water.
Thin with boiling water and boil 2 minutes.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Mix pancake mix, salt, milk and beaten eggs.
Stir slightly. Fold in potatoes, onion and butter.
Pour 1/4 cup batter for each pancake on a hot, lightly oiled griddle.
Bake to a golden brown, turning only once.
Serve with hot applesauce.

title: broccoli-chicken casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and chicken.
Mix the next 4 ingredients in a bowl.
Spread a thin layer over the bottom of baking dish.
Place a layer of broccoli next, then a layer of chicken, layer of broccoli and another layer of chicken.
Pour remaining soup mixture over the top.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Cook chicken and tear in pieces; put in bottom of 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Mix sour cream; pour over chicken.
Smash crackers; mix with the melted butter and put on top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: cowboy bean bake
directions: Brown hamburger with onion.
Drain.
Combine macaroni, beans, hamburger, soup and 1/2 cup of water.
Sprinkle brown sugar on top.

title: barbecue meatballs
directions: Mix hamburger, crackers, eggs and onion together.
Form into meatballs.
Place in bottom of roaster.
Mix remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Pour over meatballs and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: molded tuna luncheon salad
directions: Mix jello in 1/2 cup boiling water.
Add soup, tuna, celery, pecans or almonds, Cool Whip and mayonnaise.
Mix well. Refrigerate to gel.
Serve with carrot curls, celery top leaves, parsley, etc. (to decorate).

title: cranberry salad
directions: Combine cranberries, pineapple and sugar.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Add whipped cream and mini marshmallows.

title: cherry jubilee
directions: Mix oleo with crumbs, put half in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Mix Dream Whip according to directions.
Add sugar and cream cheese; beat until mixture stands in peak.
Put half over crumbs.
Spread 2 cans of pie filling over whip, cover with remaining whip, then top with crumbs.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: fancy chicken a la king
directions: In a hot skillet cook green pepper and onion until tender, stirring occasionally.
Stir in soup and milk and blend well. Stir in meat, cheese and pimentos.
Cook for 5 minutes until thoroughly heated.
Pour over split biscuits.
Yields 6 servings.

title: roquefort spread
directions: Spread cheese in 9-inch pie plate.
Mix remaining ingredients. Spread over cheese.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Refrigerate for several hours.
Serve with Melba rounds or cocktail pumpernickel.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package.
Place in crock-pot.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Cook on high for 2 hours, then on low for 2 to 3 hours more.

title: ham tetrazzini
directions: Cook spaghetti and mix with Parmesan cheese.
Add cooked ham and toss together.

title: after school "munch mix"
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Mix cereal, raisins, peanuts and cinnamon in large bowl.
Pour melted margarine over mixture; toss to coat. Spread in 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Bake 8 minutes.
Cool. Store in a tightly-covered container.
Makes 4 cups or 8 servings.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg, vanilla and lemon peel. Add dry ingredients with milk alternately.
Roll and cut.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: holiday jingles
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine butter, brown sugar, egg yolk, orange peel and vanilla.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Combine flour and salt.
Shape into 1-inch balls, 1-inch apart.
Press thumb gently in center of each cookie.
In square pan, combine raisins with apple jelly. Fill thumb print with raisin mixture.

title: deer jerky (or beef jerky)
directions: Cut venison into 1/2 x 1/4 x 3-inch slivers.
Mix smoke and soy sauce in bowl.
Add deer meat and soak in refrigerator over night 8-12 hours.
Drain excess liquid in the morning.
Separate slivers and lay on dehydrator trays.
Dehydrate on medium high setting approximately 6-8 hours or more until very leathery and dry but not brittle.
Store in air tight containers or zip lock bags.
Keep in cool and dry place.

title: baked eggplant
directions: Saute onion in oil; add puree, water, salt, oregano and pepper.
Bring to boil.
Simmer 15 minutes.
